label: median longitudinal carina of first metasomal sternum
Defs: The carina that is located in the anteroposterior median line of the first metasomal sternum.

label: front
Defs: A directional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s direction that is similar to the direction of an object to the south when it faces north.

label: prospinasternal apodeme
Defs: The apodeme on the anteroventral margin of the mesopectus that serves as the site of origin of prospinasternal muscles.

label: distolateral galeal sclerite
Defs: The sclerite that is located on the lateral wall of the galeo-lacinial complex distaly of the lateral galeal crease and bears the distolateral galeal setiferous patch.

label: anterior flange of abdominal tergum nine
Defs: The flange that extends along the anterolateral margin of female T9.

label: normal behavioural activity
Defs: A behavioural quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting normal or average activity.

label: male
Defs: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population whose sex organs contain only male gametes.

label: ovipositor muscle
Defs: The abdominal muscle that inserts on the ovipositor.

label: gonostipital arm
Defs: The apodeme that is located proximally on the ventral part of the gonostipes.

label: T8-first valvifer muscle
Defs: The ovipositor muscle that originates from the lateral part of female T8 and inserts on the dorsal margin of the first valvifer.

label: frequency
Defs: A physical quality which inheres in a bearer by virtue of the number of the bearer\'s repetitive actions in a particular time.

label: irregular thickness
Defs: A thickness quality which lacks pattern.

label: petiole width
Defs: The maximum width of the petiole in dorsal view.

label: mesobasalar muscle
Defs: The thoracic muscle that inserts on the mesobasalare.

label: specificity to
Defs: A molecular quality that inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of whether the bearer exhibits the ability of a probe to react precisely with a specific target molecule.

label: antero-lateral region
Defs: Anatomical region that overlaps the anterior and lateral regions of a body or body part.

label: median sclerotized style
Defs: The sclerite that is located ventrally between the penisvalvae.

label: gonostyle/volsella complex
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the sclerites that are located distally of the cupula and surround the aedeagus.

label: partially posterioralized
Defs: A posterioralized quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s gross morphology containing what are normally posterior structures and missing some but not all of what are normally anterior structures.

label: trochanter
Defs: The leg segment that is located proximal to the femur and distal to the coxa.

label: ruptured
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s components being torn, typically used for soft tissues or membranes.

label: acrosternite 2
Defs: The acrosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 2.

label: institutional identification
Defs: A textual entity intended to identify a particular institution

label: dorsolateral orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed dorsolaterally.

label: multi-colored
Defs: A color pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of bearer\'s having two or more hues or degrees of saturation.

label: meconium
Defs: The acellular anatomical structure that is in the hind gut of the pupa.

label: deviation
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s changed direction of position towards another entity.

label: increased fatigability
Defs: A fatigability which is relatively high.

label: axillary sclerite
Defs: The sclerite that is located on the axillary region and articulates with one of the thoracic wing processes.

label: profurco-postoccipital muscle
Defs: The muscle that arises from the profurca and inserts on the postocciput.

label: sternaulus
Defs: The line that marks the site of origin of the mesopleuro-basalare and first mesopleuro-mesonotal muscle.

label: metanotal trough
Defs: The area that is concave, and is delimited medially by the metascutellum, laterally by the supraalar area and posteriorly by the metascutellar arm.

label: dorsal T8-T9 muscle
Defs: The abdominal muscle that arises from the anteromedian margin of female T8 and inserts on the anteromedian margin of the female T9.

label: mesoscutellar-axillar complex
Defs: The area that is located posteriorly of the transscutal line and is composed of the axillae and the mesoscutellum.

label: Metanoto-propodeo-metapecto-mesopectal complex
Defs: The sclerite that is connected anterolaterally and anteroventrally with the pronotum and anterodorsally with the mesoscutellum and the mesopostnotum.

label: quality of a suspension
Defs: A physical quality inhering in an entity by virtue of the bearer\'s solid or liquid constituents being transiently dispersed in a solid, liquid, or gas before settling due to gravity or centrifugal forces.

label: transverse orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed transversely.

label: metanotal flange
Defs: The carina that is transverse and is located on the metascutellum.

label: decreased mobility
Defs: A mobility which is relative low.

label: basal lamina
Defs: Acellular anatomical structure that consists of a thin sheet of fibrous proteins that underlie and support the cells of an epithelium. It separates the cells of an epithelium from any underlying tissue.

label: metapleural arm
Defs: The area that is located anterodorsally on the metapleuron.

label: ventral lock of the femoro-tibial joint
Defs: The lock between a sclerite that is on or continuous with the tibial flexor tendon and the ventral femoral wall.

label: dorsal rim of pronotal plate
Defs: The carina that extends along the posterior border of the pronotal plate.

label: herniated
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s bodily structure that has protruded through an abnormal opening in the wall that contains it.

label: spherical
Defs: A spheroid quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s resembling a ball (a sphere whose equatorial diameter is equal to the polar diameter).

label: trough shaped
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s shape resembling that of a trough, being narrow, long, and boxlike in shape.

label: anterior coxal articular process of the mesotrochanter
Defs: The articular process that is located anteriorly on the proximal margin of the mesotrochanter and bears the anterior coxal fossa of the mesotrochanter.

label: central keel
Defs: The frontal line that is a carina.

label: lathlike
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer resembling a thin narrow strip.

label: distivolsellar apodeme
Defs: The apodeme that is located distally on the parossiculus and is the site of insertion of the gonostyle/volsella complex-gonostyle muscle.

label: sternaulus length
Defs: The straight anatomical line between the anterior and posterior ends of the sternaulus.

label: right angle to
Defs: An angle which is 90 degrees to another entity.

label: decreased humidity
Defs: An decrease in humidity.

label: decreased life span
Defs: A life span which is relatively low.

label: anterior angle of the first valvifer
Defs: The corner on the first valvifer that marks the posterior end of the first valvula.

label: subsalivarial gland
Defs: The gland that is situated ventrally of the salivarium and empties into the salivarium.

label: rotational curvature
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curved around an axis.

label: frontal suture
Defs: The suture that diverges ventrally (or anteriorly) from the coronal suture between the antennal foramina toward the anterior articulations of the mandibles.

label: obtuse angle to
Defs: An angle which is between 90 degrees and 180 degrees to another entity.

label: submarginal vein
Defs: Basal-most portion of the forewing vein complex that occurs behind the costal cell; measured from the constriction that delimits the humeral plate to the point at which the vein touches the leading edge of the wing apically.

label: axial to
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located towards the central axis of the organism or an extremity.

label: sensitivity toward
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to detect or perceive external stimulation.

label: subalar ridge
Defs: The carina that corresponds with the mesepimeral inflection and delimits the subalar area.

label: fragile
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to being easily damaged or destroyed.

label: interpenisvalval muscle
Defs: The male genitalia muscle that connects the valvurae.

label: increased perimeter
Defs: A perimeter which is relatively high.

label: ventromedial cupulo-gonostyle/volsella complex muscle
Defs: The cupulo-gonostyle/volsella complex muscle that inserts medially on the ventral region of the gonostyle/volsella complex.

label: oblanceolate
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being extended along a straight line, and is shaped like a reversed lance-point, with the tapering point attached to the leafstalk.

label: anterior glossal sclerite
Defs: The sclerite of the anterior glossal plate that is lateral to the median conjunctiva of the anterior glossal plate.

label: rod-like sensilla
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of rod-like sensilla and is located apically on the distal labial palp segment.

label: normal mass
Defs: A mass which is relatively normal or average.

label: references section
Defs: A part of a document that has citations as parts

label: seventh flagellomere
Defs: The flagellomere that is located immediately distal to the sixth flagellomere.

label: flow rate
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s motion characteristic.

label: stacked
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being positioned with multiple entities of the same type above and below.

label: mesosterno-mesocoxal muscle
Defs: The mesocoxal muscle that originates at least partly from the mesodiscrimenal lamella and inserts on the mesocoxa.

label: concave
Defs: A shape quality in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s curving inward.

label: parossiculus
Defs: The sclerite that is connected via conjunctiva distomedially to the gonostipes, and articulates with the gonossiculus.

label: count
Defs: A measurement datum that is the output of counting.

label: ventral gonostyle/volsella complex-penisvalval muscle
Defs: The penisvalval muscle that arises ventrally from the gonostyle/volsella complex.

label: nerve conductivity
Defs: A conductivity quality inhering in motor and sensory nerves by virtue of the bearer\'s ability to convey electricity.

label: electric charge
Defs: A molecular quality that inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of the overall electric charge of the molecule, which is due to a comparison between the total number of electrons and the total number of protons.

label: malar line
Defs: The anatomical line that is the shortest between the lower orbit and the ventrolateral margin of the cranium.

label: sessile (sensu zoology)
Defs: A attachment quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s inability to move about.

label: parameral seta
Defs: The seta that is located apically on the gonstyle.

label: friability
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to be reduced to smaller pieces with little effort.

label: notopleural suture
Defs: The suture that is located between the mesonotum and mesopleuron.

label: mesepisternum
Defs: The area that is located anteriorly of the mesepimeral sulcus.

label: reclinate
Defs: A curled quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s edges of its surface being bent down upon their stalk.

label: cup-shaped socket on pleuron
Defs: The projection that is located posteriorly on the subalar area and accommodate the posterior end of the second axillary sclerite of the fore wing at the beginning of the upstroke of the wing.

label: inner lobe of the lacinia
Defs: The lacinial lobe that is medial to the outer lobe of the lacinia.

label: pupal
Defs: A maturity quality inhering in a insect by virtue of the bearer\'s being in the chrysalis (cocoon) or post larval stage.

label: procoxa
Defs: The coxa that is located on the fore leg.

label: medial stipital groove
Defs: The depression that extends medially and adjacent to the medial portion of the principal carina of stipes.

label: distal lobe of the lateral flange of the principal carina of the stipes
Defs: The area of the lateral flange of the principal carina of the stipes distal to the notch of the principal carina of the stipes.

label: furcal pit
Defs: The pit that corresponds to the furca.

label: decreased turgor
Defs: A turgor which is relatively low.

label: assigning a centrally registered identifier
Defs: A planned process in which a new CRID is created, associated with an entity, and stored in the CRID registry thereby registering it as being associated with some entity

label: apical-basal gradient
Defs: Anatomical gradient that is distributed along the apical-basal axis.

label: anatomical region
Defs: A 3D region in space without well-defined compartmental boundaries; for example, the dorsal region of an ectoderm.

label: tooth number 3
Defs: The tooth located proximal to tooth number 2.

label: coxa
Defs: The leg segment that is connected to the body and to the trochanter via conjunctivae and muscles.

label: disrupted
Defs: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being interrupted of its normal course.

label: erose
Defs: A surface feature shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having an irregularly toothed edge.

label: ocellar fovea
Defs: The depression that extends along the lateral margin of a lateral ocellus or along anterior margin of the anterior ocellus.

label: mesotrochantinal muscle
Defs: The thoracic muscle that inserts on the mesotrochantin.

label: prepecto-mesobasalar muscle
Defs: The mesobasalar muscle that arises from the prepectus.

label: pyramidal
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having triangular faces that meet at a common point and containing a polygonal shaped base.

label: anterior orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed anteriorly.

label: lateral margin of mesoscutum
Defs: The inflection that extends along the anterolateral margin of the mesoscutum and fit with the dorsal pronotal inflection.

label: wing crease
Defs: The line along which the wing is creased.

label: primiparous
Defs: A viviparous organism having given birth one time.

label: pleural pit line
Defs: The anatomical line between the mesopleural and metapleural pits.

label: labral apodeme
Defs: The tendon that connects the fronto-labral muscle with the lateral margin of the labrum.

label: S9
Defs: The sternite that is connected posteriorly to the cupula via muscles.

label: pinnate
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having leaflets or leaflets-like structures on each side of a common axis.

label: granular
Defs: A composition quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing granules.

label: grey
Defs: A color between white and black colors.

label: hypostomal carina
Defs: The carina that delimits the hypostoma from the cranium.

label: peduncle
Defs: The area that is located anteriorly on the petiole, delimited posteriorly by constriction and bears the propodeal fossa of the petiole.

label: abdominal segment
Defs: The segment that is located posterior to the head and is does not bear legs.

label: first intrinsic muscle of the labial palp
Defs: The muscle that arises from the first sclerite of the labial palp and inserts on the second sclerite of the labial palp.

label: triangular
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having three angles.

label: cervical pronotal area
Defs: The area that is located medially on the pronotum and is delimited laterally by the epomial carina.

label: laminar
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s processing the form of a thin plate sheet or layer.

label: neoplastic, non-malignant
Defs: A disposition inhering in a tumour by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition not to progress, invade surrounding tissues or metastasize.

label: hypothesis textual entity
Defs: A textual entity that expresses an assertion that is intended to be tested.

label: fourth tarsomere of the fore leg
Defs: The tarsomere that is distal to and connected to the third tarsomere of the fore leg.

label: principal carina of stipes
Defs: The flange that extends along the margin of the posterior stipital wall.

label: coxopleurite
Defs: The pleurite that extends ventrally of the anapleurite and dorsally of the coxa.

label: anteroposterior anatomical line
Defs: The anatomical line that extends between the anterior and posterior margins of an anatomical structure.

label: median mesofurco-mesotrochanteral muscle
Defs: The mesotrochanteral muscle that arises from the ventral surface of the lateral mesofurcal arm medial to the site of origin of the lateral mesofurco-mesotrochanteral muscle and inserts on the mesotrochanteral apodeme.

label: water composition
Defs: A composition quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the quantities or relative ratios of water of the inhering entity.

label: anteroventral cavity
Defs: The depression that is located anteroventrally on the vertical part of the metapectus.

label: ventral surface
Defs: Anatomical surface that is located on the ventral side of the body or body part.

label: advanced phase
Defs: A phase which occurs earlier than the natural start time.

label: membrane-bounded organelle
Defs: Organized structure of distinctive morphology and function, bounded by a single or double lipid bilayer membrane. Includes the nucleus, mitochondria, plastids, vacuoles, and vesicles. Excludes the plasma membrane.

label: lateral scapo-pedicellar muscle
Defs: The antennal muscle that arises posteromedially on the proximal part of the scape and inserts laterally on the proximal part of the pedicel.

label: perfoliate
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s two basal lobes being united together.

label: gastral tergum
Defs: The tergum that is located in the gaster.

label: basal node
Defs: The projection that is located proximally on the external surface of the mandible distomedially of the mandibular condyle.

label: algorithm
Defs: A plan specification which describes the inputs and output of mathematical functions as well as workflow of execution for achieving an predefined objective. Algorithms are realized usually by means of implementation as computer programs for execution by automata.

label: author list
Defs: A part of a document that enumerates the authors of the document

label: drooping
Defs: To bent or hang downwards.

label: transversely fractured
Defs: A fractured quality where the fracture traverses the bone perpendicular to the axis of the bone.

label: ommatidium
Defs: One of the facets of the compound eye.

label: trochanteral fossa of the profemur
Defs: The fossa that is located laterally on the proximal margin of the profemur accommodating the femoral articular process of the protrochanter.

label: metapecto-metacoxal joint
Defs: The dicondylic joint that is composed of the metapectus, the metacoxa and the articular membrane of the metapecto-metacoxal joint.

label: dorsal pronotal inflection
Defs: The inflection that extends along the dorsal margin of the pronotum and supports the anterior inflection of the mesoscutum.

label: weight
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer that has mass near a gravitational body.

label: posterior metapleuro-metabasalar muscle
Defs: The metapleuro-metabasalar muscle that arises posterior to the paracoxal ridge.

label: sawtooth
Defs: The process that is located along the ventral margin of the first valvula or the dorsal margin of the second valvula.

label: uninflated
Defs: A structure quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being not filed with air.

label: speculum
Defs: The area that is located dorsolaterally on the mesosoma, is delimited posteriorly by the mesepimeral ridge and corresponds to the site of origin of the anterior mesopleuro-mesofurcal muscle.

label: anterior setal pit
Defs: The anteriormost setal pit on the dorsal side of the petiole.

label: sonic
Defs: A sound frequency in the range of 20 to 20.000 Hz.

label: process profile
Defs: b is a process_profile =Def. there is some process c such that b process_profile_of c (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [093-002])

label: pteralia
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the axillary sclerites and the humeral plate.

label: adhesivity
Defs: An emergent molecular quality that arises by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to exhibit molecular attraction to another entity in contact.

label: tergo-valvifer articulation
Defs: The articulation that is located between the female T9 and the first valvifer and is composed of the ninth tergal condyle of the first valvifer and the first valviferal fossa of the ninth tergite.

label: increased duration of temperature
Defs: A duration of temperature which is greater relative to the normal or average in respect to the quality of temperature of enduring or continuing in time.

label: posterior mesoscutellar carina
Defs: The carina on the posterior face of the mesoscutellum that is dorsally convex.

label: process efficacy
Defs: The ability of a process to produce its output.

label: procoxal foramen
Defs: The coxal foramen that is located on the propectus.

label: face
Defs: The area that extends from the median ocellus to the oral foramen.

label: male genitalia
Defs: The genitalia that is part of the male organism.

label: maxillary palpal socket
Defs: The margin of the posterior stipital sclerite that is concave and accommodates the base of the maxillary palp.

label: sensitivity to irradiation
Defs: A sensitivity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exposure to radiation.

label: tarsal plantula
Defs: The projection that is median, membraneous and is located distally on the ventral margin of the tarsomere.

label: anterior mesonoto-metanotal muscle
Defs: The mesonoto-metanotal muscle that arises from the mesoscutum.

label: increased strength
Defs: A strength which is relatively high.

label: susceptibility toward
Defs: A quality inhering in an entity by virtue of the bearer\'s propensity to resist an external stimulus.

label: osmolality
Defs: A concentration quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s amount of osmoles of solute per kilogram of solvent.

label: mesopleural triangle
Defs: The area that is limited dorsally by the subalar ridge, posteroventrally by the speculum and ends posteriorly in the subalar pit.

label: decreased depth
Defs: A depth which is relatively low.

label: basitarsal comb
Defs: The row of setae that extends along the ventral margin of the probasitarsus.

label: prescutum
Defs: The area that is located on the alinotum and is limited by the antecostal suture and prescutal suture.

label: ornamentation
Defs: A surface feature shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the degree of the bearer\'s highly topographical with ridges, pits, rugosity or other surface structures.

label: corbicula
Defs: The area that is located on the metatibia and is delimited by a fringe of setae arising from the metatibial margins.

label: decreased magnetism
Defs: A magnetism which is relatively low.

label: coeloconic sensillum of the galea
Defs: The coeloconic sensillum that is located on the medial surface of the galeo-lacinial complex distal to the base of the lacinial lobe.

label: constricted
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being drawn together, compressed or squeezed physically.

label: normal flexibility
Defs: A flexibility which is relatively normal or average.

label: ethical approval textual entity
Defs: A textual entity that documents the ethical approval of some study design.

label: photosensitive
Defs: A photosensitivity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting photosensitivity.

label: stridulitrum
Defs: The area that is composed of file-like ridges on the upper surface of the anterior tergum of abdominal segment 4.

label: antennal segment
Defs: The antennomere that is an appendage segment.

label: medial coxal condyle of the metapectus
Defs: The medial coxal condyle of the pectus that is located on the medial coxal articular process of the metapectus and inserts into the medial metapectal fossa of the metacoxa.

label: metatarsomere
Defs: The tarsomere that is located in the metatarsus.

label: anterior profile of petiolar node
Defs: The anteriodorsal area of the petiolar node that is oriented anterodorsally and is delimited posteriorly by a dorsally or posterodorsally orineted area.

label: salivarial orifice
Defs: The anatomical space that is situated posteriorly in the salivarium, proximal to the insertion of the dilatators.

label: cyclic cyclicity
Defs: Cyclic cyclicity inheres in a molecule when the atoms of the molecule do contain at least one cycle in the atom-atom connection paths (through bonds).

label: protelotarsus
Defs: The telotarsus that is located on the protarsus.

label: keyword textual entity
Defs: A textual entity listing keywords indicating the major theme(s) of a document.

label: dorsal T9-second valvifer muscle
Defs: The ovipositor muscle that arises along the posterodorsal part of the anterior margin of female T9 and inserts on the anterior section of the dorsal flanges of the second valvifer.

label: texture
Defs: A morphologic quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s relative size, organization and distribution of its surface elements or the representation or invention of the appearance of its surface; visual and tactile surface characteristics.

label: tibial flexor sclerite
Defs: The proximal sclerite of the tibial flexor tendon.

label: anatomical surface
Defs: Non-material anatomical entity of two dimensions, that is demarcated by anatomical lines or points on the external or internal surfaces of anatomical structures.

label: anterolateral mesopectal inflection
Defs: The inflection that extends along the anterior margin of the mesopectus and articulates with the posterior pronotal inflection.

label: indiscriminate
Defs: A discrimination quality in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being incapable perceiving differences between two or more stimuli.

label: paralysed
Defs: A behavioral quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being affected by loss of the ability to move a body part.

label: bent
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having one or more angle(s) in its length.

label: distensibility
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the extent to which the bearer is capable of being stretched or swollen.

label: length of mesoscutellar-axillar complex
Defs: The median anatomical line of the mesoscutellar-axillar complex in dorsal view.

label: maximally connected
Defs: A structural quality inhering in the bearer by virtue of the bearer consisting of a single, maximally connected structure.

label: adenomatous
Defs: A morphology quality inhering in a tumour by virtue of the bearer\'s exhbiting the morphological characteristics of a glandular epithelial cell.

label: proximolateral projection of the cupula
Defs: The projection that is between the proximodorsal notch of cupula and the proximoventral notch of the cupula.

label: deciduous (plant)
Defs: A quality inhering in a plant by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to shed foliage.

label: scutellar tubercular projection
Defs: The process that is located just medially of the margin of the scutellar plate.

label: software module
Defs: A software module is software composed of a collection of software methods.

label: width_08
Defs: A 1-D extent quality which is equal to the distance from one side of an object to another side which is opposite.

label: frontal orbit
Defs: The area that extends along the lateral margin of the upper face.

label: normal sensitivity of a process
Defs: A sensitivity of a process which is relatively normal.

label: mesopostscutellum
Defs: The area that is located posteromedially on the  mesoscutellum, is delimited anteriorly by the posterior scutellar depression.

label: collapsed
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being broken down; caved in.

label: abdominal tergum 1
Defs: The tergum that is located on abdominal segment 1.

label: apical-basal axis relative to substrate
Defs: An axis that extends through an organism or organism part from the part of the organism or organism part attached to a substrate (basal) to the furthest from the attachment (apical). Note that the apical-basal axis is often used for organismal parts where there is attachment via a basal lamina or other structure.

label: J-shaped
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being shaped in the form of the letter J.

label: anchor-shaped
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a shape resembling an anchor.

label: decreased variability of color
Defs: A variability of color which is relatively low.

label: rugose
Defs: A surface feature shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having many wrinkles or creases on the surface.

label: medial-radial axis
Defs: An anatomical axis that is perpendicular to an apical/basal axis or proximal/distal axis and extends from the center of an axis (shoot axis or root in the case of plants) to any point on the exterior of the axis.

label: gastral tergite
Defs: The tergite that is located on the gaster.

label: 2-D extent
Defs: A size quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s extension in two dimensions.

label: oblique orientation
