Defs: A quality of inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to move freely.

label: radioactive
Defs: A radiation quality inhering in bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting or being caused by radioactivity.

label: anterior metapleuro-metafurcal muscle
Defs: The metafurcal muscle that arises anteriorly of the site of origin of the posterior metapleuro-metafurcal muscle.

label: plush
Defs: A texture quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being covered or partially covered with hair that has increased thickness and softness.

label: increased velocity
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s increased rate of change of the position.

label: inflorescence-like
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s similarity to the appearance of an inflorescence.

label: anterior mesepisternal area
Defs: The area delimited anteriorly by the pronotal-mesopectal suture, posterodorsally by the ventral limit of the subacropleural sulcus, and posteroventrally by the episternal foveal line.

label: delayed closure
Defs: A duration quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s delay to complete the closure of the opening of an anatomical entity.

label: oral foramen
Defs: The foramen that is located anteriorly/ventrally on the cranium in which the mouthparts are positioned.

label: parossiculo-phallotremal muscle
Defs: The male genitalia muscle that originates from the parossiculus and inserts on the endophallic membrane around the phallotrema.

label: north
Defs: North is one of the four compass points or cardinal directions. It is the opposite of south and is perpendicular to east and west.

label: anterior mesopleuro-third axillary sclerite of fore wing muscle
lateral antecostal projection
Defs: The projection that extends over the lateral portion of the antecostal sulcus.

label: normal phosphorylation
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being phosphorylated to a normal or average extent.

label: abdominal sternum 8
Defs: The abdominal sternum that is located on abdominal segment 8.

label: median sulcus of postgenal bridge
Defs: The sulcus that is located on the postgenal suture.

label: obsolete increased relaxation
Defs: A relaxation which is relatively high.

label: partially ventralized
Defs: A ventralized quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s gross morphology containing what are normally ventral structures and missing some but not all of what are normally dorsal structures.

label: saturated magenta
Defs: A color consisting of magenta color and high saturation.

label: unicellular
Defs: A cellularity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s consisting of exactly one cell.

label: caption
Defs: A textual entity that describes a figure

label: metatibio-pretarsus of the metatarsus muscle
Defs: The flexor of the pretarsal claws of the hind leg muscle that arises from the metatibia.

label: anatomical plane
Defs: A flat 2D plane intersecting an anatomical continuant, dividing it into two adjacent portions.

label: anterior area of the second abdominal sternite
Defs: The sternite that is located anteriorly on the second abdominal sternum

label: dorsomedial cupulo-gonostyle/volsella complex muscle
Defs: The cupulo-gonostyle/volsella complex muscle that inserts medially on the dorsal region of the gonostyle/volsella complex.

label: antero-dorsal margin
Defs: Anatomical margin that is located on the antero-dorso region of the body or body part.

label: fluid flow rate
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a fluid (liquid or gas) by virtue of the amount of fluid which passes through a given surface per unit time.

label: abdominal segment 5
Defs: The abdominal segment that is located between abdominal segment 4 and abdominal segment 6.

label: prothoracic katepisternum
Defs: The sclerite that is between the propleuron and the procoxa. The intrinsic muscle of the propleuron inserts on the conjunctiva anterior to the prothoracic katepisternum.

label: deviation towards the lateral side
Defs: A deviation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s changed direction of position towards the side.

label: supraorbital suture
Defs: The sulcus that delimits anteriorly the supraorbital trabecula.

label: labial palpomere
Defs: The sclerite that is part of the labial palp.

label: aerobic (for occurrence)
Defs: A sensitivity of a process inhering in a biological process by virtue of the process unfolding in a location with oxygen.

label: peracute
Defs: Extremely acute and aggressive onset of a pathological process.

label: plumose
Defs: A branched quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having many fine filaments or branches that give a feathery appearance: for example, resembling a feather.

label: sternellum
Defs: The area that is located on the eusternum posteriorly of the site of origin of the furca.

label: knobbled
Defs: A surface feature shape having numerous very small circular rounded projections or protuberances.

label: skeletal muscle
Defs: The muscle that is attached at either end to the cuticle.

label: posterolateral orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed posterolaterally.

label: median longitudinal carina of the metasomal tergum
Defs: The carina that is located in the nteroposterior median lineof the metasomal tergum.

label: mesospinasternal apodeme
Defs: The apodeme that is oriented poseteriorly and arises from the mesodiscrimenal lamella at the base of the mesofurca.

label: distolateral galeal setiferous patch
Defs: The setiferous patch that is located distolaterally on the galeo-lacinial complex.

label: antennal muscle
Defs: The muscle that inserts on the antenna.

label: dendrogram
Defs:
A dendrogram is a report graph which is a tree diagram
frequently used to illustrate the arrangement of the clusters produced by a
clustering algorithm.

label: facial sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that arises medially from the ventral margin of the median ocellus and extends towards the intertorular carina.

label: epithelium
Defs: Portion of tissue, that consists of one or more layers of epithelial cells connected to each other by cell junctions and which is underlain by a basal lamina.

label: tibial flexor tendon
Defs: The tendon that is connected to the distal end of the tibial flexor muscle.

label: hyperplastic
Defs: A increased size quality inhering in an organ or tissue by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting increased number of cells.

label: mesocoxal foramen
Defs: The coxal foramen that is on the mesopectus.

label: straight angle to
Defs: An angle which is 180 degrees to another entity.

label: distodorsal submedian notch of gonostyle/volsella complex
Defs: The notch that is located submedially on the proximodorsal margin of the gonostyle/volsella complex and accommodates the gonossiculus when it is pivotted proximodorsally presumably by the contraction of gonosiculal muscles.

label: trochantin
Defs: The sclerite that is located anterolaterally of the coxa and corresponds to the site of insertion of the notal-trochantinal muscle.

label: disheveled
Defs: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being in disarray; extremely disorderly.

label: mesosternal shelf
Defs: The area that is located ventrally on the mesopectus between the mesocoxal depression and the epicnemial carina.

label: increased mass density
Defs: A density which is higher relative to the normal or average.

label: motley
Defs: A color pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of bearer\'s having 3 or more hues or degrees of saturations.

label: degeneration
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer exhibiting deterioration of its structure.

label: decreased fatigability
Defs: A fatigability which is relatively low.

label: release and spread structure
Defs: The evaporatorium that is located on the sex segment.

label: arrested
Defs: A quality of a process which ends earlier than the natural end time or reference process.

label: normal variability
Defs: A variability which is relatively normal or average

label: metanotal-propodeal sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that extends along the anterior margin of the fused metanotum and abdominal tergum 1 and delimit an anterior narrow, usually differently sculptured area.

label: dorsal surface of the mesoscutellum
Defs: The area that surrounds the scutellar plate and differs from it in sculpture.

label: mesoscutello-metanotal muscle
Defs: The metanotal muscle that arises from the mesonotum and inserts on the metanotum.

label: metanotal muscle
Defs: The thoracic muscle that inserts on the metanotum.

label: decreased viscosity
Defs: A viscosity which relatively low.

label: trochanteral condyle of the metafemur
Defs: The condyle that is located on the trochanteral articular process of the metafemur.

label: opacity
Defs: An optical quality which obtains by virtue of the ability of the bearer to absorb visible light.

label: decreased pressure
Defs: A pressure which is relatively low.

label: mediosternite 5
Defs: The mediosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 5.

label: metapleural carina
Defs: The carina that delimits the metapleuron dorsally from the propodeum, extends from just ventral of the metapleural arm to the metacoxal articulation and passes anteroventral to the propodeal spiracle.

label: surface feature shape
Defs: A surface shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s shape of features present on its surface or outer shell.

label: pronotal fovea
Defs: The well delineated depressed area that is submedian on the pronotum, and is delimited medially by the median bridge of the pronotal plate.

label: partially paralysed
Defs: A functionality quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of being not completely paralysed.

label: basitarsal articular process of the metatibia
Defs: The articular process that is located anteriorly on the distal margin of the metatibia and bears the basitarsal articular fossa of the metatibia.

label: narrative object
Defs: A narrative object is an information content entity that is a set of propositions.

label: process boundary
Defs: p is a process boundary =Def. p is a temporal part of a process & p has no proper temporal parts. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [084-001])

label: mesopleuron length
Defs: The anatomical line that extends between the lateral end of the epicnemial carina and the postpectal carina and is parallel to the lateroventral mesopleural carina.

label: neutral charge
Defs: A quality which inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of the molecular entity possessing the same amount of electrons overall as protons, thus having an overall neutral charge.

label: quality of a plasma
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting the physical characteristics of an entity consisting of roughly equal proportions of positively and negatively charged particles, having neither a defined volume nor defined shape, having internal magnetic fields, and being electrically conductive.

label: femoral groove
Defs: The scrobe that is located on the mesopleuron into which the mesofemur fits when pressed against the mesosoma.

label: acrosternal calyx
Defs: The paired and concave area on the acrostenite 7 that bears the orifice of type III exocrine glands.

label: sloped
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having an oblique or slanted direction.

label: annulus of petiole
Defs: The area that is located posteriorly of the transverse carina of the petiole.

label: convex angle to
Defs: An angle which is less than 180 degrees to another entity.

label: submedian carina
Defs: The carina that arises from the anterior mandibular articulation that is located medially of the orbital carina and laterally of the frontal carina.

label: actinomorphic
Defs: A symmetry quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being capable of division into symmetrical halves by any longitudinal plane passing through the axis.

label: superficial
Defs: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located near a surface.

label: metapleuro-third axillary sclerite of hind wing muscle
Defs: The hind wing third axillary muscle that originates from the metapleuron and inserts on the third axillary sclerite of the hind wing.

label: ctenidium
Defs: The process that is located on the annulus.

label: strigilis
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed by transverse rows of setae on the median (posterior, inner) surface of the metabasitarsus.

label: furrowed
Defs: A grooved texture quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being marked by two or more parallel channels.

label: firm
Defs: A hardness quality of giving significant resistance to pressure.

label: prearticular portion of the postmentum
Defs: The interstipital sclerite that is connected proximally to the postarticular portion of the postmentum.

label: intersegmental membrane
Defs: The conjunctiva that connects two segments.

label: mesofemoro-mesotibial joint
Defs: The femoro-tibial joint that is composed of the mesofemur and the mesotibia.

label: furcasternum
Defs: The area that is located posteriorly on the prosternum and bears the profurca.

label: adhesive
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer exhibiting molecular attraction to another entity in contact.

label: anterior labral retractor
Defs: The labral muscle that is unpaired, arises proximally from the upper face and inserts on the median proximal margin of the labrum.

label: ramus
Defs: The process that is located on the funicular segment.

label: Maximum spiracle distance of propodeum
Defs: The anatomical line that connects the center of the propodeal spiracle with the posteriormost point of the propodeal lobe in lateral view.

label: normal mass density
Defs: A density which is relatively normal or average.

label: increased thickness
Defs: A thickness which is relatively high.

label: proximal-distal gradient
Defs: Anatomical gradient that is distributed along the proximal-distal axis.

label: eighth flagellomere
Defs: The flagellomere that is located immediately distal to the seventh flagellomere.

label: epistomal line
Defs: The line that extends between the anterior tentorial pits.

label: hollow
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having an empty space or cavity within.

label: supra-marginal carina
Defs: The carina that extends laterally on the mesonotum along the mesoscutal suprahumeral sulcus.

label: mesosterno-procoxal muscle
Defs: The procoxal muscle that arises anteriorly from the mesodiscrimenal lamella and inserts posteriorly on the procoxa.

label: receptivity
Defs: A behavioral quality which holds by virtue of whether the bearer exhibits the ability to receive another agentitive entity.

label: invariant
Defs: A variability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking or not exhibiting variation.

label: patch
Defs: The area that is round and differs from surrounding regions in sculpture, setae, and/or pigmentation.

label: anterodorsal orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed anterodorsally.

label: counting
Defs: The planned process of finding the number of elements in a finite set of objects.

label: dorsal rod
Defs: The sclerite that is located dorsally between the penisvalvae.

label: auxiliar sclerite
Defs: The sclerite that is located between the unguitractor and the bases of claws.

label: malar sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that extends between the ventral margin of the compound eye and the base of the mandible.

label: labial muscle
Defs: The head muscle that inserts on the labium.

label: posterior supraalar area
Defs: The area that is limited medially by the transmetanotal carina and bears the postmedian metanotal wing process.

label: protrochanter
Defs: The trochanter that is located on the fore leg.

label: sternum
Defs: The area that is located on the integument and is ventral of the ventral diaphragm.

label: petiolar flange
Defs: The area that is located anteriorly on the second metasomal sternum and overlaps ventrally the petiole.

label: abdominal tergum 7
Defs: The tergum that is located on abdominal segment 7.

label: dumbbell-shaped
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having two parts, roughly spherical and of equal size, connected by a bar.

label: cuticular evagination
Defs: The area that is evaginated.

label: obsolete_unit of measure
Defs: a unit of measure is the quality of some material entity compared to which another quality is some multiple of.

label: increased turgor
Defs: A turgor which is relatively high.

label: nodular
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s consisting a knot-like mass.

label: margin
Defs: The anatomical region that extends along the margin.

label: tooth number 4
Defs: The tooth located proximal to tooth number 3.

label: pleural apodeme
Defs: The apodeme that is located on the pleuron.

label: coxal foramen
Defs: The foramen that is located lateroventrally of the pectus, in which the coxa is positioned.

label: raised
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a colony by virtue of the bearer\'s appearing above the medium surface with terraced edges.

label: propodeal muscle
Defs: The abdominal muscle that inserts on the propodeum.

label: ocellus
Defs: The multi-tissue structure that is located on the top of the head, composed of the corneal lens, pigment cell, rhabdoms and synaptic plexus.

label: anterior metanoto-metacoxal muscle
Defs: The metacoxal muscle that arises laterally from the metanotum, anterior to the site of origin of the posterior metanoto-metacoxal muscle.

label: inflection
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of a ridge that extends along the margin of a sclerite and the marginal area of the sclerite delimited from the sclerite by the ridge articulating with the inflection of another sclerite.

label: lance-ovate
Defs: A spheroid quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting a continuous convex surface with an axis of symmetry and one axis longer than the other; characterized with an egg-shaped form crossed with a lance-head shaped form.

label: increased intensity
Defs: An intensity which is relatively high.

label: upturned
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curved or tilted such that the tip points upwards.

label: wing membrane
Defs: The area that is not vein and not sclerotised.

label: software interpreter
Defs: A software interpreter is a software application that executes some specified input software.

label: institution list
Defs: A part of a document that has parts that are institution identifications associated with the authors of the document

label: width
Defs: The anatomical line that is perpendicular to the longitudinal axis of the anatomical structure and between one side of an object to the opposite side.

label: subocular area
Defs: The area that is located between the malar sulcus and preorbital suture.

label: metapectus
Defs: The sclerite that is connected anteriorly with the mesopectus, dorsally with the metanotum and posteriorly with the abdominal tergum 1.

label: lateral orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed laterally.

label: exposure event or process
Defs: A process occurring within or in the vicinity of an organism that exerts some causal influence on the organism via the interaction between an exposure stimulus and an exposure receptor. The exposure stimulus may be a process, material entity or condition (for example, lack of nutrients). The exposure receptor can be an organism, organism population or a part of an organism.

label: semen
Defs: The portion of tissue that is produced by the gland cells of the internal male genitalia.

label: purple
Defs: A color that falls about midway between red and blue in hue.

label: hypostomal sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that extends along the posteroventral margin of the cranium between the pleurostomal fossae and delimits the hypostoma.

label: acinus
Defs: Having a shape that resembles a many-lobed "berry," such as a raspberry.

label: increased height
Defs: A height which is relatively high.

label: second intrinsic muscle of the labial palp
Defs: The muscle that arises from the second sclerite of the labial palp and inserts on the third sclerite of the labial palp.

label: fifth tarsomere of the fore leg
Defs: The tarsomere that is distal to the fouth tarsomere of the fore leg.

label: occipito-cardinal muscle
Defs: The maxillar muscle that arises medially from the occiput dorsally of the occipital foramen and inserts on the proximolateral part of the cardo.

label: tension
Defs: A physical quality that pertains by virtue of a pulling force that is directed away from the bearer and attempts to stretch or elongate the bearer.

label: median mesoscutal line
Defs: The line that is located in the anteroposterior median line of the mesoscutum.

label: decayed
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s decomposition into component parts.

label: associating information with a centrally registered identifier in its registry
Defs: A planned process in which a CRID registry associates an information content entity with a CRID symbol

label: fusiform
Defs: Having a spindle-like shape that is wide in the middle and tapers at both ends.

label: white
Defs: An achromatic color of maximum brightness; the color of objects that reflect nearly all light of all visible wavelengths.

label: genal pilosity
Defs: The pilosity that is located on the gena.

label: premature closure
Defs: A duration quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s premature completion of the closure of the opening of an anatomical entity.

label: impact-fractured
Defs: A fractured quality in which one of the fragments is driven into another fragment.

label: cardinal condyle of the stipes
Defs: The condyle that articulates with the stipital fossa of the cardo.

label: decreased sensitivity to irradiation
Defs: A sensitivity to irradiation which is relatively low.

label: anterior area of the second valvifer
Defs: The area of the second valvifer which is anterior to the anatomical line that is the shortest distance from the first valviferal fossa of the second valvifer and the ventral margin of the second valvifer.

label: functional mouth
Defs: The anatomical space that is delimited posteriorly by the distal part of the sitophore and anteriorly by the tormae.

label: permeability
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to being permeated or pervaded by a gas or liquid (as by osmosis or diffusion).

label: east
Defs: East is one of the four cardinal directions or points of the compass. It is the opposite direction from west.

label: ammochaetae
Defs: The row of setae that is composed of elongate setae and used to manipulate foreign substrates.

label: salivarial sclerite
Defs: The sclerite that is located on wall of the salivarium and corresponds to the site of insertion of the ventral premento-salivarial muscle.

label: dorsal petiolar scrobe
Defs: The scrobe that is dorsal to the propodeal foramen and accommodates the proximodorsal area of the petiole.

label: tibial fossa of the femur
Defs: The fossa that is located distally on the femur and accommodates the femoral condyle of the tibia.

label: decreased perimeter
Defs: A perimeter which is relatively low.

label: verricule
Defs: The setiferous patch that is composed of closely gathered setae.

label: magnetic
Defs: A magnetic quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s ability to exert magnitism.

label: lateral region
Defs: Anatomical region laterally located on the body or body part.

label: frontofacial sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that is transverse, located on the upper face and medially joining or intersecting the scrobal sulcus and interantennal area.

label: relational quality
Defs: b is a relational quality = Def. for some independent continuants c, d and for some time t: b quality_of c at t & b quality_of d at t. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [057-001])

label: anterior proximal process of the probasitarsus
Defs: The process that is located anteriorly on the proximal margin of the probasitarsus and corresponds to the site of insertion of the anterior protibio-probasitarsal muscle.

label: pterothorax
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the meso- and metathorax and if the latter is fused with, the first abdominal tergum.

label: medial coxal condyle of the mesopectus
Defs: The medial coxal condyle that is located on the medial coxal articular process of the mesopectus and inserts into the medial pectal fossa of the mesocoxa.

label: anterior plate of pronotum
Defs: The area that is medial to the lateral pronotal carina and posterior to the anterior rim of pronotum.

label: prophragmo-laterocervical muscle
Defs: The laterocervical muscle that arises from the prophragma.

label: posterodorsal metapleural area
Defs: The area that is anterior to the metapecto-propodeal conjunctiva, posterior to the metapleural pit and dorsal to the metapleural sulcus.

label: normal amount
Defs: An amount which normal.

label: dorsal petiolar profile
Defs: The area of the petiolar node that is dorsomedial, and oriented dorsally and is delimited anteriorly by the anterior petiolar profile and posteriorly by the caudal petiolar profile.

label: tentorio-mandibular muscle
Defs: The mandibular muscle arises ventrolaterally from the anterior part of the anterior tentorial arm and inserts dorsomedially on the proximal part of mandible.

label: decreased efficacy
Defs: A decrease in the ability of a process to produce its output.

label: facial fovea
Defs: The area that is concave, narrow, often finely and densely pubescent and extends along the inner orbit.

label: orbital furrow
Defs: The impression that arises laterally from the antennal rim and extends along the inner margin of the compound eye.

label: dark phase
Defs: A phase which occurs during dark cycle.

label: normal sensitivity to irradiation
Defs: A sensitivity to irradiation which is relatively normal or average

label: anatomical system
Defs: Anatomical group that is has as its parts distinct anatomical structures interconnected by anatomical structures at a lower level of granularity.

label: mandible
Defs: The appendage that is encircled by one sclerite that is connected to the cranium proximolaterally and to the maxillo-labial complex proximomedially via conjunctivae and articulates with the cranium via the anterior and posterior cranio-mandibular articulations.

label: pedicellate
Defs: A attachment quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having or being supported by a pedicel or pedicle.

label: pecto-coxal joint
Defs: The joint that is composed of the pectus, the coxa and the articular membrane of the pecto-coxal joint.

label: tarsomere
Defs: The annulus that is the part of the tarsus.

label: viscous
Defs: A viscosity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having viscosity.

label: crescent-shaped
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a circular disk by virtue of the bearer\'s having a segment of another circle removed from its edge, so that what remains is a shape enclosed by two circular arcs of different diameters which intersect at two points (usually in such a manner that the enclosed shape does not include the center of the original circle).

label: friable
Defs: Easily reduced to powder or easily fragmentable or crumbly.

label: disconnected
Defs: A structural quality inhering in the bearer by virtue of the bearer consisting of multiple structures lacking any physical connection to each other.

label: anterodistal notch of the fore wing
Defs: The notch that is on the anterior wing margin, is adacent to the anterior end of the poststigmal fold line.

label: discriminate
Defs: A discrimination quality in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being capable of perceiving differences between two or more stimuli.

label: convolute
Defs: A curled quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s one edge of its surface being wholly rolled up in another.

label: duplicated
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being present in two copies.

label: subacute
Defs: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having an onset and time course between acute and chronic.

label: foretarsal rake
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of longitudinal rows of spurs extending along the tarsomeres of the protarsus and are continuous with the row of spur of the preceeding and/or subsequent tarsomeres.

label: mesoscutellar arm
Defs: The area that extends along the posterior margin of the mesoscutellum between the axillary level and the mesoscutellar disc, enclosing the anatomical space connecting the axillary level with the pulsatory organ of the fore wing.

label: corbicula
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed by the concave lateral (external, anterior) area of the metatibia and two rows of setae extending along the lateral margins of the area.

label: prepupal
Defs: A maturity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being in an inactive stage in the development of some insects, between the larval and the pupal stages.

label: prespecular sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that delimits anteriorly the speculum and corresponds to the anterior margin of the speculum.

label: ornamented
Defs: A surface feature shape in which the bearer\'s surface is highly topographical with ridges, pits, rugosity or other surface structures.

label: corner
Defs: The projection that is located at the intersection of two or more edges.

label: ocellar diameter
Defs: The diameter of the ocellus.

label: proximal lobe of lateral flange of the principal carina of the stipes
Defs: The area of the lateral flange of the principal carina of the stipes proximal to the notch of the principal carina of the stipes.

label: curation subset ontology module
Defs: A subset ontology that is intended as a whitelist for curators using the ontology. Such a subset will exclude classes that curators should not use for curation.

label: software library
Defs: A software library is software composed of a collection of software modules and/or software methods in a form that can be statically or dynamically linked to some software application.

label: anterior coxal fossa of the protrochanter
Defs: The fossa that is located anteriorly on the proximal margin of the protrochanter accommodating the anterior trochanteral condyle of the procoxa.

label: apicomedial galeal plate
Defs: The sclerite that is located on the medial surface of the galeo-lacinial complex and bears the coeloconic sensillum of galea.

label: mesoscutal humeral sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that extends medially along the parascutal carina and corresponds to a shallow ridge.

label: asymmetrically curved
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curved asymmetrically.

label: figures section
Defs: A part of a document that contains one or more figures.

label: normal fluid flow
Defs: A fluid flow which is relatively normal or average.

label: light purple
Defs: A color consisting of purple color and high brightness.

label: anterolateral wall of the stipes
Defs: The area that extends between anterior margin of the median wall of the stipes and the lateral margin of the posterior wall of the stipes and the base of the mandible and the labrum.

label: dorsal premental adductor
Defs: The tentorio-labial muscle that arises from the cranium and inserts distally on the labium adjacent to the level of the salivary orifice.

label: salivarium
Defs: The area that is adjacent to the proximal end of the salivary duct and corresponds to the site of insertion of the dorsal and ventral premento-salivarial muscles.

label: propodeum
Defs: The area of the metapectal-propodeal complex that is located posterior to the metapleural sulcus.

label: lateral mesofurcal arm
Defs: The apodeme that arises from the base of the mesofurca.

label: grand multiparous
Defs: A viviparous organism that has given birth five or more times.

label: metapleural epicoxal carina
Defs: The carina that delimits posteriorly the metapleural triangle.

label: sound frequency
Defs: The frequency of transmitted vibrations.

label: postmentum
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the sclerites that are on the postmental area.

label: passive
Defs: A behavioral quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s receiving or being subjected to an action without responding or initiating an action in return.

label: circular
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being such that every part of the surface or the circumference is equidistant from the center.

label: funicular segment
Defs: The flagellomere that is located in the funicle.

label: humidity
Defs: A quality inhering in air by virtue of the partial pressure exerted by the bearer\'s water vapour content.

label: proximoventral notch of cupula
Defs: The notch on the proximoventral margin of the cupula just lateral to the gonocondyle.

label: non-deciduous (any body part)
Defs: A quality inhering in a plant by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to not shed any body part.

label: color
Defs: A composite chromatic quality composed of hue, saturation and intensity parts.

label: blade-like
Defs: A tapered shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being flat, slender, and tapering to a point.

label: abdominal segment 1
Defs: The abdominal segment that is located between the metathorax and abdominal segment 2.

label: information carrier
Defs: A quality of an information bearer that imparts the information content

label: paraocular lobe
Defs: The area that is located ventromedially on the paraocular area and is surrounded partly by the epistomal sulcus.

label: abdominal tergum 10
Defs: The abdominal tergum that is located in the abdominal segment 10.

label: neoplastic, malignant
Defs: A disposition inhering in a tumour by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to progress, invade surrounding tissues or metastasize.

label: combustibility
Defs: The propensity of a material to undergo combustion. Combustion encompasses smouldering and flaming combustion. Combustibility is usually applied to solids.

label: submetapleural carina
Defs: The carina that is located along the ventral metapleural margin, between the mesocoxal foramen and metacoxal foramen.

label: quadripartite
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being divided into four parts.

label: torular space
Defs: The area that is located between the antennal rims.

label: calyptra
Defs: The flange that is located just laterally of the first abdominal spiracle.

label: diluted
Defs: A concentration which relatively low.

label: decreased water composition
Defs: A composition quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the reduction in amount of water the bearer contains.

label: prophragma
Defs: The phragma that extends along the anterior margin of the mesonotum.

label: plasma membrane
Defs: The membrane surrounding a cell that separates the cell from its external environment. It consists of a phospholipid bilayer and associated proteins.

label: anterior tentorio-scapal muscle
Defs: The antennal muscle that arises dorsally on the anterior part of the anterior tentorial arm and inserts anterolaterally (ventrolaterally) on the proximal part of the scape.

label: monophasic
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having only one phase or stage.

label: intercardinal sclerite
Defs: The sclerite on the intercardinal area that is not paired.

label: villiform
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s resembling a minute projection (villus).

label: decurrent
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being prolonged below the point of insertion.

label: normal male fertility
Defs: A male fertility which is relatively normal or average.

label: surcoxal depression
Defs: The depression that is located anteroventrally on the mesopectus anterior of the precoxal carina.

label: transverse trabecula
Defs: The bar that extends between each eye ventral (anterior) to the anterior ocellus and dorsal (posterior) to the antennal formamina and laterally terminates at the juncture of the supraorbital trabecula and preorbital trabecula.

label: desaturated blue
Defs: A color consisting of blue hue and low saturation.

label: trochanteral fossa of the metafemur
Defs: The fossa that is located laterally on the metafemur and accommodates the femoral articular process of the metatrochanter.

label: overlapping
Defs: Overlap with quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being positioned over another entity so as to cover some portion of it.

label: scrobal carina of the mesoscutum
Defs: The carina that delimits laterally the cranial scrobe of the mesoscutum.

label: first valvifer-second valvifer muscle
Defs: The ovipositor muscle that arises from the interarticular ridge of the first valvifer and inserts on the second valvifer.

label: ultrasonic
Defs: A sound frequency in the range of 20 000 + Hz.

label: medial pectal fossa of the metacoxa
Defs: The medial pectal fossa of the coxa that is located medially on the proximal margin of the metacoxa and accommodates the medial coxal condyle of the metapectus.

label: tibial condyle of the metabasitarsus
Defs: The condyle that is located on the tibial articular process of the metabasitarsus and inserts into the basitarsal fossa of the metatibia.

label: posterior thoracic spiracle
Defs: The spiracle that is located dorsally on the border between the mesopectus and the metapectus.

label: pear shaped
Defs: Having the shape of a pear; tapering near the top and bulging toward the base or bottom. From thefreedictionary.com

label: exocuticle
Defs: The procuticle that is tanned (sclerotised, proteins are highly crosslinked) and located between the endocuticle and epicuticle.

label: radius
Defs: A length quality which is equal to the length of any straight line segment that passes from the center of a circle to any endpoint on the circular boundary. The radius is half of the diameter.

label: normal distribution
Defs: A distribution which is relatively normal or average

label: metapleuro-propodeal muscle
Defs: The propodeal muscle that arises from the metapleuron.

label: metalaterophragmo-metafurcal muscle
Defs: The metafurcal muscle that arises from the metalaterophragma.

label: barred
Defs: A color pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of bearer\'s exhibiting vertical bars of one hue or degree of saturation crossing another.

label: T9-genital membrane muscle
Defs: The ovipositor muscle that arises from the cordate apodeme and inserts dorsally on the proximal part of the genital membrane and on the opposite cordate apodeme.

label: abdominal tergum 5
Defs: The tergum that is located on abdominal segment 5.

label: invariant temperature
Defs: A variability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking or not exhibiting variation of temperature.

label: transpleural sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that extends from the mesopleural pit to the mesocoxal articulation.

label: facial pit
Defs: The pit that overlaps with the facial apodeme.

label: damaged
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being harmed or injured or spoiled, such that its functionality is impaired.

label: base ontology module
Defs: An ontology module that comprises only of asserted axioms local to the ontology, excludes import directives, and excludes axioms or declarations from external ontologies.

label: large disc sensilla
Defs: The row of sensilla whose cuticular component are flat, circular and lack a median peg.

label: decreased strength
Defs: A strength which is relatively low.

label: normal wetness
Defs: A wetness which is relatively normal or average

label: posterior profemoro-protibial articulation
Defs: The posterior femoro-tibial articulation that is composed of the posterior tibial condyle and fossa of the profemur and the posterior femoral condyle and fossa of the protibia.

label: decreased osmolality
Defs: An osmolality which is relatively low.

label: mesopleuro-mesobasalar muscle
Defs: The mesobasalar muscle that originates anteroventrally from the mesopleuron and insert on the mesobasalare.

label: efficiency
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of ratio of the bearer\'s output to the bearer\'s input.

label: chorion
Defs: A hard shell external to the vitelline membrane of the egg.

label: tenth flagellomere
Defs: The flagellomere that is located immediately distal to the ninth flagellomere.

label: antecostal sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that corresponds to the antecosta.

label: median conjunctiva of cardines
Defs: The conjunctiva that separates the left and the right cardines.

label: scutellar spine
Defs: The spine that is located posteromedially on the mesoscutellum.

label: light violet
Defs: A color consisting of violet hue and high brightness.

label: prosternum
Defs: The sclerite that is connected posteriorly to the propleuron and bears the prodiscrimen and the profurca.

label: ventral pronotal pit
Defs: The pit that is located ventrally on the pronotum.

label: laterosternite 5
Defs: The laterosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 5.

label: protrochanteral apodeme
Defs: The sclerite that is located medially on the proximal margin of the protrochanter and corresponds to the site of origin of the median procoxo-protrochanteral muscle.

label: heart shaped
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a sinus or rounded lobe at the base.

label: pentaploid
Defs: A polyploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing five homologous sets of chromosomes.

label: antennal shelf
Defs: The area that is delimited by two transverse edges extending just ventrally and dorsally of the antennal foramina.

label: fleshy
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer resembling or containing flesh.

label: lower mesepimeron
Defs: The area that corresponds to the site of origin of the mesopleuro-mesosubalar muscle.

label: undistributed
Defs: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s not being spread out or scattered about or divided up.

label: peg-like
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a short and stout cylindrical shape.

label: acidic
Defs: An medium acidity quality inhering in a solution by virtue of the bearer\'s a high concentration of H+ ions.

label: ninth abdominal tergal muscle
Defs: The tergal muscle that inserts on female T9.

label: proximal gonostyle/volsella complex-harpal muscle
Defs: The gonostyle/volsella complex-harpal muscle that inserts on the median wall of the harpe and arises proximally of the site of origin of the distal gonostyle/volsella complex-harpal muscle.

label: anterior trochanteral fossa of the mesocoxa
Defs: The fossa that is located anteriorly on the distal margin of the mesocoxa accommodating the anterior coxal condyle of the mesotrochanter.

label: diagonal to
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located on a sloping line joining two nonconsecutive points of an entity relative to another entity.

label: length of metanotum
Defs: The median anatomical line of the metanotum in dorsal view.

label: basicostal suture
Defs: The sulcus that corresponds to the basicosta.

label: decreased efficiency
Defs: An efficiency which is relatively low.

label: permanent
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s underlying structure not changing over time.

label: glandular release pit of the scutellum
Defs: The area that is concave is located medially on the scutellar plate and corresponds to the opening of an exocrine gland.

label: translucent
Defs: A optical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting low opacity.

label: increased variability of size
Defs: A variability of size which is relatively high.

label: interaxillar sulcus
Defs: The median sulcus of the mesonotum between the anterior margin of the mesoscutellar-axillar complex and the anterior margin of the mesoscutellum.

label: frontal patch
Defs: The setiferous patch that is located on the frons.

label: normal sensitivity of a process to oxygen
Defs: A sensitivity of occurrent to oxygen which is relatively normal.

label: pronotal spine
Defs: The spine that is located at the dorsolateral edge of the cranial scrobe of the pronotum.

label: has fewer parts of type
Defs: The bearer of this quality has_part < n AND has_part > 0 of the indicated entity type, where n is the normal amount for a comparable organism. Note that the bearer of the quality is the whole, not the part. Formally: If a bearer entity e has fewer parts of type X at time t, then the number of instances x of X at t such that x part_of e is < n, where n is either the normal number for comparable entities, or n is stated explicitly.

label: unstratified
Defs: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking a layered configuration.

label: oral-aboral axis
Defs: An axis that extends from the oral opening to the furthest point in an organism that is directly opposite.

label: abdominal sternite 3
Defs: The sternite that is located on the abdominal segment 3.

label: propleural cervical sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that extends along the dorsal margin of the propleuron.

label: maturity
Defs: A quality of a single physical entity which is held by a bearer when the latter exhibits a state of growth, differentiation, or development.

label: decreased radiopacity
Defs: A radiopacity that is relatively low.

label: slit-like
Defs: Shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer exhibiting a narrow and elongate opening.

label: peritreme
Defs: A sclerotic ring surrounding the outer spiracular opening.

label: lateral area of the mesoscutum
Defs: The area that is located between the notaulus and the parascutal carina.

label: hyponastic
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting a upward bending of its leaves or other plant parts.

label: imperforate
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having no opening.

label: callus
Defs: The area that is located laterally of the propodeal spiracle and is delimited anterolaterally by the metapleural sulcus.

label: wholly ventralized
Defs: A ventralized quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s gross morphology containing only what are normally ventral structures.

label: branched
Defs: A branchiness quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having branches.

label: desaturated yellow
Defs: A color consisting of yellow hue and low saturation.

label: anatomical line
Defs: Non-material anatomical entity of one dimension, which forms a boundary of an anatomical surface or is a modulation of an anatomical surface.

label: opisthogaster
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of all abdominal segments posterior to abdominal segment 3.

label: simple squamous epithelium
Defs: Unilaminar epithelium that consists of a single layer of squamous cells.

label: interlocked with
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being locked together or interconnected to another entity.

label: rectangular
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of it being a quadrilateral polygon in which all four angles are right angles.

label: palpifer
Defs: The area that is located on the stipes and which articulates with the maxillary palp.

label: fibrinopurulent
Defs: A composition quality inhering in exudate by virtue of the bearer\'s containing fibrin.

label: circling
Defs: A behavioral quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting movement in a circular course.

label: subantennal groove
Defs: The impression that is located on the face ventrally of the antennal foramen and dorsally of the clypeus.

label: dorsal incision of the pronotum
Defs: The notch that is located submedially on the dorsal margin of the pronotum and fits with the anterior extension of the preaxilla.

label: normal female fertility
Defs: A female fertility which is relatively normal or average.

label: multi-localised
Defs: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being confined or restricted to multiple locations.

label: submedian groove
Defs: The line that is lobgitudinal and is located  closer to the midline than to the lateral margin of the mesoscutellum.

label: spiculate patch of the galea
Defs: The area on the galeo-lacinial complex distal to the lacinial lobe that is covered with acanthae.

label: occlusor muscle apodeme
Defs: The apodeme that corresponds to the site of origin of the occlusor muscle of the thoracic spiracle.

label: unserrated
Defs: A surface feature shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking sharp straight-edged teeth pointing to the apex.

label: posterior trochanteral articular process of the metacoxa
Defs: The articular process that is located posteriorly on the distal margin of the metacoxa and bears the posterior trochanteral condyle of the metacoxa.

label: momentum
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s velocity multiplied by its mass.

label: hind leg
Defs: The leg that is located on the metathorax.

label: patent
Defs: A document that has been accepted by a patent authority

label: proximal surface
Defs: Anatomical surface that is located on the proximal side of the body or body part.

label: mesobasalare
Defs: The basalare that is located in the mesothorax.

label: unipotent
Defs: A cellular potency that is the capacity to produce only one differentiated cell type.

label: lateral metepisternal projection
Defs: The projection that is located anteriorly on the lateral longitudinal metepisternal carina.

label: temporally extended
Defs: A quality of a process which ends later than the natural end time.

label: gonossiculal muscle
Defs: The male genitalia muscle that inserts on the gonossiculus.

label: material anatomical entity
Defs: An anatomical entity that has mass.

label: polarity
Defs: A molecular quality that inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of whether or not the molecular entity has a separation of electric charge which leads to the molecule having an electric dipole.

label: median procoxo-protrochanteral muscle
Defs: The protrochanteral muscle that arises medially from the procoxa and inserts on the protrochanteral apodeme.

label: bullet-shaped
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being short and wide and tapered distally.

label: irregularly shaped
Defs: A shape quality inhering on a bearer by virtue of a bearer\'s shape lacking in pattern or uniformity; for example, it may have sides of different lengths, different curvatures, or unequal angles.

label: mesocoxo-mesobasalar muscle
Defs: The mesobasalar muscle that arises from the mesocoxa.

label: mosaicism
Defs: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having two or more cell populations that differ in genetic makeup. This situation can affect any type of cell, including blood cells, gametes (egg and sperm cells), and skin.

label: fifth tarsomere of the mid leg
Defs: The tarsomere that is distal to the fourth tarsomere of the mid leg.

label: mesothorax
Defs: The thoracic segment that is located between the prothorax and the metathorax and is delimited by the mesopectus and the mesonotum.

label: mucro
Defs: The projection that is median and is located anteriorly on the propodeum.

label: metapleural pit
Defs: The pleural pit that is corresponds to the metapleural apodeme.

label: hypopharyngeal rod
Defs: The ligament that connects the proximolateral margin of the prementum with the proximal part of the ligula.

label: obsolete narcolepsy
Defs: A sleep pattern quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disrupted sleep during normal sleeping period; often accompanied by cataplexy, sleep paralysis.

label: maxilla
Defs: The appendage that is encircled by the area that is proximally delimited by the hypostoma posteriorly, the median margin of the mandible laterally, the labrum anterolaterally and the labium medially.

label: refractile
Defs: A reflectivity quality inhering in the bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s ability to refract light.

label: scrobiculate
Defs: A texture that is uniformly covered in short, oblong, or trench-like depressions.

label: multiporous gustatory sensillum
Defs: The multiporous plate sensillum that is gustatory in function.

label: conflict of interest section
Defs: A part of a document used to declare any competing interests regarding the authors and/or funding organization for the work described in the document.

label: thyridium
Defs: The patch that is located on the gastrocoelus and has specialized sculpture.

label: mesopleural line
Defs: The straight line that extends ventrally on the lateral (vertical) surface of the mesopectus and is oriented anteroposteriorly.

label: structurally discontinuous
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being marked by interruptions or gaps.

label: paramandibular process
Defs: The projection that is located distolaterally on the hypostoma and extends to the clypeus separating the mandibular socket from the oral foramen.

label: invariant color
Defs: A variability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking or not exhibiting variation of color.

label: transversely striated
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being marked by narrow lines or grooves, usually parallel, that are oriented transversely relative to the long axis of the bearer.

label: body length
Defs: The anatomical line between the anteriormost pont of the cranium and the posteriormost point of the metasoma.

label: gastrocoelus
Defs: The area that is concave, transverse, and located anterolaterally on abdominal tergum 3.

label: increased quality
Defs: A quality that has a value that is increased compared to normal or average.

label: stylus of the third valvula
Defs: The sclerite that is connected to the distal end of the third valvula via conjunctiva.

label: preaxilla
Defs: The area that is delimited laterally by the parascutal carina, adjacent to the tegula anteriorly and bears the anterior and antemedian mesonotal wing processes.

label: increased spatial extent of a process
Defs: A spatial distribution of a process in which the process occupies a greater length, area, or volume than the reference process. For example, heterochromatin may form over a shorter length of a chromosome in a mutant than in wild type.

label: 2nd abdominal spiracle
Defs: The abdominal spiracle that is located on the abdominal segment 2.

label: synchronous
Defs: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s occurring or existing at the same time or having the same period or phase.

label: synsternal setiferous patch
Defs: The setiferous patch that is located on the synsternum.

label: volsellar plate
Defs: The area that is located on the parossiculus ventromedially of the cuspis.

label: proximodorsal process of the metatibia
Defs: The process that is located laterally (dorsally) on the proximal margin of the metatibia and corresponds to the site of insertion of the lateral metafemoro-metatibial muscle.

label: median mesoscutal impression
Defs: The median mesoscutal line that is an impression.

label: obsolete_report table
Defs: A report table is a report display element consisting of a matrix of cells layed out in a grid, some set of which are filled with some information content

label: preocellar pit
Defs: The pit that is located on upper face adjacent the anterior margin of the median ocellus and corresponds internally to a conical apodeme and not the tentorium.

label: paraglossal sclerite
Defs: The anteroproximal sclerite of the paraglossa that bears the basiparaglossal brush.

label: biomaterial purity
Defs: A composition quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s homogeneity of a biomaterial.

label: tomentose
Defs: A quality of being covered with short, dense, matted hairs.

label: anterior process of the prosternum
Defs: The projection that is median and is located on the anterior margin of the basisternum.

label: larval abdomen
Defs: The larval tagma that is located posterior to the thorax.

label: mesofurco-propleural arm muscle
Defs: The propleural muscle that arises form the mesofurca.

label: ploidy
Defs: A cellular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s number of homologous sets of chromosomes in the nucleus or primary chromosome-containing compartment of the cell, each set essentially coding for all the biological traits of the organism.

label: anterior metanotal wing process
Defs: The fossa that is located laterally on the metanotum and accommodates the anterior condyle of the first axillary sclerite of the hind wing.

label: jugal region
Defs: The wing region that is delimited by the plica jugalis.

label: median mesocoxo-mesotrochanteral muscle
Defs: The mesotrochanteral muscle that arises posteromedially from the mesocoxa and inserts on the mesotrochanteral apodeme.

label: decreased speed
Defs: A speed which is relatively low.

label: conductivity
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to transmit of an entity through a medium.

label: posterodorsal edge of pronotum
Defs: The edge that is located at the intersection of the dorsal and lateral margins of the pronotum.

label: autofluorescence
Defs: A fluorescence quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting fluorescence which is self-induced.

label: phallotrema
Defs: The anatomical space that is the distal opening of the endophallus.

label: gonostyle/volsella complex-gonossiculus articulation
Defs: The articulation that is composed of the parossiculal articular surface of the gonossiculus and the gonossiculal articular surface of the parossiculus.

label: positional polarity
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s location of features or characteristics along an axis.

label: polycystic
Defs: A structure quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s body containing more than one cyst - formations of an epithelium bounded cavity not associated with neoplasia.

label: dark pale pink
Defs: Pink color having medium brightness and low saturation.

label: mass density
Defs: A physical quality which inheres in a bearer by virtue of some influence is exerted by the bearer\'s mass per unit size.

label: width pato
Defs: A 1-D extent quality which is equal to the distance from one side of an object to another side which is opposite.

label: maxillary gland
Defs: The gland that opens medially at the bases of the maxillae.

label: waisted
Defs: A shape quality in which the bearer possesses a gradual, yet distinct, thinning from a wide starting point.

label: articular surface
Defs: The area that is located on the sclerite and that makes movable direct contact with another sclerite.

label: sunken
Defs: Flattened from above downward; below the normal level or the level of the surrounding parts.

label: one dimensional cartesian spatial coordinate datum
Defs: A cartesion spatial coordinate datum that  uses one value to specify a position along a one dimensional spatial region

label: metathorax
Defs: The thoracic segment that is located between the mesothorax and the first abdominal tergum and is delimited by the metanotum and the metapectus.

label: glossa
Defs: The lobe of the labium that is limited posteroproximally by the prementum, anteroproximally by the fold traversing the salivary orifice and laterally by the paraglossae.

label: time sampled measurement data set
Defs: A data set that is an aggregate of data recording some measurement at a number of time points. The time series data set is an ordered list of pairs of time measurement data and the corresponding measurement data acquired at that time.

label: microtrichia
Defs: The acantha that is on the wing blade.

label: deep region
Defs: Anatomical region located deep within an organism or structure.

label: galeal fringe
Defs: The row of setae that extends along the margin of the galeo-lacinial complex, distal to the lacinial lobe.

label: increased fluid flow
Defs: A fluid flow that is relatively high.

label: denotator type
Defs: A denotator type indicates how a term should be interpreted from an ontological perspective.

label: subcosta
Defs: The wing vein that is connected to the first axillary sclerite and extends posterior to the costa.

label: protrochantero-profemoral muscle
Defs: The intrinsic leg muscle that arises anteriorly from the wall of the protrochanter and inserts on the proximal profemoral apodeme.

label: cuspis

Defs: The notch on the posterior wing margin that is adjacent to the posterior end of the discal fold.

label: actinodromous
Defs: A branched quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having three or more primary branches diverging radially from a single point.

label: suppurative
Defs: A quality inhering a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s ability to generate pus.

label: source code repository
Defs: A document that comprises at least one source code module and provenance data about who contributed the set of files making up the module(s), and optionally comprises also multiple versions of files with detailed change history about who committed files and when, a license for the software, readme files, documentation, executables, etc.

label: propagation velocity
Defs: The velocity of spatial propagation of a process. Examples include the velocity of propagation of an action potential along an axon.

label: impression
Defs: The groove that does not correspond to a ridge.

label: profemur
Defs: The femur that is located on the fore leg.

label: evergreen (plant)
Defs: A quality inhering in a plant by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to retain foliage.

label: palpal formula
Defs: The ratio of the number of the maxillary sclerites and labial sclerites.

label: analysis subset ontology module
Defs: An ontology module that is intended for usage in analysis or discovery applications.

label: software application
Defs: A software application is software that can be directly executed by some processing unit.

label: anterior coxal fossa of the metatrochanter
Defs: The fossa that is located anteriorly on the metatrochanter and accommodates the anterior trochanteral condyle of the metacoxa.

label: acetabular groove
Defs: The impression that extends from the mandibular acetabulum to the preapical tooth.

label: oriented towards
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being aligned or positioned towards another entity.

label: pleural apophysis
Defs: The apophysis that is adjacent to the pleural ridge.

label: functionality
Defs: A quality of a single physical entity that arises by virtue of whether the bearer exhibits the ability to perform a regular function(s).

label: ocular ocellar line
Defs: The anatomical line that is shortest and connects the compound eye and the lateral ocellus.

label: marginal fringe of the stipes
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the spines on the distal margin of the distolateral portion of the principal carina of the stipes.

label: biological_process
Defs: A biological process represents a specific objective that the organism is genetically programmed to achieve. Biological processes are often described by their outcome or ending state, e.g., the biological process of cell division results in the creation of two daughter cells (a divided cell) from a single parent cell. A biological process is accomplished by a particular set of molecular functions carried out by specific gene products (or macromolecular complexes), often in a highly regulated manner and in a particular temporal sequence.

label: dorsal profurcal lamella
Defs: The ridge that extends dorsally on the profurcal arm and corresponds to the site of origin of the dorsal and ventral profurco-postoccipital muscles.

label: postarticular portion of the postmentum
Defs: The intercardinal sclerite that is connected distally to the prearticular portion of the postmentum.

label: normal male receptivity
Defs: A male receptivity which is relatively normal or average.

label: posterior proximal process of the probasitarsus
Defs: The process that is located posteriorly on the proximal margin of the probasitarsus and corresponds to the site of insertion of the posterior protibio-probasitarsal muscle.

label: lateral mesofurco-mesotrochanteral muscle
Defs: The mesotrochanteral muscle that arises laterally from the lateral mesofurcal arm, laterally to the site of origin  of the median mesofurco-mesotrochanteral muscle and inserts on the mesotrochanteral apodeme.

label: wing region
Defs: The area that is delimited by flexion and fold lines on the wing.

label: pleuron
Defs: The sclerite that articulates with the leg and is connected along its dorsal margin with the notum and ventral margin with the sternum.

label: mediolateral polarity
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s location of features or characteristics along the mediolateral axis.

label: saturated brown
Defs: A color consisting of brown hue and high saturation.

label: postnotum
Defs: The sclerite that bears the phragma and is located posterior to a notum.

label: decreased occurrence
Defs: An occurrence which is relatively low.

label: submedial notch on distoventral margin of gonostyle/volsella complex
Defs: The notch that is on the distoventral margin of the gonostyle/volsella complex laterally of the gonostyle/volsella complex-gonossiculus articulation.

label: gastral tail
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the ovipositor and the distalmost abdominal tergum or the ovipositor and the distalmost abdominal tergum and the preceeding abdominal tergum.

label: continuant fiat boundary
Defs: b is a continuant fiat boundary = Def. b is an immaterial entity that is of zero, one or two dimensions and does not include a spatial region as part. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [029-001])

label: aliform
Defs: Shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being shaped like a wing.

label: abdominal segment 10
Defs: The abdominal segment that is located posterior to abdominal segment 9.

label: paddle shaped
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s resembling the form of a paddle.

label: parapenis
Defs: The area that is the dorsomedian part of the gonostipes and is the site of origin of the distodorsal and proximodorsal gonostyle/volsella complex-penisvalval muscles.

label: lateral head length
Defs: The anatomical line that connects the widest point between the apical edge of the compound eyes and extends to the anterior and posterior cranial margins in lateral view.

label: neoplastic, metastatic
Defs: A disposition inhering in a tumour by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to spread and invade distant tissues.

label: overlap with
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s coinciding spatially, partially or wholly with another entity.

label: subpleural signum
Defs: The signum that is located submedially on the ventral face of the mesopleuron. The subpleural signum corresponds to the site of origin of the first mesopleuro-mesonotal (pl2-t2a) muscle.

label: stipito-lacinial muscle
Defs: The maxillar muscle that arises along the lateral margin of the posterior stipital sclerite and inserts proximally on the median wall of the stipes just proximal to the lacinal lobe.

label: occipito-lacinial muscle
Defs: The maxillar muscle that arises from the occiput and inserts on the proximal part of the lacinial lobe.

label: normal elevation
Defs: An elevation which is relatively normal or average

label: glabrous
Defs: A pilosity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lack of hairs or bristles.

label: circumscutellar carina
Defs: The carina that encompasses a horizontal, median, rounded area of the mesoscutellar disc.

label: median mesoscutal sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that is a median mesoscutal line and that is adjacent to the (internal) median mesoscutal ridge.

label: loose
Defs: A pattern quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s not being compact or dense in arrangement.

label: propleural arm
Defs: The apodeme that is located on the posterodorsal corner of the lateral propleural area and corresponds to the site of muscle attachment.

label: pharyngeal wall
Defs: The area that is anterior on the foregut and that is situated posterior to the cibarium.

label: anterior stipito-palpal muscle
Defs: The stipito-palpal muscle that arises medially on the proximal part of the stipes and inserts anteroproximally on the first maxillary sclerite.

label: polyphasic
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having or existing in many phases.

label: obsolete far red light sensitivity value
abdominal tergum 6
Defs: The tergum that is located on abdominal segment 6.

label: apical-basal polarity
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s location of features or characteristics along an apical-basal axis.

label: frozen
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being kept below its freezing point.

label: transscutal fissure
Defs: The line that traverses the mesoscutum and originates from the lateral margin between the antemedian and postmedian notal wing processes.

label: high brightness
Defs: A color brightness which is relatively high.

label: ninth tergal condyle of the first valvifer
Defs: The condyle that is located on the first valvifer and articulates with the first valviferal fossa of T9.

label: herniated out of
Defs: A protruding quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s bodily structure that has protruded out of the surface or boundary of another entity.

label: linearly fractured
Defs: A fractured quality where the fracture runs parallel to the long axis of a bone.

label: undamaged
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of not being harmed or injured or spoiled.

label: trochanteral fossa of the mesofemur
Defs: The fossa thet is located laterally on the proximal margin of the mesofemur.

label: overlapped by
Defs: Overlap with quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being positioned under another entity so as to be covered by some portion of it.

label: Schizosaccharomyces pombe mating type
Defs: A S. pombe mating type determined by the gene configuration on the mat1 locus.

label: molar volume
Defs: A volume quality inhering in a homogeneous substance containing 6.02 x 1023 atoms or molecules by virtue of the amount of 3-dimensional space it occupies.

label: fimbriated
Defs: Having a fringe or border of hairlike or fingerlike projections.

label: laminated bridge
Defs: The area that is located proximally on the notal membrane near the processus articularis is sclerotised and is continuous with the second valvulae.

label: quiet
Defs: A sound amplitude which is relatively low.

label: medial pectal fossa of the mesocoxa
Defs: The medial pectal fossa of the coxa that is located medially on the proximal margin of the mesocoxa and accommodates the medial coxal condyle of the mesopectus.

label: mesoscutellar comb
Defs: The median row of spines on the mesoscutellum.

label: future directions section
Defs: A part of a document detailing extensions of the described work that may be implemented at some future point in time.

label: protrochantellus
Defs: The trochantellus that is located on the profemur.

label: fasciated
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being abnormally flattened or coalesced.

label: hexaploid
Defs: A polyploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing six homologous sets of chromosomes.

label: anterior tentorial arm
Defs: The apodeme that extends between the anterior tentorial pit and the tentorial bridge.

label: herbaceous
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s upper parts die back to the rootstock at the end of the growing season.

label: odontoid process
Defs: The flange that is located on the ventral edge of the mandible and not continuous with the mandibular condyle.

label: apex gonostipitis
Defs: The apodeme that is located medially on the proximoventral margin of the gonostipes and is the site of origin of the ventral gonostyle/volsella complex-penisvalval muscles.

label: ventro-medial region
Defs: The region corresponding to the ventral region of the entity, towards the midline.

label: occiput
Defs: The area that is concave and surrounds the postocciput.

label: variant temperature
Defs: A variability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having or exhibiting variation of temperature.

label: posteroventral to
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located toward the rear and abdomen of an organism relative to another entity.

label: increased efficacy
Defs: A increase in the ability of a process to produce its output.

label: boomerang shaped
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a shape like a boomerang, with two arms connected at an angle.

label: normal rate
Defs: A rate which is relatively normal.

label: normal sensitivity toward
Defs: A sensitivity toward an external stimulus which is relatively normal or average

label: gonocondyle
Defs: The apophysis that is located ventromedially on the proximal margin of the cupula and is the site of insertion of the lateral S9-cupulal muscle.

label: fluorescent
Defs: A fluorescence quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of emitting light during exposure to radiation from an external source.

label: tarsus
Defs: The leg segment that is apical to the tibia.

label: editors ontology module
Defs: An ontology module that is intended to be directly edited, typically managed in source control, and typically not intended for direct consumption by end-users.

label: sensillum coeloconicum A
Defs: The sensillum coeloconicum, in which the diameter of the tip of the hairlike cuticular component is 1/3-1/5 of the diameter of the surrounding depression.

label: normal duration
Defs: A duration quality of a process which is relatively normal.

label: increased osmolality
Defs: An osmolality which is relatively high.

label: mesopleuro-mesocoxal muscle
Defs: The mesocoxal muscle that arises from the mesopleuron and inserts on the mesocoxa.

label: anteverted
Defs: An oriented quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s axis being positioned forward.

label: potability
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to being fit to be used as a safe means of hydration.

label: prespiracular propodeal area
Defs: The area that is located between the first metasomal spiracle and metapleural arm and delimited laterally by the metapleural carina.

label: hemorrhagic
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting excessive discharge of blood from the blood vessels.

label: unornamented
Defs: A surface feature shape in which the bearer\'s surface is lacking ridges, pits, rugosity or other surface structures.

label: transverse median carina on scutellar plate
Defs: The carina that extends transversely across the scutellar plate, anterior to glandular release pit.

label: intercoxal space
Defs: The area that is located between the acetabular carina and the ventral mesopleural carina.

label: dark violet
Defs: A color consisting of violet hue and low brightness.

label: prothorax
Defs: The thoracic segment that is located between the head and the mesothorax is composed of the pronotum, the propectus and the fore leg.

label: inedible
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer not being suitable for use as food.

label: ventral propleural area
Defs: The area that is located ventrally on the propleuron and is delimited laterally by the longitudinal carina of the propleuron.

label: apical glossal setae
Defs: The row of setae of the glossa that is adjacent to the distal glossal edge.

label: basal galeal sclerite
Defs: The sclerite that receives the site of insertion of the stipito-galeal muscle.

label: laterosternite 6
Defs: The laterosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 6.

label: abrased
Defs: A texture quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of a portion of the bearer\'s surface being scraped away.

label: normal fluorescence
Defs: A fluorescence which is relatively normal or average.

label: dark red
Defs: A color consisting of red hue and low brightness.

label: stubby
Defs: A size quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a short, stocky build.

label: macrotergite
Defs: The syntergum that is located posteriorly of the petiole.

label: postgenal sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that corresponds with the postgenal ridge.

label: light brown
Defs: A color consisting of brown hue and high brightness.

label: propodeum
Defs: The area of the metapectal-propodeal complex that is located posterior to the metapleural carina.

label: asexual organism
Defs: Multi-cellular organism that does not produce gametes.

label: cranial condyle of the propleuron
Defs: The condyle that is located distally on the cervical prominence and inserts into the propleural fossa of the cranium.

label: proctiger
Defs: The area that is located arond the anal opening posterior to the epipygium and hypopygium.

label: colleterial gland
Defs: The glandula mucosa that secretes an adhesive substance used to fasten the eggs to a support.

label: anterior trochanteral articular process of the procoxa
Defs: The articular process that is located anteriorly on the distal margin of the procoxa and bears the anterior trochanteral condyle of the procoxa.

label: metabasitarsus
Defs: The basitarsus that is located on the hind leg.

label: progenetic growth
Defs: A paedomorphic growth quality which is due to an ealier offset.

label: increased tolerance to
Defs: A tolerance quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s increased ability to endure a stimulus.

label: dorsal length of propodeum
Defs: The median anatomical line of the metapectal-propodeal complex in dorsal view.

label: basicoxite
Defs: The area that is located on the coxa proximal to the basicostal suture.

label: transverse line of the metanotum/propodeum
Defs: The line of the metanoto-propodeo-metapecto-mesopectal complex that connects the humeral sclerite to the third phragma.

label: color hue
