Defs: A chromatic scalar-circular quality inhering in an object that manifests in an observer by virtue of the dominant wavelength of the visible light; may be subject to fiat divisions, typically into 7 or 8 spectra.

label: life span
Defs: A time quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s expected maximum age.

label: increased combustibility
Defs: An increase in combustibility.

label: ductus ejaculatorius
Defs: The duct that connects the vas deferens with the endophallus and is ectodermal in origin.

label: animal-vegetal axis
Defs: An axis that extends from the animal end of an egg or early embryo to the opposite, vegetal end. In animals with yolk-bearing eggs, the vegetal end is the yolk bearing pole. (pertains to animals only - both vertebrate and invertebrate embryos).

label: metasomal tergite
Defs: The tergite that is located on the metasoma.

label: increased concentration
Defs: A concentration which is higher relative to the normal or average.

label: propleural epicoxal sulcus
Defs: The epicoxal sulcus that sets of the epicoxal lobe from the ventral part of the ventral propleural area.

label: virulence
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the severity of infectious disease caused by the bearer in a target organism.

label: external to
Defs: Positional quality in which an entity is located outside of another entity.

label: phallobase
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the cupulae, gonostipites and volsellae.

label: posterior trochanteral articular process of the mesocoxa
Defs: The articular process that is located posteriorly on the distal margin of the mesocoxa bears the posterior trochanteral condyle of the mesocoxa.

label: lateral articular process
Defs: The projection that is located on the prolpeuron posterolaterally of the epicoxal lobe and bears the procoxal condyle of the propleuron.

label: pronoto-propleural arm muscle
Defs: The propleural muscle that originates from the pronotum and inserts on the propleural arm.

label: concave 3-D shape
Defs: A complete three dimensional shape in which there is a line connecting pair of points on the object that lies outside the object. Or: a shape with cavities. Contrast: concave.

label: mesocoxal depression
Defs: The acetabulum that is located posteroventrally on the mesopectus, accommodates the mesocoxa and is delimited anterolaterally by the postpectal carina.

label: wetness
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer\'s being covered by a liquid.

label: paracoxal notch
Defs: The notch that is at the lateral end of the paracoxal sulcus.

label: apical-basal axis relative to direction of growth
Defs: An axis of a plant structure that is determined by the direction of apical growth, either by an apical meristem or an apical cell. Apical is toward the direction of apical growth: toward the tip of a growing shoot axis, root, thallus, or non-vascular leaf. Basal is away from the direction of apical growth: toward the root-shoot junction in the case of the primary root or stem, toward the primary root or stem for higher order roots or branches, toward the point of attachment for non-vascular leaves, and toward the original point of growth (as determined in the embryo) for thalli.

label: medioventral conjunctiva of the gonostyle/volsella complex
Defs: The conjunctiva that is linear and extends medially on the ventral region of the gonostyle/volsella complex.

label: cleft
Defs: A concave quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s resembling a groove or fissure.

label: immaterial anatomical entity
Defs: An anatomical entity that has no mass.

label: flattened
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s surface becoming more extended in a plane.

label: polar polarity
Defs: Polar polarity is a quality that inheres in a molecular entity when the molecular entity is polar, i.e. does possess an electric dipole.

label: metanoto-metapectal-propodeal conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva that extends between the metanotum and the metapectal-propodeal complex.

label: distal side
Defs: Anatomical side that is distally located on an organism or structure.

label: unicuspidate
Defs: Cuspidate quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s possessing a single cusp.

label: pronotal condyle of the mesoscutum
Defs: The submedial condyle that is located on the ventral margin of the mesoscutum and inserts into the mesonotal fossa of the pronotum.

label: subdermal
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located or placed beneath the skin.

label: palpus
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the palpal segments.

label: gastral scrobe
Defs: The scrobe that is located ventrally of the propodeal foramen and accommodates the gaster.

label: first axillary sclerite
Defs: The axillary sclerite that articulates with the mesonotum.

label: material entity
Defs: An independent continuant that is spatially extended whose identity is independent of that of other entities and can be maintained through time.

label: anteromedially rotated
Defs: A rotation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of being rotated towards the front and the middle of an organism.

label: physiological state
Defs: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the state of bearer\'s mechanical, physical, and biochemical processes.

label: subaxillular bar
Defs: The area that is elevated, located on the lateroventral margin of the mesoscutellar axillar complex and is continuous anteriorly with the postalar process.

label: metapleural ridge
Defs: The pleural ridge that corresponds to the metapleural sulcus.

label: chela
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is formed from the tarsal claw and the apical tarsomere, and is grasping in function.

label: normal female receptivity
Defs: A female receptivity which is relatively normal or average.

label: left side of
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located on left side of from the a another entity.

label: mandibular appendage
Defs: The area that is located proximoventrally on the mandible, is projected posteriorly and bears posteroventrally oriented rows of spines.

label: epithelial cell
Defs: Cell which has as its part a cytoskeleton that allows for tight cell to cell contact and which has apical-basal cell polarity.

label: trophic quality
Defs: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to synthesize a particular organic compound required for its growth.

label: ventral margin of the mesopectus
Defs: The median anatomical line that extends between the acetabular carina and the medial coxal articulations.

label: upper mesopleural rim
Defs: The carina that traverses the subdorsal mesopleuron.

label: iridescent
Defs: A quality of certain surfaces which appear to change colour as the angle of view changes.

label: serration
Defs: A surface feature shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having or lacking sharp straight-edged teeth pointing to the apex.

label: power
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s rate of doing work.

label: document part
Defs: An information content entity that is part of a document.

label: decreased quality
Defs: A quality that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.

label: integrated tarsal plantula
Defs: The tarsal plantula that arises medially on the tarsomere.

label: dorsal valve
Defs: The area that is articulated with the right and left second valvifers at the basal articulation and bears the rhachises.

label: diameter
Defs: A length quality which is equal to the length of any straight line segment that passes through the center of a circle and whose endpoints are on the circular boundary.

label: lateral metatrochantero-metafemoral articulation
Defs: The articulation that is composed of the femoral articular process of the metatrochanter and the trochanteral fossa of the metafemur.

label: posterior protibio-probasitarsal muscle
Defs: The intrinsic leg muscle that arises posteriorly from the protibia and inserts on the posterior proximal process of the probasitarsus.

label: inflexible
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s inability of being turned, bowed, or twisted without breaking.

label: pleurostoma
Defs: The area that extends on the ventral (anterior) margin of the cranium along the site of origin of the conjunctiva connecting the mandible with the cranium and is delimited posteriorly (ventrally) by the posterior (ventral) margin of the pleurostomal fossa and anteriorly (dorsally) by the anterior (dorsal) margin of the pleurostomal condyle and laterally by the mouth margin.

label: male pseudohermaphrodite
Defs: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population by virtue of having internal reproductive organs of male and external sexual characteristics of female.

label: oblique to
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a slanting direction (neither perpendicular nor parallel) relative to another entity.

label: internal metanotal ridge
Defs: The ridge that corresponds to the metascutellar arm.

label: measurement datum
Defs: A measurement datum is an information content entity that is a recording of the output of a measurement such as produced by a device.

label: central nervous system
Defs: Collective name for all the nerve centers and their connective in the insect\'s body. In the context of Drosophila refers to the part of the nervous system consisting of the brain and ventral ganglia.

label: lateral and rotional curvature
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curved around an axis and towards the side.

label: mesotrochantin
Defs: The trochantin that is located in the mesothorax.

label: anterior metapleuro-metabasalar muscle
Defs: The metapleuro-metabasalar muscle that arises anteriorly of the paracoxal ridge.

label: hypopharynx
Defs: The area that is delimited proximally by the proximal margin of the sitophore, distally by the salivarial orifice.

label: variability of rate
Defs: A variability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer exhibits rate variation or change.

label: metapleuron
Defs: The area of the metapectal-propodeal complex that is anterior to the metapleural carina and lateral to the metadiscrimen.

label: doubled haploid
Defs: A ploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s haploid cells undergo chromosome doubling.

label: paraocular area
Defs: The area that is located on the face and delimited ventromedially by the epistomal sulcus.

label: pathological
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being abnormal and having a destructive effect on living tissue.

label: distal gonostyle/volsella complex-harpal muscle
Defs: The gonostyle/volsella complex-harpal muscle that inserts on the median wall of the harpe and arises distally of the site of origin of the proximal gonostyle/volsella complex-harpal muscle.

label: variant color
Defs: A variability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having or exhibiting variation of colour.

label: laterocervico-procoxal muscle
Defs: The procoxal muscle that arises from the cervical apodeme and inserts on the procoxa on the opposite side from which it arises.

label: ventromedian apodeme of the aedeagus
Defs: The apodeme that arises distoventrally from the aedeagus and is not continuous with the ventromedian conjunctiva of the gonostyle/volsella complex.

label: distoventral submedian corner of the cupula
Defs: The submedial corner at the distoventral margin of the cupula.

label: gena
Defs: The area that is delimited by the intersection of the interorbital plane, the margin of the compound eye, the margin of the oral foramen, the occipital carina and the malar sulcus.

label: saturated purple
Defs: A color consisting of purple color and high saturation.

label: second valvifer
Defs: The area of the second valvifer-second valvula-third valvula complex that is proximal to the basal articulation and to the processus musculares and articulates with female T9.

label: shriveled
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being smaller and contracted, expecially due to loss of moisture.

label: synsternal translucent patch
Defs: The translucent patch that is located on the synsternite.

label: increased efficiency
Defs: An efficiency which is relatively high.

label: metatibia
Defs: The tibia that is located on the hind leg.

label: volsellar ridge
Defs: The ridge that is located on the parossiculus, originates from the gonossiculo-parossicular articulation and extends towards the proximal margin of the parossiculus.

label: proximodorsal process of the mesotibia
Defs: The process that is located laterally (dorsally) on the proximal margin of the mesotibia and corresponds to the site of insertion of the lateral mesofemoro-mesotibial muscle.

label: isosceles triangular
Defs: A triangular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having two sides have the same length.

label: mesopleural impression
Defs: The groove that corresponds to the transepisternal line.

label: defasciculated
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s in which bundles of aligned anatomical fibers have become separated.

label: preoral cavity
Defs: The anatomical cluster that includes the labrum, hypopharynx and labium.

label: basiparaglossal sclerite
Defs: The sclerite that is located medially on the paraglossa and articulates with the anterior glossal plate and is continuous with the hypopharyngeal rod..

label: cupulate
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being a cupule, with a structure similar to a cup that also encloses the ovule in partiality.

label: anterior profurcal lamella
Defs: The ridge that extends along the median line of the dorsal profurcal lamella and that receives the site of attachment of the profurco-laterocervical muscle.

label: prophragmal muscle
Defs: The muscle that inserts on the prophragma.

label: apical distance of pronotal spines
Defs: The anatomical line between the distal ends of the pronotal spines.

label: has extra parts of type
Defs: The bearer of this quality has_part > n of the indicated entity type, where n is the normal amount for a comparable organism. Note that the bearer of the quality is the whole, not the part.

label: median longitudinal metepisternal carina
Defs: The carina that delimits medially the metepisternal depression.

label: posterodorsal edge of the mesopleuron
Defs: The edge that is located at the intersection of the mesepimeral ridge and the inflected dorsal margin of the mesopleuron.

label: pharate adult
Defs: The developing adult after pupal-adult apolysis, i.e. from stage P8 (when yellow eye color first becomes visible through the pupal case), to eclosion.

label: inconspicuous
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of not being clearly visible.

label: ossified
Defs: A composition quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being hardened by the deposition of calcium into bone.

label: caudate
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a tail or tail-like projection.

label: basal bridge
Defs: The area that connects the parosicculi.

label: maxillary palp
Defs: The anatomical structure that is distal to the proximal margin of the first sclerite of the maxillary palp.

label: articular membrane of the protibio-probasitarsal joint
Defs: The articular membrane that is located in the protibio-probasitarsal joint.

label: mesobasitarsus
Defs: The basitarsus that is located in the mid leg.

label: interarticular ridge of the first valvifer
Defs: The ridge that extends along the posterior margin of the first valvifer between the intervalvifer and tergovalvifer articulations.

label: premento-glossal muscle
Defs: The labial muscle that arises on the ventral part of the prementum, laterally to the ventral premento-salivarial muscle and inserts on the anterior glossal plate.

label: red brown
Defs: A color consisting of red and brown hue.

label: anterior ocellus-torulus distance
Defs: The anatomical line that is the shortset between the ventral margin of the anterior ocellus and the dorsal margin of the torulus.

label: first valvifer-genital membrane muscle
Defs: The ovipositor muscle that arises from the posterior part of the first valvifer and inserts anteriorly on the genital membrane anetrior to the T9-genital membrane muscle.

label: atypical epithelium
Defs: Epithelium that consists of epithelial cells not arranged in one ore more layers.

label: superficial region
Defs: Anatomical region superficially located on the body or body part.

label: interantennal area
Defs: The area that is delimited dorsally by the antennal scrobes.

label: opaque
Defs: A optical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s not being clear; not transmitting or reflecting light or radiant energy.

label: posterior to
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located toward the rear of an organism relative to another entity.

label: crown like
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a shape like a crown.

label: subgenal carina
Defs: The carina that is located on the cranium, ventrally of the gena and extending from the hypostomal carina to the facial articulation of the mandible.

label: metapleural triangle
Defs: The area that is located anteroventrally on the metapectus, is delimited ventrally by the ventral carina of the metapleuron and is triangular.

label: protrochantero-profemoral joint
Defs: The monocondylic joint that is composed of the protrochanter and profemur.

label: radiopaque
Defs: A readiopacity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s prevention of the passage of electromagnetic radiation.

label: orbit
Defs: The margin of the compound eye.

label: posterior surface of the glossa
Defs: The area of the glossa that is between the distal margin of the prementum and the distal glossal edge.

label: submedian carina of propodeum
Defs: The carina that is longitudinal and extends closer to the midline than to the lateral margin of the propodeum.

label: ligneous
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer resembling wood.

label: frontal carina
Defs: The carina that extends along the lateral margin of the intertorular area (median margin of the antennal foramen) towards the vertex.

label: distal projection of the parossiculus
Defs: The distal projection of the volsella that corresponds to the apical parossiculal seta.

label: postgenal bridge
Defs: The subforaminal bridge that is sclerotised and limited anteriorly (ventrally) by the hypostomal carina and is subdivided medially by the median sulcus of the postgenal bridge.

label: oligopotent
Defs: A cellular potency that is the capacity to form multiple differentiated cell types of a specific lineage and lack self renewing capacity.

label: increased anterior-posterior diameter
Defs: An anterior-posterior diameter quality which is relatively large.

label: dorsope
Defs: The pit that is located proximally on the abdominal tergum 2 between the dorsal and lateral petiolar carinae.

label: antero-ventral margin
Defs: Anatomical margin that is located on the antero-ventral region of the body or body part.

label: male organism
Defs: Gonochoristic organism that can produce male gametes.

label: medial apodeme of female S7
Defs: The apophysis that is located proximomedially on the female S7.

label: distal vertical conjunctiva of the second valvifer-third valvula complex
Defs: The conjunctiva that traverses the second valvifer-third valvula complex and is located distal to the median bridge of the second valvifer.

label: hydrophilicity
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue the bearer\'s disposition to having an affinity for water; it is readily absorbing or dissolving in water.

label: procumbent
Defs: Growing horizontal to the ground without setting roots.

label: intervalvula
Defs: The sternal sclerite in the venter of the ninth abdominal segment between the second valvifers.

label: increased contractility
Defs: A contractility which is relatively high.

label: variant shape
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue the bearer\'s having or exhibiting variation its shape.

label: metatrochanter
Defs: The trochanter that is located on the hind leg.

label: open
Defs: A morphological quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s affording unobstructed passage or view.

label: areolate
Defs: A surface feature shape inhering in a surface by virtue of the bearer\'s being divided by ridge-like structures into a number of small, irregular spaces.

label: biological sex
Defs: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s ability to undergo sexual reproduction in order to differentiate the individuals or types involved.

label: dwarf-like
Defs: A size quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being abnormally small.

label: yellow brown
Defs: A color consisting of yellow and brown hue.

label: mesofurcal muscle
Defs: The thoracic muscle that inserts on the mesofurca.

label: obliquely striated
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being marked by narrow lines or grooves, usually parallel, that are oriented obliquely relative to the long axis of the bearer.

label: dorsal apodeme of penisvalva
Defs: The apodeme that is located proximodorsally on the aedeagus and is the site of insertion of the distodorsal gonostyle/volsella complex-penisvalval muscle.

label: concentrated
Defs: A concentration quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting concentration.

label: fragmented
Defs: Existing or functioning as though broken into separate parts; disorganized; disunified.

label: investigation
Defs: a planned process that consists of parts: planning, study design execution, documentation and which produce conclusion(s).

label: ovipore
Defs: The anatomical space that receives sperm ejected from the aedeagus.

label: anterior-posterior gradient
Defs: Anatomical gradient that is distributed along the anterior-posterior axis.

label: solubility
Defs: A molecular quality that inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to dissolve in a liquid.

label: protibial apical pegs
Defs: The row of spurs that extends along the apical margin of the fore tibia.

label: adult thorax
Defs: The thorax that is part of the adult.

label: strength
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s power or force.

label: atretic
Defs: A morphological quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s absence or closure of a normal body orifice or tubular passage.

label: mobile
Defs: A mobility quality of inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to move freely.

label: lateral carina of clypeus
Defs: The carina that extends between the ventral (anterior) margin of the antennal foramen to the apical clypeal margin.

label: metanotum
Defs: The alinotum that is located in the metathorax, is connected with the mesoscutellum and the mesopostnotum anteriorly and the acrotergite of the first abdominal tergum posteromedially.

label: information content entity
Defs: A generically dependent continuant that is about some thing.

label: decreased fecundity
Defs: A fecundity which is relatively low.

label: balanced
Defs: A balance quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having balance.

label: wholeness
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer includes all its components.

label: coiled
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curled or wound (especially in concentric rings or spirals).

label: haploid
Defs: A ploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing a single set of homologous chromosomes.

label: juxtantennal carina
Defs: The carina that is longitudinal and mesal to the antennal base.

label: increased male receptivity
Defs: A male receptivity which is relatively high.

label: remigial region
Defs: The wing region anterior to the vannal fold containing the costa, subcosta, radius, medius, cubitus, and postcubitus.

label: ovipositor clip
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the distal notch on the second valvula and the associated dentition and flexible flap.

label: cardinal ridge
Defs: The carina that is on the cardo.

label: basitarsal fossa of the mesotibia
Defs: The fossa that is located on the basitarsal articular process of the mesotibia and accommodates the tibial condyle of the mesobasitarsus.

label: axillary cord of the hind wing
Defs: The axillary cord that is located on the hind wing.

label: lateral ocellus
Defs: The ocellus that is paired.

label: submedian area of clypeus
Defs: The area between the median carina of clypeus and the lateral carina of clypeus.

label: second sclerite of the maxillary palp
Defs: The sclerite that is ringlike and is connected distally to the first sclerite of the maxillary palp via conjunctiva and muscle.

label: increased degree of illumination
Defs: An increase in illumination.

label: posterolateral metapleuro-metanotal muscle
Defs: The metapleuro-metanotal muscle that arises posterolaterally from the metapleuron.

label: fibula ducti
Defs: The sclerite that is located in the proximal end of the unpaired part of the ductus ejaculatorius.

label: aplastic
Defs: Absence of an organ, tissue or cell due to failure to develop from a primordium or precursor cell.

label: gonostyle/volsella complex-gonossiculus muscle
Defs: The gonossiculal muscle that arises ventromedially from the gonostyle/volsella complex and inserts laterally on the gonossiculus.

label: reflex angle to
Defs: An angular placement quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s placement at an angle that is greater than 180 degrees but less than 360 degrees to another entity.

label: transmural
Defs: Extending through or affecting the entire thickness of the wall of an organ or cavity or boundary.

label: ventral margin of the metapectus
Defs: The median anatomical line that extends between the anterior margin of the ventral region of the metapectus and the distal end of the projection bearing the medial coxal condyle of the metapectus.

label: thorax
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the pterothorax and the metapectus.

label: angular
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having at least one salient angle on the margin.

label: heterotaxic
Defs: An oriented quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being abnormally placed or arranged.

label: ventral protibio-probasitarsal muscle
Defs: The intrinsic leg muscle that arises ventrally from the protibia and inserts ventrally on the articular membrane of the protibio-probasitarsal joint.

label: profurcal pit
Defs: The furcal pit that is located in the prothorax.

label: external import ontology module
Defs: An imported ontology module that is derived from an external ontology. Derivation methods include the OWLAPI SLME approach.

label: decondensed
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being thinner or more losely packed.

label: lateral premental face
Defs: The area of the prementum, that lays parallel and connected via conjunctiva to the medial stipital vall.

label: cranium
Defs: The sclerite that is articulated with the cervical prominence, the scapes and the mandibles.

label: fore wing third axillary muscle
Defs: The thoracic muscle that inserts on the third axillary sclerite of the fore wing.

label: maximum height
Defs: The height that is the longest.

label: abduction
Defs: A displaced angular placement quality inhering in a body part by virtue of the bearer\'s movement away from the medial plane of the body.

label: postal address
Defs: A textual entity that is used as directive to deliver something to a person, or organization

label: anterior mesofurco-mesolaterophragmal muscle
Defs: The mesofurco-mesolaterophragmal muscle that originates from the mesofurca and inserts anteriorly on the mesolaterophragma.

label: lateral propleuro-procoxal articulation
Defs: The articulation that is composed of the lateral coxal condyle of the propleuron and the lateral pectal articular fossa of the procoxa.

label: materials section
Defs: A part of a document about the materials required to reproduce the content of the document.

label: normal odor
Defs: An odor quality of having relatively normal or average odor.

label: process quality
Defs: A quality which inheres in an process.

label: ontology module subsetted by OWL profile
femoral articular process of the metatrochanter
Defs: The articular process that is located laterally on the distal margin of the metatrochanter and bears the femoral condyle of the metatrochanter.

label: sound quality
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of vibration, as perceived by the sense of hearing.

label: ambidextrous handedness
Defs: Handedness where the organism exhibits no overall dominance in the use of right or left hand or foot in the performance of tasks that require one hand or foot or a dominant hand or foot.

label: saturated green
Defs: A color consisting of green hue and high saturation.

label: duration of disease
Defs: A duration quality of a process inhering in a disease by virtue of the bearer\'s duration of an impairment of health or of a condition of abnormal functioning.

label: increased rate
Defs: A rate which is relatively high.

label: metasomal condyle of the propodeum
Defs: The condyle that is located on the propodeal tooth and inserts into the anterolateral depression of the propodeum.

label: S3 felt field
Defs: The felt field that is located on the abdominal sternum 4.

label: dorsal tentorial arm
Defs: The apodeme that arises anterodorsally from the anterior tentorial arm and extends to the anterior wall of the cranium.

label: simple organ
Defs: Multi-tissue structure that is not part of a compound organ.

label: mesotrochantero-mesofemoral joint
Defs: The monocondylic joint that is composed of the mesotrochanter, the mesofemur and the articular membrane of the mesotrochantero-mesofemoral joint.

label: mandibular dentition
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the mandibular teeth.

label: decreased waxiness
Defs: A waxiness which is relatively low.

label: premental ditch
Defs: The scrobe of the prementum that is adjacent to and extends lateral to the premental carina and accommodates the medial part of the posterior stipital sclerite.

label: lateral scutellar keel
Defs: The carina which is present on the lateral margin of the mesoscutellum.

label: conclusion textual entity
Defs: A textual entity that expresses the results of reasoning about a problem, for instance as typically found towards the end of scientific papers.

label: misrouted
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having mistakenly taken course, way, or passage; ill-routed.

label: epicuticle
Defs: The cuticle that does not contain chitin fibrils and is located externally of the exocuticle.

label: decreased radioactivity
Defs: A radioactivity which is relatively high.

label: stipes
Defs: The appendage that is connected posteroproximally to the hypostoma, anteroproximally and lateroproximally to the mandible and medioproximally to the labium and the hypopharynx via conjunctiva, is connected to the cranium via muscles and that bears the maxillary palp.

label: posttergite
Defs: The area that corresponds to the narrow postcostal lip of a postnotal thoracic plate.

label: cell space
Defs: Anatomical space that is part of a cell.

label: mesotarsal claw
Defs: The tarsal claw that is located in the mid leg.

label: decreased functionality
Defs: A functionality quality held by the bearer when the latter exhibits decreased ability to perform a regular function(s).

label: elastic
Defs: An elasticity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s ability to recover its size and shape after deformation in any way.

label: pin-like
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being thin and lacking outgrowths.

label: transverse pronotal carina
Defs: The carina that delimits posteriorly the pronotal neck.

label: first valvifer-first valvula complex
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the sclerites that articulate with the ninth abdominal tergite and the second valvifer.

label: pronoto-third axillary sclerite of fore wing muscle
Defs: The fore wing third axillary muscle that arises from the pronotum.

label: propodeal tooth
Defs: The articular process that is located on the margin of the propodeal-metapectal complex around the propodeal foramen and bears the metasomal condyle of the propodeum.

label: hispid
Defs: A quality of being covered with stiff or rough hairs.

label: bifurcated
Defs: A branched quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being divided into two branches.

label: behavioral quality of a process
Defs: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s behavior.

label: T2 longitudinal internal ridge
Defs: The longitudinal ridge of the petiole that is median.

label: mediosternite 7
Defs: The mediosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 7.

label: normal pigmentation
Defs: A degree of pigmentation quality which is relatively normal or average

label: side scatter
Defs: A reflective quality that is the light scattering occurring at wide angle (around 90 degrees) to the incident beam.

label: decreased width
Defs: A width which is relatively small.

label: atonicity
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lack elastic tension that facilitate response to stimuli.

label: posterior area of the second valvifer
Defs: the area of the second valvifer that is posterior to the anatomical line that is the shortest distance from the first valviferal fossa of the second valvifer to the ventral margin of the second valvifer

label: saturated orange
Defs: A color consisting of orange hue and high saturation.

label: posterior mesosomal comb
Defs: The row of setae that extends along the posterolateral edge of the metanoto-propodeo-mesopecto-metapectal complex and the metacoxa.

label: tibial articular process of the metabasitarsus
Defs: The articular process that is located dorsally on the proximal margin of the metabasitarsus and bears the tibial condyle of the metabasitarsus.

label: volume
Defs: A 3-D extent quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s amount of 3-dimensional space it occupies.

label: posterior orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed posteriorly.

label: increased force
Defs: A force which relative high.

label: contractile
Defs: A contractility quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s ability of contracting or being contracted.

label: mislocalised radially
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being out of its usual or proper place, or position around a central point or axis.

label: orange
Defs: A color hue with high-medium wavelength that of that portion of the visible spectrum lying between red and yellow, evoked in the human observer by radiant energy with wavelengths of approximately 585 to 620 nanometers.

label: hypostomal tooth
Defs: The projection that is located on the posterolateral margin of the oral foramen at the junction of the hypostoma and the pleurostomal fossa.

label: increased width
Defs: A width which is relatively large.

label: complete structure
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being fully formed compared to entities lacking parts.

label: dilated
Defs: A size quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being made wider or larger in all dimensions.

label: metapectus
Defs: The area that is located anteriorly of the metapleural sulcus and ridge.

label: posterior region
Defs: Anatomical region posteriorly located on the body or body part.

label: mislocalised anteriorly
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being positioned towards the front of an organism.

label: generically dependent continuant
Defs: b is a generically dependent continuant = Def. b is a continuant that g-depends_on one or more other entities. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [074-001])

label: nucleated
Defs: A nucleate quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having one or more nucleus.

label: interorbital plane
Defs: The area that is defined by the anatomical lines that are tangent to a point at the minimal distance from the eyes to the lateral ocelli.

label: photograph
Defs: A photograph is created by projecting an image onto a photosensitive surface such as a chemically treated plate or film, CCD receptor, etc.

label: spur shaped
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s possessing a small, spike-like shape.

label: felt field
Defs: The setiferous patch that is located sublaterally on an abdominal sternum.

label: decreased branchiness
Defs: Branchiness quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of decreasing the degree to which there are subdivisions or offshoots in a bearer entity.

label: simple columnar epithelium
Defs: Unilaminar epithelium that consists of a single layer of columnar cells.

label: normal height
Defs: A height which is relatively normal or average

label: abdominal mediotergite 10
Defs: The mediotergite that is located on abdominal tergum 10.

label: bilateral symmetry
Defs: A symmetry quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being symmetric about a plane running from its frontal end to its caudal end (head to tail), and has nearly identical right and left halves.

label: lateral epomia
Defs: The area that is limited medially by the dorsal end of the epomial carina.

label: tuberculate verricule
Defs: The verricule that arises from a tubercle.

label: ovipositor apparatus
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the ovipositor, abdominal terga 8-10, abdominal sternum 7 and muscles connecting them.

label: matted
Defs: A tangled quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being not possible to unravel.

label: acetabular carina
Defs: The area that is located medially on the epicnemial carina.

label: interocellar space
Defs: The area that is limited posteriorly by the posterior ocellar line and laterally by the lateral ocellar line.

label: funicle segment
Defs: The annulus that is located in the funicle.

label: basiparaglossal brush
Defs: The anteroproximal area of the paraglossa that is covered with long acanthae and corresponds to the ligament connecting the hypopharyngeal button with the basiparaglossal sclerite.

label: west
Defs: West is one of the four cardinal directions or points of the compass. It is the opposite direction from east.

label: posterior mesofemoro-mesotibial articulation
Defs: The posterior femoro-tibial articulation that is composed of the posterior tibial condyle and fossa of the mesofemur and the posterior femoral condyle and fossa of the mesotibia.

label: biconcave
Defs: A concave quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s curving inward on both sides or surfaces.

label: third flagellomere
Defs: The flagellomere that is located immediately distal to the second flagellomere.

label: reasoned ontology module
Defs: An ontology module that contains axioms generated by a reasoner. The generated axioms are typically direct SubClassOf axioms, but other possibilities are available.

label: dorsal head width
Defs: The anatomical line between the posteriormost (dorsalmost) points of compound eyes in frontal view.

label: transverse row of setae of cercus
Defs: The row of setae that is transverse and delimits the distal cercal area on T9.

label: mesoscutum
Defs: The scutum that is located on the mesonotum.

label: decreased diameter
Defs: A diameter which is relatively small.

label: vertex patch
Defs: The setiferous patch that is located on the vertex.

label: submedian pronotal apodeme
Defs: The apodeme that is located submedially just ventrally of the dorsal margin of the pronotum and corresponds to the site of origin of the pronoto-propleural muscle.

label: mesotibio-mesobasitarsal joint
Defs: The monocondylic joint that is composed of the mesotibia, the mesobasitarsus and the articular membrane of the mesotibio-mesobasitarsal joint.

label: increased female fertility
Defs: A female fertility which is relatively high.

label: puncture
Defs: The depression that is point-like, without a flat bottom, and occurs in areas of punctate surface sculpture.

label: increased permeability
Defs: A permeability which is relatively high.

label: uniporous sensillum
Defs: The sensillum whose cuticular component has one cuticular pore.

label: decreased fluorescence
Defs: A fluorescence which is lower than normal.

label: negative charge
Defs: A quality which inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of the molecular entity possessing more electrons overall than protons, thus having an overall negative charge.

label: intraciliary transport particle
Defs: A nonmembrane-bound oligomeric protein complex that participates in bidirectional transport of molecules (cargo) along axonemal microtubules.

label: postocellar furrow
Defs: The sulcus that extends between the posterior margin of the lateral ocelli.

label: mandibular condyle
Defs: The condyle that is located ventrally (posteriorly) on the proximolateral edge of the mandible and inserts into the pleurostomal fossa.

label: posterior trochanteral condyle of the mesocoxa
Defs: The condyle that is located on the posterior trochanteral articular process of the mesocoxa and inserts into the posterior coxal fossa of the mesotrochanter.

label: sex flagellomere
Defs: The flagellomere that is modified and located on a male organism.

label: anatomical cluster
Defs: The anatomical group that has its parts adjacent to one another.

label: watery
Defs: Having the consistency of water.

label: petiole length
Defs: The median anatomical line that extends between the transverse carina on petiole and the posterior margin of the petiole.

label: parallelodromous
Defs: A branched quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having two or more parallel primary branches originate beside each other and converge apically.

label: posterior rim of the propodeum
Defs: The rim that extends along the propodeal foramen.

label: diameter of propodeal spiracle
Defs: The maximum diameter of the first abdominal spiracle.

label: costa
Defs: The wing vein that is anterior to the subcosta and is connected to the humeral plate.

label: first sclerite of the maxillary palp
Defs: The sclerite that is ringlike and is connected distolaterally to the posterior stipital sclerite via conjunctiva and muscle.

label: spiny
Defs: A surface feature shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having spines, thorns or similar thin projections on its surface.

label: posterior mesocoxo-mesotrochanteral articulation
Defs: The articulation that is composed of the posterior trochanteral condyle of the mesocoxa and the posterior coxal fossa of the mesotrochanter.

label: left
Defs: A directional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s direction that is similar to the direction of an object to the north when it faces east.

label: intersegmentalia
Defs: The sclerite that is located on the intersegmental membrane.

label: gaster
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of all abdominal segments posterior to abdominal segment 2.

label: increased adhesivity
Defs: A adhesivity which is relatively high.

label: funding source declaration textual entity
Defs: A textual entity documenting the source of funding that supported some study.

label: variant
Defs: A variability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer exhibits variation or change.

label: antero-dorsal region
Defs: Anatomical region that overlaps the anterior and dorsal regions of a body or body part.

label: coating
Defs: A texture quality that exists through a liquid cover on the surface of the bearer.

label: smooth
Defs: A texture quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s processing a surface free of roughness or irregularities.

label: prong of hypopygium
Defs: The projection that is located submedially on the distal margin of the hypopygium.

label: lower tooth
Defs: The apical tooth of the mandible that is located the most distal to the clypeus.

label: propodeo-second abdominal sternal muscle
Defs: The second abdominal sternal muscle that originates ventral to the metaphragma and inserts on the anterodorsal margin of the abdominal sternite 2.

label: nucleus
Defs: A membrane-bounded organelle of eukaryotic cells in which chromosomes are housed and replicated. In most cells, the nucleus contains all of the cell\'s chromosomes except the organellar chromosomes, and is the site of RNA synthesis and processing. In some species, or in specialized cell types, RNA metabolism or DNA replication may be absent.

label: anteroventral orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed anteroventrally.

label: mediosternite 9
Defs: The mediosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 9.

label: lateral mesoscutellar spine
Defs: The projection that is located on the posterodorsal margin of the axillula.

label: fluctuating
Defs: Recurrent and often more or less cyclic alteration.

label: axillar carina
Defs: The line that separates the dorsal and lateral axillar surfaces.

label: postpetiole height
Defs: The maximum distance between the dorsal and ventral margin of the postpetiole in lateral view.

label: decreased sensitivity toward
Defs: A sensitivity toward an external stimulus which is lower than normal/average.

label: necrotic
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s undergoing unprogrammed cell death.

label: upper mesepisternum
Defs: The area that corresponds to the site of origin of the mesopleuro-mesobasalar, second and third mesopleuro-third axillary sclerite of fore wing and second mesopleuro-mesonotal muscles.

label: intrinsic muscle of the propleuron
Defs: The propleural muscle that arises from the propleuron.

label: square
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having an equal-sided rectangular form.

label: protarsus
Defs: The tarsus that is located on the fore leg.

label: semi-deciduous(plant)
Defs: A quality inhering in a plant by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to being between evergeen and deciduous.

label: compound organ component
Defs: Multi-tissue structure that is part of a compound organ.

label: sigmoid
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s consisting of two curves, in opposite directions. S-shaped.

label: parapenisjugum
Defs: The area that is narrow and connects the parapenis with the rest of the gonostipes.

label: head width
Defs: The anatomical line that is the longest horizontal diameter of the cranium in frontal view.

label: scirrhous
Defs: A hardness quality of being rigid and resistant to pressure and fibrous.

label: differentiated
Defs: A cellular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of its stable specialization to a particular cell type.

label: subpleuron
Defs: The area that is located ventrally on the pectus.

label: stipito-galeal muscle
Defs: The maxillar muscle that arises from the posterior sclerite of the stipes medial to the site of origin of the stipito-lacinial muscle and inserts on the median wall of the galeo-lacinial complex distal to the stipito-lacinial muscle.

label: posteromedial to
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located toward the rear and mid-line surface of an organism relative to another entity.

label: pleural area
Defs: The anatomical cluster composed of the pro-, meso-, and metapleura.

label: variability
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to varying or changing.

label: facial impression
Defs: The area that is concave and is located between and ventral of the antennal foramina.

label: phototoxic
Defs: A photosensitivity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to being susceptible to damage by light.

label: posterolateral mesoscutellar carina
Defs: The carina on the posterodorsal mesoscutellum that is dorsally convex.

label: ventral metapleuro-third axillary sclerite of hind wing muscle
Defs: The metapleuro-third axillary sclerite of hind wing muscle that arises ventrolaterally from the metapectus.

label: dissolved
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s passing into solution.

label: prora
Defs: The carina that transverse and is located anterior to the antecostal sulcus on the abdominal sternum 3.

label: strain
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the relative change in the bearer\'s length or the bearer\'s volume when being stretched or squashed.

label: wing vein
Defs: The area that is linear and sclerotised and acts as support for the wing membrane.

label: acknowledgements section
Defs: Part of a publication that is about the contributions of people or institutions other than the authors.

label: desaturated brown
Defs: A color consisting of brown hue and low saturation.

label: transverse metepisternal carina
Defs: The carina that delimits posteriorly the metepisternal depression.

label: alpha mating type (yeast)
Defs: A S. cerevisiae mating type cells that secrete a pheromone that stimulates a haploids.

label: molar mass
Defs: A physical quality that inheres in a homogeneous substance containing 6.02 x 1023 atoms or molecules.

label: lateral coxal condyle of the metapleuron
Defs: The lateral coxal condyle of the pleuron that is located on the lateral coxal articular process of the metapleuron and inserts into the lateral pectal fossa of the metacoxa.

label: submedian conjunctiva on the distoventral margin of gonostyle/volsella complex
Defs: The conjunctiva that is elongate, is on the distoventral margin of the gonostyle/volsella complex and delimits laterally the site of origin of the gonostyle/volsella complex-gonossiculus muscle.

label: segmented
Defs: Consisting of segments or similar parts arranged in a longitudinal series.

label: loud
Defs: A sound amplitude which is relatively high.

label: medial metafemoro-metatibial muscle
Defs: The intrinsic leg muscle that arises medially (ventrally) of the hind femur and inserts on the genuflexor plate of the hind leg.

label: chaetobothria
Defs: The row of stout spines that is located along the anterior edge of the protibia.

label: absolute cephalic size
Defs: The arithmetic mean of the maximum cephalic length in median line and the dorsal head width.

label: fissure
Defs: The line that secondarily divides a sclerite.

label: light green
Defs: A color consisting of green hue and high brightness.

label: metascutellar arm
Defs: The area that is elevated and extends along the posterior margin of the metanotum from the metascutellum to the supraalar area.

label: occlusor of posterior thoracic spiracle
Defs: The spiracular muscle that arises form the mesopectus and inserts on the posterior thoracic spiracle.

label: normal pressure
Defs: A pressure which is relatively normal or average

label: hairy
Defs: A pilosity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being covered with hair or hairlike projections.

label: median metapleuro-metacoxal muscle
Defs: The metacoxal muscle that arises from the paracoxal ridge and from the metadiscrimenal lamella and inserts anterolaterally on the dorsal margin of the metacoxa.

label: reproductive quality
Defs: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s ability to produce new life or offspring.

label: centrally registered identifier symbol
Defs: A symbol that is part of a CRID and that is sufficient to look up a record from the CRID\'s registry.

label: parietal
Defs: The area that is lateral on the cranium between the frontal and occipital areas, separated above by the coronal suture.

label: multifocal to coalescing
Defs: Multiple lesions some interconnecting with each other.

label: everted
Defs: An oriented quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being turned outward in placement.

label: speculum
Defs: The area that is smooth, located laterally of the frontal carina and is surrounded by sculptured regions of the upper face.

label: undifferentiated
Defs: A cellular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of having not yet acquired a special structure of function.

label: displaced to
Defs: An angular placement quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being changed in position in relation to another entity.

label: gonoforceps
Defs: The sclerite that is located distally of the cupula and dorsolaterally of the volsella, surrounds the aedeagus dorsolaterally and does not connected to any sclerite distally.

label: obliquely fractured
Defs: A fractured quality where the fracture occurs at a plane oblique to the long axis of the bone.

label: anterior tentorio-stipital muscle
Defs: The tentorio-stipital muscle that is anterior to the posterior tentorio-stipital muscle.

label: tight
Defs: A pattern quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being compact or dense in arrangement.

label: main release ontology module
Defs: An ontology module that is intended to be the primary release product and the one consumed by the majority of tools.

label: mesopleuro-third axillary sclerite of hind wing muscle
Defs: The hind wing third axillary muscle that arises from the mesopleuron and inserts on the third axillary sclerite of hind wing.

label: non-potable
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer not being suitable for use as a safe means of hydration.

label: labral muscle
Defs: The head muscle that inserts on the labrum.

label: postacetabular patch
Defs: The setiferous patch that is located ventrally on the mesopleuron posterior to the epicnemial carina.

label: serrated
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of having sharp straight-edged teeth pointing to the apex.

label: mesonotal fossa of the pronotum
Defs: The submedian fossa that is located on the dorsal margin of the pronotum and accommodates the pronotal condyle of the mesonotum.

label: ventral keel of petiole
Defs: The carina that is median and extends ventrally along the petiole.

label: styloconic sensillum
Defs: The seta that is on a process.

label: elevation
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s vertical distance of a point above or below a reference surface.

label: future directions textual entity
Defs: A textual entity expressing ideas regarding future work relevant to work described in a document that could be done.

label: protibio-probasitarsal joint
Defs: The monocondylic joint that is composed of the protibia and the probasitarsus.

label: lateral carina of abdominal tergite 3
Defs: The carina that extends along the lateral margin of abdominal tergite 3.

label: affinity
Defs: A molecular quality that arises from the molecular attraction exerted between two atoms or compounds.

label: aneuploid
Defs: A ploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing a non-integral multiple of the monoploid number, due to extra or missing chromosomes.

label: abdominal laterotergite 2
Defs: The laterotergite that is located on abdominal tergum 2.

label: additional results section
Defs: A results section that reports analyses other than main results of the study (e.g. subgroups analyses, adjusted analyses, sensitivity analyses, etc.)

label: lanze
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the first valvifer and the first valvula.

label: medial coxal articular process of the metapectus
Defs: The articular process that is located on the ventral margin of the metapectus medially of the metacoxal foramen and bears the medial coxal condyle of the metapectus.

label: maxillary process of the hypostoma
Defs: The articular process that bears the cardinal condyle of the cranium.

label: activation quality
Defs: A quality that inheres in a bearer in virtue of its realizing one of its functions.

label: specillum
Defs: The median, smooth area that is smooth, is surrounded by sculptured areas and is on the abdominal mediotergite 4.

label: apex of the calcar
Defs: The area that extends distally of the apex of the velum or comb of the spur.

label: postgenal suture
Defs: The groove that is median, vertical and extends between the occipital and oral foramina separating the postgenae.

label: portion of epithelium
Defs: The anatomical structure of the epithelium that is delimited by material or immaterial anatomical entities.

label: tendrilous
Defs: Slender and spirally coiled.

label: preorbital carina
Defs: The carina that is located on the face, parallels the inner orbit and is paired.

label: tripartite
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being divided into three branches.

label: light phase
Defs: A phase which occurs during the light cycle.

label: electromagnetic (EM) radiation quality
Defs: A physical quality that inheres in an bearer by virtue of how that bearer interacts with electromagnetic radiation.

label: fore wing tegula
Defs: The cuticular evagination that is located laterally of the preaxilla and obscures the anterior mesonoto-first axillary articulation and the mesopleuro-second axillary sclerite joints.

label: multiporous plate sensillum
Defs: The sensillum that corresponds to a multiporous plate.

label: anterior trochanteral condyle of the procoxa
Defs: The condyle that is located on the anterior trochanteral articular process of the procoxa and inserts on the anterior coxal fossa of the protrochanter.

label: dilator muscle apodeme
Defs: The apodeme that corresponds to the site of origin of the dilator muscle of the propodeal spiracle.

label: increased position
Defs: A position which is relatively high.

label: length of 1st flagellomere
Defs: The proximodistal anatomical line of the 1st flagellomere.

label: basisternum
Defs: The area that is located anteriorly of the site of origin of the furca.

label: presternum
Defs: The area that is located on the basisternum and is delimited by the sternacostal sulcus.

label: median ocellus
Defs: The ocellus that is located medially on the cranium.

label: poorly differentiated
Defs: A cellular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of its lacking most of the cellular characteristics which would allow it to be fully differentiated.

label: level with
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located at the same level as another entity.

label: internal male genitalia
Defs: The compound organ that functions as producer and transporter of sperm, spermatophore and semen, composed of the testes, vas deferens, accessory glands and ductus ejaculatorius. Ecto- and mesodermal in origin.

label: single layer subset ontology module
Defs: A subset ontology that is largely comprised of a single layer or strata in an ontology class hierarchy. The purpose is typically for rolling up for visualization. The classes in the layer need not be disjoint.

label: software script
Defs: A software script is software whose instructions can be executed using a software interpreter.

label: anterior trochanteral condyle of the metacoxa
Defs: The condyle that is located on the anterior trochanteral articular process of the metacoxa and inserts into the anterior coxal fossa of the metacoxa.

label: postmental area
Defs: The area that is limited distally by the posterior margin of the prementum and laterally by the median margins of the cardines and the stipites.

label: digitate
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having distinct parts arising from a common point or center.

label: sulcus
Defs: The groove that corresponds to a ridge.

label: acetabulum
Defs: The area that is concave and accommodates the base of a segment.

label: subelliptical
Defs: A shape that is almost an ellipse.

label: intertergal suture
Defs: The line of separation that is located between consecutive abdominal terga.

label: epimeral notch
Defs: The notch that is located on the posterodorsal margin of the mesopectus and accommodates the mesothoracic spiracle.

label: bilobed
Defs: A lobed quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being divided into or having two lobes.

label: propleuro-postoccipital muscle
Defs: The postoccipital muscle that arises from the propleuron and inserts on the postocciput.

label: reduced virulence
Defs: A virulence that is relatively low.

label: distomedial stipital flange
Defs: The medial part of the principal carina of the stipes that is overlapped by the premental carina and overlaps the lateral premental face.

label: dorsal profurco-postoccipital muscle
Defs: The postoccipital muscle that arises from the dorsal part of the lateral area of the dorsal profurcal lamella and inserts on the postocciput.

label: posterior tooth of the mandible
Defs: The tooth tooth that is located on the posterior surface of the lower tooth.

label: mesosubalare muscle
Defs: The thoracic muscle that inserts on the mesosubalare.

label: broad
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s width being notably higher than its length.

label: apoptotic
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s consisting of blebbing of the nucleus and DNA fragmentation due to the cell undergoing a specific form of programmed cell death termed apoptosis.

label: postoccipital ridge
Defs: The ridge that corresponds to the postoccipital sulcus.

label: second tarsomere of hind leg
Defs: The tarsomere that is distal to and connected to the first tarsomere of the hind leg.

label: dorso-ventrally flattened
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being flattened along dorso-ventral axis.

label: peramorphic growth
Defs: A heterochronic growth quality inhering in an organism, structure, or group of organisms by virtue of the bearer\'s increased growth.

label: genal carina
Defs: The carina that extends on the gena from the lateral margin of the oral foramen.

label: abdominal sternum 4
Defs: The abdominal sternum that is located on abdominal segment 4.

label: anteromedian projection of the metanoto-propodeo-metapecto-mesopectal complex
Defs: The median projection on the anterior region of the metanoto-propodeo-metapecto-mesopectal complex.

label: dorsal ramus of the second valvula
Defs: The area that extends along the dorsal margin of the second valvula, bears the processus articularis anteriorly and the processus musculares on the antero-dorsal region and articulates anteriorly with the second valvifer via the basal articulation.

label: unlumenized
Defs: A structure quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking of a three dimensional space surrounded by one or more anatomical structures and containing one or more anatomical substances.

label: color brightness
Defs: A scalar optical property that is the intensity, value or amount of perceived light.

label: abbreviation textual entity
Defs: A textual entity listing abbreviations and their expansions that are used in a document.

label: tergite
Defs: The sclerite that is located on the tergum.

label: retrorse
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curved backward or downward.

label: mesonotal muscle
Defs: The thoracic muscle that inserts on the mesonotum.

label: model number
Defs: A model number is an information content entity specifically borne by catalogs, design specifications, advertising materials, inventory systems and similar  that is about manufactured objects of the same class. The model number is an alternative term for the class. The manufactered objects may or may not also bear the model number. Model numbers can be encoded in a variety of other information objects, such as bar codes, numerals, or patterns of dots.

label: porosity
Defs: A structure quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to admit the passage of gas or liquid through pores or interstices.

label: curvature
Defs: A surface shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting a degree of bending.

label: clypeal tooth
Defs: The projection that is located on the distal margin of the clypeus.

label: yellow green
Defs: A color consisting of yellow and green hues.

label: decreased concentration
Defs: A concentration which is lower relative to the normal or average.

label: occurrence
Defs: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s occurrence.

label: pressure
Defs: A physical quality that inheres in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s amount of force per unit area it exerts.

label: abstract
Defs: A summary of the entire document that is substantially smaller than the document it summarizes.  It is about the document it summarizes.

label: lateral pronoto-prophragmal muscle
Defs: The prophragmal muscle that arises laterally of the site of origin of the median pronoto-prophragmal and medially of the site of origin of the lateral pronoto-postoccipital muscles.

label: branchiness
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the degree to which there are subdivisions or offshoots in a bearer entity.

label: mesocoxo-mesosubalar muscle
Defs: The mesosubalare muscle that arises from the mesocoxa and inserts on the mesosubalare.

label: first valviferal fossa of the ninth tergite
Defs: The fossa of the ninth abdominal tergite that is adjacent to the condyle of the ninth tergal condyle of the first valvifer.

label: T-shaped
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being shaped in the form of the letter T.

label: nygma
Defs: The sclerotized, round patch in the middle of wing cell.

label: tangential plane
Defs: Anatomical plane that is perpendicular to a radial plane.

label: lateral metapleuro-metacoxal articulation
Defs: The articulation that is composed of the lateral coxal condyle of the metapleuron and the lateral pectal fossa of the metacoxa.

label: proximal lobe of vas deferens
Defs: The lobe that is connected to the vas deferens.

label: anatomical line
Defs: A one dimensional, immaterial anatomical entity.

label: quality of a solid
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting the physical characteristics of an entity characterized by particles arranged such that their shape and volume are relatively stable.

label: sharpness
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a sharp or tapered end or point.

label: nonpolar polarity
Defs: A molecular quality which inheres in a molecular entity when the molecular entity does not possess an electrical dipole.

label: profemoral scrobe of the mesopectus
Defs: The scrobe that is on the mesopectus and accommodates the profemur.

label: female pseudohermaphrodite
Defs: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population by virtue of having internal reproductive organs of female and external sexual characteristics of male.

label: anteromedial orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed anteromedially.

label: dorsal side
Defs: An anatomical region that is the entire part of an anatomical structure dorsal to a horizontal plane and bounded on one side by the same transverse plane.

label: labial palp
Defs: The anatomical structure that is distal to the proximal margin of the first sclerite of the labial palp.

label: uniform diameter
Defs: A diameter that remains constant throughout the extent of an entity.

label: pronoto-mesonotal articulation
Defs: The articulation that is composed of the pronotal condyle of the mesoscutum and the mesonotal fossa of the pronotum.

label: circulatory system
Defs: The anatomical system that is involved in circulation.

label: lateral carina of the gastral scrobe
Defs: The carina that delimits laterally the gastral scrobe.

label: first median plate
Defs: The sclerite that is located between the second axillary and the distal arm of the third axillary at the base of the mediocubital field.

label: physical object quality
Defs: A quality which inheres in a continuant.

label: posterior profurcal lamella
Defs: The ridge that extends along the dorsal margin of the dorsal profurcal lamella and corresponds to the site of origin of the lateral profurco-procoxal muscle.

label: metapleural sulcus
Defs: The line that corresponds with the metapleural ridge.

label: liquid configuration
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s parts having the arrangement which exhibits characteristics of liquids.

label: amphiphilic
Defs: Having both hydrophilic and hydrophobic (or lipophilic) groups.

label: marginal rim of scutellum
Defs: The area that extends along the posterior margin of the mesoscutellum and is delimited anteriorly by the posterior mesoscutellar sulcus.

label: accessory gland
Defs: The gland that empties into one of the reproductive ducts.

label: seta
Defs: The sensillum with a hair-like cuticular component.

label: anteromesoscutum
Defs: The area that is located anterior to the transscutal articulation.

label: valvar ridge
Defs: The ridge that is vertical and extends along the valviceps.

label: laterope
Defs: The depression that is located laterally and proximally on abdominal tergum 2.

label: mislocalised dorsally
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being positioned towards the back or upper surface of an organism.

label: basal vein
Defs: The wing vein that is basally located on the fore wing and connects or nearly connects the submarginal vein and the medial plus cubital veins.

label: normal object quality
Defs: A quality of an object that has a value that is normal or average.

label: basal lacinial sclerite
Defs: The sclerite that is on the medial stipital wall, connected to the lacinial lobe and receives the site of insertion of the stipito-lacinial muscle.

label: ruffled
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting disturbance of its smoothness or regularity.

label: decreased process quality
Defs: A quality of a process that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.

label: sensillum coeloconicum B
Defs: The sensillum coeloconicum, in which the diameter of the tip of the hairlike cuticular component is as wide as the surrounding depression.

label: stridulatory organ
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the plectrum and the stridulitrum.

label: normal duration of temperature
Defs: A duration quality of temperature quality of a process which is relatively normal.

label: posterior proximal process of the mesobasitarsus
Defs: The process that is located posteriorly on the proximal margin of the mesobasitarsus and corresponds to the site of insertion of the posterior mesotibio-mesobasitarsal muscle.

label: pronope
Defs: The depression that is dorsomedian and is located on the pronotum.

label: pleurostomal condyle
Defs: The condyle that is located on the anterior (dorsal) margin of the pleurostoma and inserts into the mandibular acetabulum.

label: median profurco-procoxal muscle
Defs: The procoxal muscle that arises partly from the posteroventral surface of the ventral profurcal lamella and partly from the ventral surface of the profurcal arm.

label: interocellar pit
Defs: The pit that is located on the upper face between lateral ocelli and corresponds internally with a conical apodeme and not the tentorium.

label: lateral petiolar carina
Defs: The carina that extends laterally on the abdominal tergum 2 from the petiolar collar to the second abdominal spiracle laterally of the dorsope.

label: behavioural inactive
Defs: A behavioral quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to lack activity.

label: protibial spur
Defs: The tibial spur that is located on the fore leg, is curved and together with the probasitarsus forms the strigil.

label: irregular density
Defs: A density quality which lacks pattern.

label: pronotal plate
Defs: The area of the pronotum that is median, raised and limited laterally by sharp edges.

label: laterosternite 7
Defs: The laterosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 7.

label: anterior rim of pronotum
Defs: The area that extends along the anterior margin of the pronotum and is delimited posteriorly by the transverse pronotal suclus.

label: anterior metatibio-metabasitarsal muscle
Defs: The intrinsic leg muscle that arises anteriorly from the metatibia and inserts on the anterior proximal process of the metabasitarsus.

label: medial profemoro-protibial muscle
Defs: The intrinsic leg muscle that arises medially from the profemur and inserts on the genuflexor plate of the fore leg.

label: increased variability of rate
Defs: A variability of rate which is relatively high.

label: retinaculum
Defs: The area that is located posteriorly on the fore wing, is ventrally curved and accommodate the hamuli.

label: scutoscutellar suture
Defs: The line that traverses the mesonotum between the postmedian notal wing processes.

label: decreased combustibility
Defs: An decrease in combustibility.

label: phragma
Defs: The antecosta that corresponds to the site of attachment of the dorsal longitudinal muscles in the thorax.

label: statistical analysis section
Defs: A part of the document used to describe the statistical methodologies employed in the work presented in the document.

label: first subdiscal
Defs: The wing cell that is located on the wing.

label: light cyan
Defs: A color consisting of cyan hue and high brightness.

label: abdominal segment 7
Defs: The abdominal segment that is located between abdominal segment 6 and abdominal segment 8.

label: desaturated purple
Defs: A color consisting of purple color and low saturation.

label: occlusor muscle apodeme of the mesothoracic spiracle
Defs: The apodeme that corresponds to the site of origin of anterior thoracic spiracle occlusor muscle.

label: second valvula
Defs: The area of the second valvifer-second valvula-third valvula complex that is distal to the basal articulation and to the processus musculares and is limited medially by the median body axis.

label: longitudinal carina of the propleuron
Defs: The carina that extends along the lateral margin of the ventral propleural area.

label: wilty
Defs: To bend or hang downwards due to loss of water

label: decreased tolerance to
Defs: A tolerance quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s decreased ability to endure a stimulus.

label: inefficient
Defs: An efficiency quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking efficiency.

label: metepimeron
Defs: The epimeron that is located on the metapleuron and is located posteriorly of the metapleural sulcus.

label: glymma
Defs: The groove that is located between the spiracle and the anterior margin of abdominal tergum 2.

label: scalene triangular
Defs: A triangular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having all sides of unequal length.

label: transvalviferal conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva that traverses the first valvifer and separates the dorsal and ventral sclerites of the first valvifer.

label: postero-ventral region
Defs: Anatomical region that overlaps the posterior and ventral regions of a body or body part.

label: morphology
Defs: A quality of a single physical entity inhering in the bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s size or shape or structure.

label: necessity (continuant)
Defs: A quality of a single physical entity inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer is essential or indispensable.

label: subgenal coronet
Defs: The row of setae that extends along the carina paramandibular process and curves behind the mandibular base.

label: scape length
Defs: The proximodistal anatomical line of the scapal area that is distal to the radicle.

label: population quality
Defs: A quality that inheres in an entire population or part of a population.

label: ectophallus
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the sclerites and muscles of the external male genitalia.

label: dot plot
Defs: A dot plot is a report graph which is a graphical representation of data where each data point is represented by a single dot placed on coordinates corresponding to data point values in particular dimensions.

label: anterior surface of the glossa
Defs: The area of the glossa that is between the distal glossal edge and the anterior glossal plate.

label: basal to
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located toward the base of an organism relative to another entity.

label: lateral axillar area
Defs: The area that is located laterally on the axilla and is delimited medially by the axillar carina.

label: glutinous
Defs: An amylose composition quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having negligible or no amylose content.

label: methods section
Defs: A part of a publication about an investigation that is about the study design of the investigation

label: wet
Defs: A wetness quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being covered by a liquid.

label: proximodorsal gonostyle/volsella complex-penisvalval muscle
Defs: The dorsal gonostyle/volsella complex penisvalval muscle that arises proximodorsally from the gonostyle/volsella complex and inserts on the penisvalva distally of the site of insertion of the distodorsal gononstyle/volsella complex-penisvalva muscle.

label: basal grooves
Defs: The row of impressions that extends along the anterior margin of an abdominal tergum or a sternum.

label: facial apodeme
Defs: The apodeme that is dorsal to the intertorular line and ventral to the anterior ocellus.

label: postgenal cushion
Defs: The setiferous patch that is located on the postgena.

label: trapezoid
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being a quadrilateral with two parallel sides.

label: second tarsomere of mid leg
Defs: The tarsomere that is distal to and connected to the first tarsomere of the mid leg.

label: lateral metafemoro-metatibial muscle
Defs: The intrinsic leg muscle that arises laterally from the metafemur and inserts on the dorsal process of the metatibia.

label: infrabuccal pouch
Defs: The pouch that is situated on the hypopharyngeal wall distally of the sitophore.

label: grooved
Defs: Texture quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being marked with one or more channels.

label: second valvifer-third valvula complex
Defs: The area of the second valvifer-second valvula-third valvula complex that is proximal to the basal articulation.

label: hydrophilic
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to having a strong affinity for water; tending to dissolve in, mix with, or be wetted by water.

label: dark red brown
