Defs: A color consisting of red and brown hue and low brightness.

label: sixth maxillary palpal sclerite
Defs: The sclerite that is ringlike and is connected via conjunctiva distally to the fifth sclerite of the maxillary palp via conjunctiva.

label: cavitated compound organ
Defs: Compound organ that contains one or more macroscopic anatomical spaces.

label: fore wing base
Defs: The wing base that is located in the mesothorax.

label: w-shaped
Defs: An angular shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having two angles in its length giving the bearer the form of the letter W.

label: invariant shape
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking or not exhibiting variation of shape.

label: paracoxal ridge
Defs: The ridge that extends along the anterior margin of the metapectus.

label: longitudinal sensillum
Defs: The multiporous plate sensillum that is elongate.

label: umbilicated fovea
Defs: The depression that is medially raised and bears medially a seta.

label: transparent
Defs: A optical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking opacity.

label: shell shaped
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a shape like a shell.

label: metapleuro-metabasalar muscle
Defs: The metabasalar muscle that arises from the metapleuron and inserts on the metabasalare.

label: right side of
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located on right side of a another entity.

label: metasomal sternum
Defs: The abdominal sternum that is located in the metasoma.

label: normal strength
Defs: A strength which is relatively normal or average

label: acrosternite 5
Defs: The acrosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 5.

label: sternite
Defs: The sternite that is located on the abdominal sternum.

label: ovipositor
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the first valvulae, second valvulae, third valvulae, first valvifers, second valvifers and female T9.

label: multipotent
Defs: A cellular potency that is the capacity to form multiple differentiated cell types.

label: dorsal-ventral gradient
Defs: Anatomical gradient that is distributed along the dorsal-ventral axis.

label: bacterial mating type
Defs: A mating type that indicates whether the F plasmid has integrated into the chromosome.

label: tubular A9
Defs: The conjunctiva that connects the female T8 with female T9 and is tubular.

label: prospinasternum
Defs: The spinasternum that is located anterior to the mesopectus.

label: aedeagus
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of sclerites that are adjacent to the distal end of the ejaculatory duct.

label: viscid
Defs: A coating quality which is sticky or clammy.

label: anterior mesonoto-mesotrochanteral muscle
Defs: The mesonoto-mesotrochanteral muscle that arises from the mesonotum anterior to the site of origin of the posterior mesonoto-mesotrochanteral muscle when present and inserts on the mesotrochanteral apodeme.

label: intervolsellal muscle
Defs: The male genitalia muscle that connects the proximal part of parossiculi.

label: maximum cephalic length
Defs: The median anatomical line that extends between the posterior margin of the cranium and the distal clypeal line in frontal view.

label: decreased contractility
Defs: A contractility which is relatively low.

label: increased weight
Defs: A weight which is relatively high.

label: unbalanced
Defs: A balance quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking balance.

label: decreased male receptivity
Defs: A male receptivity which is relatively low.

label: reproductive system
Defs: The anatomical system that is involved in reproduction.

label: foveate
Defs: A texture quality inhering in a surface by virtue of the bearer\'s being marked by the presence of small, shallow, regular depressions called fovae.

label: basal glossal invagination
Defs: The anterior invagination of the labium that is adjacent with the distal end of the salivarium and separates the glossa proximally from the distal hypopharynx and the paraglossae.

label: spatulate
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being oblong, with the lower end very much attenuated.

label: axillary cord of the fore wing
Defs: The axillary cord that is located on the fore wing.

label: dark yellow brown
Defs: A color consisting of yellow and brown hue and low brightness.

label: third sclerite of the maxillary palp
Defs: The sclerite that is ringlike and is connected distally to the second sclerite of the maxillary palp via conjunctiva.

label: trachea
Defs: The cuticular invagination that is tubular, branched into tracheoles and bears the taenidia.

label: cellular anatomical entity
Defs: A part of a cellular organism that is either an immaterial entity or a material entity with granularity above the level of a protein complex but below that of an anatomical system. Or, a substance produced by a cellular organism with granularity above the level of a protein complex.

label: mesopleural sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that corresponds to the mesopleural ridge.

label: medial propodeal furrow
Defs: The impression that is longitudinal and located medially on the abdominal tergum 1.

label: permeable
Defs: A permeability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being capable to be permeated or pervaded by a gas or liquid (as by osmosis or diffusion).

label: synsternum
Defs: The sternite that is at least two times as long as an adjacent sternite.

label: pectal fossa of the coxa
Defs: The fossa that is located on the coxa and accommodates the coxal condyle of the pleuron.

label: blunt
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s terminating gradually in a rounded end.

label: vulva
Defs: The anatomical space that corresponds to the opening of the vagina.

label: proximal profemoral apodeme
Defs: The apodeme that extends along the proximo-median margin of the profemur and corresponds to the site of insertion of the protrochantero-profemoral muscle.

label: metafemoral spine
Defs: The spine that is located on the anterior face of the metafemur.

label: integer numeral
Defs: A numeral that denotes an integer

label: cellular_component
Defs: A location, relative to cellular compartments and structures, occupied by a macromolecular machine when it carries out a molecular function. There are two ways in which the gene ontology describes locations of gene products: (1) relative to cellular structures (e.g., cytoplasmic side of plasma membrane) or compartments (e.g., mitochondrion), and (2) the stable macromolecular complexes of which they are parts (e.g., the ribosome).

label: neoplastic, non-invasive
Defs: A disposition inhering in a tumour by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition not to invade surrounding tissues.

label: subapical tooth
Defs: The projection that is located on the distal half of the tarsal claw and proximal to the apex.

label: ventrolateral basiglossal arm
Defs: The projection that is located proximolaterally on the anterior glossal plate and articulates with the basiparaglossal sclerite.

label: length
Defs: A 1-D extent quality which is equal to the distance between two points.

label: decumbent
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lying or growing on the ground but with erect or rising tips.

label: decreased photosensitivity
Defs: A photosensitivity which is relatively low.

label: lateral propleuro-postoccipital muscle
Defs: The propleuro-postoccipital muscle that arises laterally from the propleuron.

label: curled
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having parallel chains in undulate fashion on the border.

label: notes section
Defs: A part of a document containing typically short notes about the document itself and/or the authors. Often the notes section contains subsections related to funding, competing interests, ethical approval, etc.

label: monoploid
Defs: A ploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing a single set of unique homologous chromosomes.

label: kleisiades
Defs: The area that is located apically on the gonostyle when it consist only from one sclerite and set off partly by conjunctiva. The kleisiades is never connected to the proximal part of the gonostyle via muscles.

label: axillula
Defs: The area that is located laterally on the mesoscutellum and is limited anteriorly by the scutoscutellar suture and medially by the axillular line.

label: basal cardinal ridge
Defs: The cardinal ridge that is median.

label: ventral head line
Defs: The anatomical line between the anteriormost (ventralmost) points of compound eyes in frontal view.

label: scutoscutellar ridge
Defs: The ridge that extends along the anterior margin of the mesoscutellum and corresponds to the scutoscutellar suture.

label: abdominal segment 3
Defs: The abdominal segment that is located between abdominal segment 2 and abdominal segment 4.

label: cartilaginous
Defs: A composition quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s cartilage quantities.

label: arrow-shaped
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s forming two equal obtuse triangles with a short side in common.

label: proximoventral gonostyle/volsella complex-penisvalval muscle
Defs: The ventral gonostyle/volsella complex-penisvalval muscle that arises ventromedially from the gonostyle/volsella complex, inserts on the proximal end of the penisvalva and is oriented proximodorsally.

label: insensitive toward
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking sensitivity toward an external stimulus.

label: recent
Defs: A quality of a process which occurs near to or not long before the present.

label: articular membrane of the metacoxo-metatrochanteral joint
Defs: The articular membrane that is located in the metacoxo-metatrochanteral joint.

label: lateral scutellar pit
Defs: The pit that is located along the posterolateral margin of the mesoscutellum.

label: acidophilic
Defs: An affinity inhering in a tissue constituent by virtue of the bearer exhibiting a molecular interaction for acidic dyes under specific ph conditions.

label: occipital margin
Defs: The margin of the cranium that is dorsal in frontal view.

label: median anatomical line
Defs: The anatomical line that extends in the median axis of the organism.

label: cut
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being regularly divided by deep incisions.

label: decreased distance
Defs: A distance which is lesser relative to the normal or average.

label: radiation exposure
Defs: A radiation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of what the bearer receives as a result of being exposed to ionizing radiation.

label: labial palpal excision
Defs: The notch that is located distolaterally on the prementum and receives the base of the labial palp.

label: posterodorsal metapleural sulcus
Defs: The groove on the posterodorsal margin of the metapleuron.

label: sepal-like
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s similarity to the appearance of a sepal,

label: pleurostomal fossa
Defs: The fossa that is located postero- (ventro-) medially on the pleurostoma and accommodates the mandibular condyle.

label: capacitance
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s ability to hold an electrical charge.

label: edibility
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to being fit to be eaten.

label: orbital band
Defs: The band that extends along the medial margin of the eye.

label: pronotal triangle
Defs: The area that is delimted by two pronotal ridges laterally and the posterior margin of the pronotum anteriorly.

label: dorsal tooth
Defs: The apical tooth of mandible that is located closest to the clypeus.

label: cellular adhesivity
Defs: A cellular quality that exists by virtue of the disposition of the cell to adhere to other cells and molecules, through the emergent action of the molecular parts of the cell surface.

label: system
Defs: A material entity consisting of multiple components that are causally integrated.

label: dystonicity
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s impaired elastic tension that facilitate response to stimuli.

label: waxy
Defs: Presence of long chain aliphatic lipids on the surface of an organism.

label: auxotrophic
Defs: A nutritional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s inability to synthesize a particular organic compound required for its growth.

label: desaturated orange
Defs: A color consisting of orange hue and low saturation.

label: decreased amount
Defs: An amount which is relatively low.

label: composition
Defs: A single physical entity inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s quantities or relative ratios of subparts.

label: ventrolaterally orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed ventrolaterally.

label: curation status specification
Defs: The curation status of the term. The allowed values come from an enumerated list of predefined terms. See the specification of these instances for more detailed definitions of each enumerated value.

label: decreased force
Defs: A force which is relative low.

label: female organism
Defs: Gonochoristic organism that can produce female gametes.

label: old
Defs: An age which is relatively high.

label: epipharyngeal brush
Defs: The setiferous patch that is unpaired, sublateral and situated distally on the epipharyngeal wall on the left torma.

label: viability
Defs: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer or a population by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to survive and develop normally or the number of surviving individuals in a given population.

label: portion of cell substance
Defs: Portion of organism substance located within a cell.

label: metaphragma
Defs: The phragma that corresponds to the site of origin of the mesophragmo-metaphragmal and metaphragmo-second abdominal tergal muscles.

label: abdominal sternum
Defs: The sternum that is located on the abdominal segment.

label: inelastic
Defs: An elasticity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s inability to recover its size and shape after deformation in any way.

label: abdominal laterotergite 6
Defs: The laterotergite that is located on abdominal tergum 6.

label: anapleurite
Defs: The pleurite that extends ventrally of the lateral margin of the tergum and dorsally of the coxopleurite.

label: photographic print
Defs: A photographic print is a material entity upon which a photograph generically depends.

label: sensillar patch of the second valvifer
Defs: The patch that is composed of placoid sensilla adjacent to the intervalvifer articulation.

label: felt line
Defs: The band that is composed of flattened setae and secretory pores and is located laterally on abdominal tergum 3.

label: posterior margin of the first valvifer
Defs: The margin of the first valvifer that is posterior and extends between the intervalvifer articulation and the anterior angle of the first valvifer.

label: normal length
Defs: A length quality which is relatively normal or average

label: propecto-procoxal joint
Defs: The monocondylic joint that is composed of the propectus, the procoxa and the articular membrane of the propecto-procoxal joint.

label: metapleural cavity
Defs: The impression that is located at the anteroventral corner of the metapleuron.

label: splayed
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curved outward.

label: cell periphery
Defs: The part of a cell encompassing the cell cortex, the plasma membrane, and any external encapsulating structures.

label: mediosternite 8
Defs: The mediosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 8.

label: undivided
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being unseparated into parts or divisions.

label: meron
Defs: The area that is located posterolaterally and proximally on the coxa, proximal to the basicostal suture.

label: type I sensillum trichodea
Defs: Sensilla trichodea type I occur on the distal ends [...] of the antennal flagellum.  They have small conical basal sockets with slender and strongly bent shafts.

label: basal line of the second valvifer
Defs: The line on the second valvifer that extends between the pars articularis and the dorsal flange of second valvifer.

label: decreased threshold
Defs: A threshold which is relatively low.

label: tibial articular process of the mesobasitarsus
Defs: The articular process that is located dorsally on the proximal margin of the mesobasitarsus and bears the tibial condyle of the mesobasitarsus.

label: soluble in
Defs: A solubility quality inhering in a substance by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to dissolve in a liquid.

label: non-contractile
Defs: A contractility quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s inability of contracting or being contracted.

label: mandibular acetabulum
Defs: The fossa that is located anteriorly on the proximolateral edge of the mandible and accommodates the pleurostomal coondyle.

label: mislocalised proximally
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being positioned towards to point of attachment or origin.

label: generated ontology module
Defs: An ontology module that is automatically generated, for example via a SPARQL query or via template and a CSV.

label: fourth flagellomere
Defs: The flagellomere that is located immediately distal to the third flagellomere.

label: incomplete structure
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking parts or having a reduced form compared to fully formed entities.

label: Ventral invagination of mesometapleural sulcus
Defs: The invagination that is at the ventral end of the of the mesometapleural sulcus.

label: mesosoma
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the prothorax, mesothorax and the metapectal-propodeal complex.

label: alobate
Defs: A surface feature shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s not having undulating edges forming lobes.

label: metapleural area of the mesonoto-metanoto-mesopecto-metapecto-propodeal complex
Defs: The lateral (vertical) area that is posterior to the mesometapleural sulcus and anterior to the metapleural carina.

label: posterior mesepimeral area
Defs: The area that extends along the posterior margin of the mesopleuron and is delimited anteriorly by the mesepimeral sulcus.

label: fore wing venation
Defs: The venation of the fore wing.

label: patients textual entity
Defs: A textual entity expressing information regarding the patients used in a study.

label: articular membrane of the mesotibio-mesobasitarsal muscle
female sterile
Defs: A female fertility quality inhering in a female by virtue of the bearer\'s being incapable of initiating, sustaining, or supporting reproduction.

label: ventral mesofurco-profurcal muscle
Defs: The profurcal muscle that arises from the mesofurcal bridge and inserts proximally of the profurca.

label: increased elasticity
Defs: An elasticity which is relatively high.

label: broken into two pieces
Defs: A broken quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being seperated into two contiguous wholes.

label: multilaminar epithelium
Defs: Epithelium that consists of more than one layer of epithelial cells.

label: fourth intrinsic muscle of the maxillary palp
Defs: The muscle that arises from the third sclerite of the maxillary palp and inserts on the fourth sclerite of the maxillary palp.

label: blistered
Defs: A texture quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of a local accumulation of fluid underneath the surface of the bearer.

label: decreased coordination
Defs: A coordination which is relatively low.

label: bronze
Defs: A medium brown color with a metallic sheen, resembles the actual alloy bronze.

label: coriaceous
Defs: The reticulate that is composed of convex scutes.

label: resistant to
Defs: A resistance quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s resistance to a stimulus.

label: intrinsic leg muscle
Defs: The leg muscle that inserts and originates in the leg.

label: radial symmetry
Defs: A symmetry quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having equal proportion around a central point or axis.

label: decreased degree of illumination
Defs: An decrease in illumination.

label: basivalvula
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of small sclerites and is located proximally on the first valvulae.

label: pretarsus
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is apical to the telotarsus and composed of the empodium, auxilia, planta, pulvillum, unguis, unguitractor plate, auxiliar sclerite and manubrium.

label: patchy
Defs: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being marked by, consisting of, or diversified with patches.

label: postocellar vertex
Defs: The area posterior to the imaginary line intersecting the lateral ocelli and anterior to the occipital carina.

label: subantennal carina
Defs: The carina that is located on the lower face ventrally of the antennal foramen and dorsally of the clypeus.

label: juvenile
Defs: A maturity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue the bearer\'s being not fully grown or developed.

label: ventral metatibio-metabasitarsal muscle
Defs: The intrinsic leg muscle that arises anteriorly from the tibia and inserts ventrally on the proximal margin of the metabasitarsus.

label: profurco-laterocervical muscle
Defs: The laterocervical muscle that arises medially from the anterior surface of the dorsal profurcal lamella.

label: splayed caudal
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curved outwards from the part of the body from which the tail arises.

label: eroding
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer bring gradually worn away.

label: punctiform
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being small and resembling a point.

label: intersternite
Defs: The intersegmentalia that is located in between sterna.

label: dorsal tendon attachment
Defs: The area that corresponds to the site of insertion of the metaphragmo-second abdominal tergal muscle.

label: non-fragile
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s ability to withstand great strain without tearing or breaking.

label: vertical apodemal lobe of the mesoscutellum
Defs: The inflection that extends along the posterolateral margin of the mesoscutellum and articulates with the dorsal propodeal inflection.

label: decreased adhesivity
Defs: A adhesivity which is relatively low.

label: anterior mesopleural area
Defs: The area that is limited posteriorly by the anterior mesopleural sulcus.

label: dorsal propleural area
Defs: The area that is located posterodorsally of the well-sclerotized lateral propleural area and usually differs from it in sculpture.

label: antecostal sulcus of the first abdominal tergum
Defs: The sulcus that corresponds to the metaphragma.

label: normal osmolality
Defs: An osmolality which is relatively normal or average odor.

label: functional
Defs: A functionality quality held by the bearer when the latter is able to perform a regular function(s).

label: decreased permeability
Defs: A permeability which is relatively low.

label: anterior side
Defs: An anatomical region that is the entire part of an anatomical structure anterior to a transverse plane and bounded on one side by the same transverse plane.

label: femoral articular process of the protrochanter
Defs: The articular process that is located laterally on the distal margin of the protrochanter and bears the femoral condyle of the metatrochanter.

label: desaturated green
Defs: A color consisting of green hue and low saturation.

label: misaligned with
Defs: An alignment quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being in a improper spatial positioning with respect to an additional entity.

label: immortal
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to being capable of indefinite growth or division.

label: fecundity
Defs: A reproductive quality inhering in an organism or population by virtue of the bearer\'s potential reproductive capacity ad measured by the number of gametes.

label: teardrop-shaped
Defs: A convex 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s shape resembling falling drop.

label: distal hypopharyngeal sclerite
Defs: The sclerite that receives the site of insertions of the dorsal and ventral premento-salivarial muscles and is continuous with the hypopharyngeal rod.

label: posterior coxal fossa of the metatrochanter
Defs: The fossa that is located posteriorly on the proximal margin of the metatrochanter and accommodates the posterior trochanteral condyle of the metacoxa.

label: obstructed
Defs: A morphological quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being blocked or filled with obstacles or an obstacle.

label: trochantinal lobe
Defs: The area that is extends along the extreme posterior margin of the mesopleuron anterior to mesocoxa and is delimited anteriorly by an impression.

label: fluid-filled
Defs: Bounded structure filled with fluid.

label: epistomal distance
Defs: The anatomical line that is the shortest between the anterior tentorial pits.

label: craspedodromous
Defs: A branched quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having secondary branches terminating at the margin.

label: compiling software
Defs: A planned process that converts human-written or curated software into a machine-executable or interpretable set of instructions.

label: length of T1
Defs: The median anatomical line of the abdominal tergum 2.

label: calyx
Defs: The anatomical space that is located anteriorly in the lateral oviduct and which receives the ovariole pedicels.

label: heatmap
Defs:
A heatmap is a report graph which is a graphical representation of data
where the values taken by a variable(s) are shown as colors in a
two-dimensional map.

label: spatial pattern
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting repetition of placement of its parts.

label: preapical tooth
Defs: The tooth that is located distodorsally on the mandible.

label: acidopore
Defs: The anatomical space that is surrounded by the posterior margin of abdominal sternum 7.

label: posterior mesocoxo-mesotrochanteral muscle
Defs: The mesotrochanteral muscle that arises posteriorly from the mesocoxa and inserts posteriorly on the mesotrochanter laterally of the posterior mesocoxo-mesotrochanteral articulation.

label: data item
Defs: An information content entity that is intended to be a truthful statement about something (modulo, e.g., measurement precision or other systematic errors) and is constructed/acquired by a method which reliably tends to produce (approximately) truthful statements.

label: increased functionality
Defs: A functional quality held by the bearer when the latter exhibits increased ability to perform a regular function(s).

label: pleural pit
Defs: The pit that is located on the pleuron and corresponds to the pleural apophysis.

label: descriptive data section
Defs: A document part that lists and defines data variables, describes data characteristics (e.g. missing data information) and any assumptions and simplifications made.

label: transverse pronotal sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that corresponds to the anteromedian pronotal ridge.

label: variability of temperature
Defs: A variability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer exhibits temperature variation or change.

label: profurco-protrochanteral muscle
Defs: The protrochanteral muscle that arises from the profurca and inserts on the protrochanteral apodeme.

label: transfacial sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that is limited laterally by the intersection of the frontofacial sulcus and the scrobal sulcus.

label: propodeo-second abdominal tergal muscle
Defs: The second abdominal tergal muscle that arises from the abdominal tergum 1 and inserts on the abdominal tergum 2.

label: height
Defs: A 1-D extent quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s vertical dimension of extension.

label: distal orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed distally.

label: increased male fertility
Defs: A male fertility which is relatively high.

label: ventral mesotibio-mesobasitarsal muscle
Defs: The intrinsic leg muscle that arises ventrally from the mesotibia and inserts ventrally on the articular membrane of the mesotibio-mesobasitarsal joint.

label: rastellum
Defs: The row of spurs that extends along the distal margin of the metatibia.

label: mediosternite 10
Defs: The mediosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 10.

label: lateral metapleuro-metacoxal muscle
Defs: The metacoxal muscle that originates ventrally of the metapleural ridge and inserts anterolaterally on the dorsal margin of the metacoxa.

label: anterioralized
Defs: A malformed quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s gross morphology containing what are normally anterior structures and missing some or all of what are normally posterior structures.

label: wing venation
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of abscissae.

label: axillary cord
Defs: The area that is heavily sclerotized and located proximally on the posterior wing margin.

label: anterior petiolar length
Defs: The median anatomical line between the setal line of petiole and the transverse carina of petiole.

label: epipharyngeal wall
Defs: The conjunctiva that extends between the distal margin of the labrum and the proximal boundary of the cibarium.

label: posterodorsal branch of pronotal Y
Defs: The sulcus that connects the transverse pronotal sulcus and the posterior margin of the pronotum ventral to the anterior thoracic spiracle and together with the ventral portion of the transverse pronotal sulcus delimits anteriorly the site of origin of the pronoto-mesobasalar muscle.

label: male fertility
Defs: A fertility quality of inhering in a male by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to initiate, sustain, or support reproduction.

label: intrinsic muscle of the metapleuron
Defs: The metapleural muscle that arises from the metapleuron.

label: T10
Defs: The tergite that is connected posteriorly to T9 via conjunctiva and muscles.

label: unbranched
Defs: A branchiness quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking branches.

label: pink
Defs: Red color having medium to high brightness and low to moderate saturation.

label: pseudoceps
Defs: The projection that is medial and located apically on the penisvalva.

label: apical region
Defs: Anatomical region located on the apical end on the body or body part.

label: mislocalised posteriorly
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being positioned towards the rear of an organism.

label: clypeus-torulus distance
Defs: The anatomical line that is the shortest between the ventral margin of the torulus and the epistomal sulcus.

label: U-shaped
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being shaped in the form of the letter U.

label: parapsidal line
Defs: The signum that is located between the notaulus and the parascutal carina and corresponds to the site of origin of the dorsoventral indirect flight muscle.

label: facet
Defs: The portion of cuticle that covers externally the cellular components of the ommatidium.

label: serous
Defs: A quality inhering a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing or resembling serum.

label: flabellum
Defs: The sclerite that is located at the apex of the glossa in Apoidea.

label: green
Defs: A color hue with medium-low wavelength of that portion of the visible spectrum lying between yellow and blue, evoked in the human observer by radiant energy with wavelengths of approximately 490 to 570 nanometers.

label: sternopleurite
Defs: The pleurite that located medially of the coxa and laterally of the sternum.

label: metascutellar carina
Defs: The carina that delimits laterally the metascutellum.

label: pilosity
Defs: A texture quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having hair or bristles.

label: ocellar hair patch
Defs: The setiferous patch that extends posteriorly or posterolaterally of the median ocellus.

label: hairy ring of T3
Defs: The setiferous patch that is extending along the third metasomal tergum.

label: median oblique line
Defs: The depression that is oblique and located submedially on the mesopleuron between the fore coxa and posterolateral corner of the mesopleuron.

label: anterior part of pronotal plate
Defs: The area medially on the anterior rim of the pronotum that is distinctly delineated and its outline directly continuous with the scutellar foveae and the pronotal plate.

label: saccular
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a three dimensional cavity with a narrow or no opening, and often containing an anatomical substance.

label: force
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s rate of change of momentum.

label: adult tagma
Defs: The tagma that is part of the adult.

label: footnote
Defs: A part of a document that is about a specific other part of the document.  Usually footnotes are spatially segregated from the rest of the document.

label: paraclypeal margin
Defs: The edge that extends laterally of the pleurostoma.

label: spirally fractured
Defs: A fractured quality that occurs when torque (a rotating force) is applied along the axis of a bone.

label: transscutal articulation
Defs: The line of separation that extends along the transscutal line.

label: interommatidial seta
Defs: The seta that is located at the intersection of the margins of three ommatidiae.

label: electronegativity
Defs: A quality that describes the power of an atom to attract electrons to itself .

label: h minus
Defs: A S. pombe mating type determined by the mat1-Mc and mat1-Mi on the mat1 locus.

label: lateral coxal condyle of the mesopleuron
Defs: The lateral coxal condyle of the pleuron that is located on the lateral coxal articular process of the mesopleuron and inserts into the lateral mesopectal fossa of the mesocoxa.

label: posterior coxal fossa of the mesotrochanter
Defs: The fossa that is located posteriorly on the proximal margin of the mesotrochanter accommodating the posterior trochanteral condyle of the mesocoxa.

label: telescopic
Defs: Having or resembling the shape of a telescope.

label: metafurcal pit
Defs: The furcal pit that is located in the metathorax.

label: postacetabular sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that extends posteriorly along the epicnemial carina.

label: distal clypeal line
Defs: The anatomical line that is perpendicular to the median anatomical line and is the tangent at the distalmost point(s) of the clypeus in frontal view.

label: medial mesopecto-mesocoxal articulation
Defs: The articulation that is composed of the medial coxal condyle of the mesopectus and the medial pectal fossa of the mesocoxa.

label: increased length
Defs: A length quality which is relatively large.

label: intertorular carina
Defs: The carina that extends between the dorsal margin of the antennal rims.

label: anterodorsal rim of petiole
Defs: The rim that is transverse and is at the posterior margin of the anterior profile of petiolar node.

label: scarred
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being fibrous tissue that replaces normal tissue destroyed by injury or disease.

label: dark grey
Defs: A color consisting of grey color and low brightness.

label: genome announcement section
Defs: A document part announcing the publication of a novel draft genome sequence.

label: abdominal laterotergite 3
Defs: The laterotergite that is located on abdominal tergum 3.

label: clava
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of apical flagellomeres bearing multiporous plates in female organism.

label: attachment quality
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having connection or association with another entity.

label: centrally registered identifier
Defs: An information content entity that consists of a CRID symbol and additional information about the CRID registry to which it belongs.

label: twelfth flagellomere
Defs: The flagellomere that is located immediately distal to the eleventh flagellomere.

label: apical clavomere ventral pit
Defs: The depression accommodates the sensilla that is located ventrally on the  apical flagellomere.

label: sense organ
Defs: Multicellular anatomical structure with largely bona fide boundary that transduces some sensory stimulus to the nervous system.

label: generalized
Defs: Affecting all regions without specificity of distribution.

label: sufficiency
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer has enough functionality.

label: polymeric
Defs: A quality inhering in a structure by virtue of it consisting of many of repeated, similar or identical subunits, arranged in some orderly array.

label: protruding
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s extending out above or beyond a surface or boundary.

label: S7-first valvula muscle
Defs: The muscle that originates from the abdominal sternum 7 and inserts on the first valvula.

label: prepectus
Defs: The intersegmentalia that is located on the mesopectus-pronotum intersegmental membrane and corresponds to the site of origin of the anterior thoracic spiracle occlusor muscle.

label: gonomacula
Defs: The conjunctiva that is located at the distal apex of the harpe.

label: full-spectrum EM radiation quality
Defs: An EM radiation quality that is independent of the EM wavelength range.

label: mandibular gland
Defs: The gland that opens mesally at the base of the mandible.

label: posterior tentorio-stipital muscle
Defs: The tentorio-stipital muscle that is posterior to the anterior tentorio-stipital muscle.

label: gigantic
Defs: A size quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being many folds greater relative to the normal average.

label: telotarsus
Defs: The tarsomere that is apical.

label: bridge ontology module
Defs: An ontology module that consists entirely of axioms that connect or bridge two distinct ontology modules. For example, the Uberon-to-ZFA bridge module.

label: written name
Defs: A textual entity that denotes a particular in reality.

label: signum
Defs: The area that corresponds to the site of the origin of a muscle.

label: semi erect
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being partially upright in position or posture.

label: extraembryonic structure
Defs: Anatomical structure that is contiguous with the embryo and is comprised of portions of tissue or cells that will not contribute to the embryo.

label: wholly dorsalized
Defs: A dorsalized quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s gross morphology containing only what are normally dorsal structures.

label: profurcal bridge
Defs: The area that connects distally the lateral profurcal arms.

label: prestigma
Defs: The patch that is enlarged, sclerotized, and located at the apex of one or more wing veins on the anterior margin of the wing.

label: peripheral
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being at the edge or boundary of a related entity.

label: costal cell
Defs: The membranous region of the forewing anterior to the submarginal vein, measured from the basal constriction that delimits the apex of the humeral plate of the wing to the point at which the submarginal vein touches the leading edge of the wing.

label: axillular groove
Defs: The axillular line that is an impression.

label: occipital margin
Defs: The edge that separates the occiput from the vertex.

label: right
Defs: A directional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s direction that is similar to the direction of an object to the north when it faces west.

label: campaniform sensillum of the glossa
Defs: The campaniform sensillum of the anterior surface of the glossa that is located proximal to the glossal annuli.

label: increased elevation
Defs: An elevation which is relatively high.

label: intercardinal area
Defs: The area that is located between the cardines and limited proximally and distally by the anatomical line that extends between the proximal and distal ends of the left and right cardines.

label: lateral gonostyle/volsella complex-penisvalval muscle
Defs: The gonostyle/volsella complex-penisvalval muscle that arises anterolaterally of the site of origin of the distodorsal gonostyle/volsella complex-penisvalval muscle and inserts laterally on the penisvalva.

label: squircle
Defs: A shape with properties between those of a square and those of a circle.

label: pleural suture
Defs: The sulcus that corresponds to the pleural ridge and separates the episternum from the epimeron.

label: research participants section
Defs: A document part that describes human subject(s) that participated in a study (e.g. inclusion & exclusion criteria, recruitment methods, reasons for non-participation, grouping and randomisation, methods of follow-up, etc.).

label: olistheter
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the rhachis of the second valvula and the aulax of the first valvula.

label: fasciculation
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer forms a bundle of anatomical fibers, as of muscle or nerve.

label: medial coxal articular process of the mesopectus
Defs: The articular process that is located on the ventral margin of the mesopectus medially of the mesocoxal foramen and bears the medial coxal condyle of the mesopectus.

label: cardinal articular condyle of the cranium
Defs: The condyle that is located on the cranium and articulates with the cranial fossa of the cardo.

label: obsolete2_text based digital entity
Defs: A text based digital entity is a digital entity that is encoded so that it only contains text characters.

label: protruding into
Defs: A quality inhering into a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s extending out above or beyond its surface or boundary into the surface or boundary of another entity.

label: postocular area
Defs: The area of the cranium between the dorsal margin of the compound eye and the posterolateral cranial corner.

label: lateral mesofurco-metafurcal muscle
Defs: The mesofurco-metafurcal muscle that inserts on the anterior metafurcal arm.

label: ovate
Defs: A spheroid quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting a continuous convex surface with an axis of symmetry and one axis longer than the other; egg-shaped.

label: arrhythmic
Defs: A rhythm quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking rhythm.

label: mobile relative to
Defs: Mobility relative to a second entity.

label: muscle
Defs: The portion of tissue that is composed of contractile fibers.

label: increased sensitivity of a process
Defs: A sensitivity of a process which is higher than normal or average.

label: anterior trochanteral articular process of the metacoxa
Defs: The articular process that is located anteriorly on the distal margin of the metacoxa and bears the anterior trochanteral condyle of the metacoxa.

label: fourth tarsomere of hind leg
Defs: The tarsomere that is distal to and connected to the third tarsomere of the hind leg.

label: back
Defs: A directional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s direction that is similar to the direction of an object to the north when it faces south.

label: width of 1st flagellomere
Defs: The width of the 1st flagellomere.

label: basitarsal notch
Defs: The notch that is located proximally on the median surface of the probasitarsus.

label: normal cellular motility
Defs: A cellular motility which is normal or average.

label: transverse frontal carina
Defs: The transverse carina that is dorsal to the facial pit and ventral to the anterior ocellus.

label: color saturation
Defs: A scalar chromatic property that is the degree of purity of perceived light.

label: gonostipo-volsellal muscle
Defs: The male genitalia muscle that arises proximally from the ventral part of the gonostipes and inserts on the volsella at the border between the gono- and parossiculi.

label: phosphorescence
Defs: A fluorescence in which the emittence continues after the absorption has ceased.

label: 3-D shape
Defs: A shape that inheres in a 3 dimensional entity.

label: antero-lateral margin
Defs: Anatomical margin that is located on the antero-lateral region of the body or body part.

label: dilator muscle of the 7th abdominal spiracle
Defs: The spiracular muscle that arises from the lateral sternal apodeme of the abdominal sternum 7 and inserts on the 7th abdominal spiracle.

label: cellular spatiotemporal quality
Defs: A spatiotemporal quality inhering in a cell.

label: valvura
Defs: The area that is located proximally of the ergot on the penisvalva.

label: supraalar area
Defs: The area that is located laterally of the longitudinal metanotal carina.

label: acropleural apodeme
Defs: The apodeme that is located anterodorsally on the mesopleuron and corresponds to the site of origin of the third mesopleuro-mesonotal muscle.

label: metasoma
Defs: The tagma that is connected anteriorly to the metapectal-propodeal complex at the propodeal foramen and consists of abdominal segments.

label: brown green
Defs: A color consisting of brown and green hues.

label: sternal apodeme
Defs: The apodeme that is located on the abdominal sternite and serves as the site of origin of muscles.

label: lateroventral mesopleural carina
Defs: The carina that extends lateroventrally on the mesopleuron between the lateral end of the epicnemium and the lateral margin of the mesocoxal foramen.

label: dense
Defs: A physical quality which inheres in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting density.

label: mesopecto-mesocoxal joint
Defs: The dicondylic joint that is composed of the mesopectus and the mesocoxa.

label: increased virulence
Defs: A virulence that is relatively high.

label: proximomedial stipital flange
Defs: The medial part of the principal carina of the stipes that is overlapped distally by the distomedial stipital carina and overlaps the lateral premental face and the proximal part of the prementum.

label: median pronoto-prophragmal muscle
Defs: The prophragmal muscle that arises medially of the site of origin of the lateral pronoto-prophragmal muscle.

label: Y-shaped
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being shaped in the form of the letter Y.

label: saturated cyan
Defs: A color consisting of cyan colour and high saturation.

label: anterior metapleural carina
Defs: The carina that is parallel to and extends anteroventrally of the metapleural carina, is continuous with the metapleural apodeme and is separated from the metapleural carina by a crenulate impresion

label: unstructured
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking distinct structure.

label: postoccipital sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that is located on the postoccipital suture.

label: laterally compressed
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being flattened along transverse axis.

label: report
Defs: A document assembled by an author for the purpose of providing information for the audience. A report is the output of a documenting process and has the objective to be consumed by a specific audience. Topic of the report is on something that has completed. A report is not a single figure. Examples of reports are journal article, patent application, grant progress report, case report (not patient record).

label: genal space
Defs: The area that is located between the genal carina and the posterior margin of the compound eye, bounded ventrally by the malar sulcus and dorsally by the vertex.

label: abdominal sternum 5
Defs: The abdominal sternum that is located on abdominal segment 5.

label: dorsolateral setal patch of propodeum
Defs: The setal patch that is elongate, is adjacent and extends just lateral to the plica and is composed of posteriorly directed and apressed setae that inserts into the retinaculum when the fore wing is in a flexed position.

label: egg canal
Defs: The anatomical space that is between the left and right olistheters.

label: lumenized
Defs: A structure quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a three dimensional space surrounded by one or more anatomical structures and containing one or more anatomical substances.

label: paleopolyploid
Defs: A polyploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having an ancient polyploid ancestor.

label: anterior protibio-probasitarsal muscle
Defs: The intrinsic leg muscle that arises anteriorly from the protibia and inserts on the anterior proximal process of the probasitarsus.

label: abbreviations section
Defs: A part of a document where abbreviations and their long-forms used within the document are listed.

label: postero-medial region
Defs: Anatomical region that overlaps the posterior and medial regions of the body or body part.

label: tergum
Defs: The area that is located on the integument and is dorsal of the ventral diaphragm.

label: pentagonal
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having five angles and five sides.

label: anterolateral mesoscutal corner
Defs: The corner that is located anterolaterally on the mesoscutum and is adjacent to the dorsal pronotal corner.

label: increased curvature
Defs: A curvature which is relatively high.

label: clava
Defs: The anatomical cluster composed of the apical flagellomeres that are differentiated by size from the basal flagellomeres.

label: normal radioactivity
Defs: A radioactivity which is relatively normal or average

label: pubescent
Defs: A maturity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having arrived at the onset of puberty (the age at which sex glands become functional) but not yet fully mature.

label: median frontal septum
Defs: The ridge that is unpaired, vertical, is located in the dorsoventral midline of the frons and corresponds to the site of origin of the posterior fronto-labral muscles.

label: material information bearer
Defs: A material entity in which a concretization of an information content entity inheres.

label: odor
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s molecules being are aerially dispersed and perceived by an odorant receptor.

label: work
Defs: A physical quality which is equal to the energy transferred by a force to a moving object.

label: prescutal ridge
Defs: The ridge that seperates the prescutum from scutum.

label: introduction to a publication about an investigation
Defs: A part of a publication about an investigation that is about the objective specification (why the investigation is being done)

label: metaplastic
Defs: A cellular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of having changed from one fully differentiated state into another.

label: lateral metapleuro-metabasalar muscle
Defs: The metapleuro-metabasalar muscle that arises from the metabasalar apodeme.

label: posterior proximal process of the metabasitarsus
Defs: The process that is located posteriorly on the proximal margin of the metabasitarsus and corresponds to the site of insertion of the posterior metatibio-metabasitarsal muscle.

label: quality of a gas
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting the physical characteristics of an entity consisting of particles that have neither a defined volume nor defined shape.

label: median propodeal carina
Defs: The carina that is oriented anteroposteriorly and is located medially on the propodeum.

label: dorsalized
Defs: A malformed quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s gross morphology containing what are normally dorsal structures and missing some or all of what are normally ventral structures.

label: increased elevation relative to
Defs: An elevation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue the bearer\'s being in a high position relative to another entity.

label: interdigitated
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s parts or projections being interlocked; for example, the fingers of two hands that are clasped.

label: obsolete increased consumption
Defs: A consumption which is relatively high.

label: cordate apodeme
Defs: The apodeme on the anterior margin of female T9. The ventral T9-second valvifer muscle attaches partly on the apodeme.

label: wavelength
Defs: A physical quality which is equal to the distance between repeating units of a wave pattern.

label: protibio-probasitarsal articulation
Defs: The articulation that is composed of the basitarsal fossa of the protibia and the tibial condyle of the probasitarsus.

label: detached from
Defs: An attachment quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking connection or association with another entity.

label: monosomy
Defs: An aneuploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing only one chromosome from a pair in a cell\'s nucleus.

label: increased affinity
Defs: An affinity which is relatively high.

label: lacinial lobe
Defs: The lobe that extends proximally on the distal margin of the medial stipital wall, is adjacent to the basal lacinial sclerite, overlaps the proximal part of the galea.

label: solid configuration
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s parts having the arrangement which exhibits characteristics of solids.

label: cicatricial
Defs: Having or resembling the characteristic of a cicatrix - a scar resulting from formation and contraction of fibrous tissue.

label: orientation
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s placement which is defined by the angle between the bearer and an axis, or the angle between the bearer and another object.

label: active
Defs: A quality of an physical object that is currently realizing one of its functions.

label: table
Defs: A textual entity that contains a two-dimensional arrangement of texts repeated at regular intervals across a spatial range, such that the spatial relationships among the constituent texts expresses propositions

label: second axillary sclerite
Defs: The axillary sclerite that articulates ventrally with the pleuron and medially with the first axillary sclerite, posteriorly with the third axillary sclerite and is connected with the base of the radial vein.

label: increased porosity
Defs: An increase in porosity.

label: deformed
Defs: A morphological quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being distorted in form.

label: anterolateral metapleuro-metanotal muscle
Defs: The lateral metapleuro-metanotal muscle that arises anterolaterally from the metapectus.

label: abdominal tergite 9
Defs: The tergite that is located on the abdominal segment 9

label: tables section
Defs: A part of a document that contains one or more tables.

label: first valvifer
Defs: The area of the first valvifer-first valvula complex that is proximal to the aulax, bears the ninth tergal condyle of the first valvifer and the second valviferal condyle of the first valvifer and is connected to the genital membrane by muscle.

label: obsolete2_binary digital entity
Defs: A binary digital entity is a digital entity that is encoded in a way that is not easily human readable and that contains other than text characters.

label: laterophragma
Defs: The apodeme that is located laterally on the postnotum.

label: black
Defs: A color that lacks any hues as parts.

label: anterior lacinial fimbriae
Defs: The row of setae that traverses the lacinia along its anterior margin.

label: basalare
Defs: The sclerite that is located on the dorsal margin of the pectus of pterothoracic segment anteriorly of the pleural wing articulation.

label: normal acidity
Defs: An acidity which is relatively normal.

label: stipital thickening
Defs: The rim that extends along the anterior (dorsal) margin of the medial stipital wall.

label: age
Defs: A time quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of how long the bearer has existed.

label: segment
Defs: An anatomical structure that is metameric and is connected to other metameric subdivisions by muscles and is delimited by its sclerites.

label: axillar crescent
Defs: The anatomical cluster composed of the transaxillar carina, axillar carina, and axillular carina.

label: normal occurrence
Defs: An occurrence which is relatively normal.

label: collagenous
Defs: A composition quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s consisting of collagen.

label: discrimen
Defs: The sulcus that corresponds with the discrimenal lamella.

label: fiber shaped
Defs: A convex 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting a by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting a consistently sized and approximately round cross-section along its length, which is many times larger than its diameter.

label: dorsal sclerite of the first valvifer
Defs: The sclerite of the first valvifer that is located dorsally of the transvalviferal conjunctiva.

label: tapered
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being gradually narrower or thinner toward one end.

label: proximal gonostipo-parossiculal muscle
Defs: The gonostyle-parossiculal muscle that arises proximally from the lateral part of the gonostipes and inserts on the proximal part of the parossiculus.

label: propleural arm-postoccipital muscle
Defs: The postoccipital muscle that arises from the propleural arm.

label: sinuous
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having many curves and turns.

label: decreased height
Defs: A height which is relatively low.

label: laterosternite 8
Defs: The laterosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 8.

label: anterior tentorial pit
Defs: The tentorial pit that corresponds to the anterior end of the tentorium and partially delimits the clypeus.

label: amplitude
Defs: A physical quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the size of the bearer\'s maximum displacement from the \'normal\' position, when periodic motion is taking place.

label: minimum spine distance
Defs: The shortest anatomical line between the lateral margins of the propodeal spines.

label: obsolete surface shape
Defs: A shape that inheres in a part of a surface. An object can have different surface shapes on different parts of its surface.

label: radiating
Defs: Shape quality inhering in a bearer expanding outward, or having parts expanding outward, from a center point.

label: frons
Defs: The area that is between the epistomal line and the anterior ocellus and limited laterally by the inner margin of compound eye.

label: falciform
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having the shape of a scythe or sickle.

label: proximal margin
Defs: Anatomical margin that is located on the proximal region of the body or body part.

label: dark cyan
Defs: A color consisting of cyan hue and low brightness.

label: increased pigmentation
Defs: A degree of pigmentation quality that is relatively high.

label: organism subdivision
Defs: Anatomical structure which is a primary subdivision of whole organism. The mereological sum of these is the whole organism.

label: clypeo-compound eye distance
Defs: The distance that is the shortest between the compound eye and the anterior tentorial pit and the compound eye.

label: tentorio-antennal muscle
Defs: The muscle that arises from the dorsal surface of the anterior broadened part of the anterior tentorial arm and inserts on the scape.

label: occlusor of the propodeal spiracle muscle
Defs: The first abdominal tergal spiracle muscle that extends between the dorsal and ventral spiracular apodemes.

label: mediosternite 2
Defs: The mediosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 2.

label: degenerate
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer whose structure deteriorates or is lost over time due to an active pathological process.

label: longitudinal line of the dorsal profurcal lamella
Defs: The line that crosses the dorsal profurcal lamella and corresponds to the site of origin of the anterior profurcal lamella.

label: accelerated growth
Defs: A peramorphic growth quality which is due to an increased rate.

label: mislocalized abaxially
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being positioned away from the axis of an organism.

label: profurcasternum
Defs: The furcasternum that is located in the prothorax.

label: gonad
Defs: The compound organ that makes gametes.

label: light red brown
Defs: A color consisting of red and brown hue and high brightness.

label: mesopectus-pronotum intersegmental membrane
Defs: The intersegmental membrane that is located between the mesopectus and the pronotum.

label: unilaminar epithelium
Defs: Epithelium that consists of a single layer of epithelial cells.

label: remigium
Defs: The area that is located anterior to the claval furrow.

label: lateral T8-T9 muscle
Defs: The ninth abdominal tergal muscle that arises from the anterolateral margin of female T8 and inserts on the anterolateral margin of female T9.

label: distensible
Defs: A structure quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being capable of swelling or stretching.

label: uncus
Defs: The abscissa that extends anteriorly from the stigmal vein.

label: necessary (continuant)
Defs: A necessity quality (continuant) inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being essential or indispensable.

label: data transformation
Defs: A planned process that produces output data from input data.

label: abdominal mediotergite 9
Defs: The mediotergite that is located on abdominal tergum 9.

label: lateral panel of pronotum
Defs: The area that is concave and is located ventrally of the level of the anterior thoracic spiracle.

label: metapleuro-metanotal muscle
Defs: The metanotal muscle that arises from the metapleuron and inserts on the metanotum.

label: edge
Defs: The margin that extends along the border of two areas that are oriented differently.

label: apical glossal hairs
Defs: The row of spines that is on the distal glossal edge.

label: mediosternite
Defs: The sternite that is located medially on an abdominal sternum.

label: obsolescence reason specification
Defs: The reason for which a term has been deprecated. The allowed values come from an enumerated list of predefined terms. See the specification of these instances for more detailed definitions of each enumerated value.

label: flavourless
Defs: A flavor quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking flavour.

label: lateral pectal fossa of the procoxa
Defs: The lateral pectal fossa of the coxa that is located laterally on the probasicoxite and accommodates the lateral coxal condyle of the propleuron.

label: non-glutinous
Defs: An amylose composition quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having high amount of amylose content.

label: laterosternite 9
Defs: The laterosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 9.

label: normal fatigability
Defs: A fatigability which is relatively normal or average

label: mesodiscrimen
Defs: The discrimen that is located in the mesothorax and corresponds with the mesodiscrimenal lamella.

label: dry
Defs: A wetness quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s not being covered by a liquid.

label: proximolateral apodeme of cupula
Defs: The apodeme that is located laterally on the proximal margin of the cupula and corresponds to the site of insertion of the second lateral 9th sterno-cupulal muscle.

label: dorsal metapleuro-third axillary sclerite of hind wing muscle
Defs: The metapleuro-third axillary sclerite of hind wing muscle that arises dorsolaterally from the mesopleuron dorsally of the vantral metapleuro-third axillary sclerite of hind wing muscle.

label: lethal (sensu genetics)
Defs: A viability quality inhering in a population by virtue of the bearer\'s long term survival inability.

label: pluripotent
Defs: A cellular potency that is the capacity to produce differentiated cell types of all three primary germ layers but not extraembryonic cell types.

label: postgenal pit
Defs: The pit that corresponds to the ventral-most point of the posterior site of fusion of the ventral lamella of the tentorium.

label: radial plane
Defs: Anatomical plane that follows the two dimensions specified by an apical-basal axis relative to direction of growth and a medial-lateral axis.

label: dendritic
Defs: A branched quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having smaller branches arising from larger branches. Resembling a tree in branching structure.

label: mesosternum
Defs: The eusternum that is located in the mesothorax.

label: lateral mesopleuro-mesocoxal articulation
Defs: The articulation that is composed of the lateral coxal condyle of the mesopleuron and the lateral pectal fossa of the mesocoxa.

label: proximodorsal notch of cupula
Defs: The notch that is medially on the proximodorsal margin of the cupula and is delimited laterally by the site of origins of the dorsomedial cupulo-gonostipal muscles.

label: tricuspidate
Defs: A cuscpidate quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer possessing three cusps.

label: anterior ridge of T9
Defs: The ridge that extends along the anterior margin of female T9 and receives the site of origin of the ventral and the dorsal T9-second valvifer muscles.

label: electric polarizability
Defs: The ease of distortion of the electron cloud of a molecular entity by an electric field.

label: miscibility
Defs: A quality of a liquid inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s ability to mix with (dissolve in) another liquid.

label: parasagittal orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is in the parasagittal plane.

label: obsolete relaxational quality
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in an inactive muscle or muscle fibers by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting gradual lengthening.

label: alternate placement
Defs: A pattern quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being placed alternately one above the other.

label: paracoxal sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that corresponds to the paracoxal ridge.

label: first mesopleuro-mesonotal muscle
Defs: The mesonotal muscle that arises ventrally from the mesopectus and inserts on the mesoscutum laterally of the notauli and medially of the parascutal carina.

label: proboscidial fossa
Defs: The scrobe that is located medially on the hypostoma and accommodates the proboscis.

label: posterior pronotal inflection
Defs: The inflection that extends along the posterior margin of the pronotum and articulates with the anterior mesopleural inflection.

label: tibial flexor muscle
Defs: The intrinsic leg muscle that arises medially (ventrally) of the femur and inserts on the genuflexor plate.

label: coiling
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being wound in a continuous series of loops.

label: decreased cellular motility
Defs: A cellular motility which is lower relative to the normal or average.

label: Postal delivery route
Defs: A plan specification that if realized, is realized by the delivery of mail to some facility or mailbox within some geographical region.

label: valviceps
Defs: The area that is the distal part of the penisvalva dorsally of the ergot.

label: acrosternite 6
Defs: The acrosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 6.

label: decreased object quality
Defs: A quality of an object that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.

label: mesopleural ridge
Defs: The pleural ridge that marks the ventral margin of the site of origin of the second mesopleuro-mesonotal and the dorsal margin of the mesopleuro-mesocoxal muscles and is located anteroventrally of the speculum.

label: anatomical side
Defs: An anatomical region bounded by a plane perpendicular to an axis through the middle.

label: obsolete unknown sex
Defs: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual whose sex is unknown.

label: anterior notal wing process
Defs: The fossa that is located posterolaterally on the preaxilla and articulates with the anterior condyle of the first axillary sclerite of the fore wing.

label: alinotum
Defs: The notum that is connected to the wings.

label: maximum diameter of the compound eye
Defs: The longest diameter of the eye.

label: scalar measurement datum
Defs: A scalar measurement datum is a measurement datum that is composed of two parts, numerals and a unit label.

label: metabasicoxite
Defs: The basicoxite that is located on the metacoxa.

label: metabasalare
Defs: The basalare that is located in the metathorax.

label: remittent intensity
Defs: An intensity which is characterized by temporary abatement in severity.

label: anterior margin
Defs: Anatomical margin that is located on the anterior side of a body or body part.

label: pronotal projection
Defs: The projection that is part of the pronotum.

label: bang sensitive
Defs: A behavioral quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting paralytic behaviour when subjected to mechanical shock.

label: broken
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s components no longer being in a single contiguous unit.

label: curved
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having or being marked by a curve or smoothly rounded bend.

label: polyploid
Defs: A ploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing more than two homologous sets of chromosomes.

label: anterior procoxo-protrochanteral articulation
Defs: The articulation that is composed of the anterior trochanteral condyle of the procoxa and the anterior coxal fossa of the protrochanter.

label: version number
Defs: A version number is an information content entity which is a sequence of characters borne by part of each of a class of manufactured products or its packaging and indicates its order within a set of other products having the same name.

label: disposition
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s prevailing tendency, mood, or inclination.

label: retractor of the epipharynx
Defs: The epipharyngeal muscle that arises from the clypeus and inserts on the epipharyngeal wall.

label: decreased variability of rate
Defs: A variability of rate which is relatively low.

label: axillular carina
Defs: The axillular line that is a carina.

label: paraglossal acroglossal button
Defs: The sclerite that is located distally on the paraglossa.

label: rhomboid
Defs: A spheroid quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being oval and a little angular in the middle.

label: fifth tarsomere
Defs: The tarsomere that is distal to the fourth tarsomere.

label: columnar
Defs: A shape inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being elongated and cylindrical.

label: bilateral
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having two sides; two-sided.

label: fourth sclerite of the maxillary palp
Defs: The sclerite that is ringlike and is connected distally to the third sclerite of the maxillary palp via conjunctiva.

label: atrium
Defs: The cuticular invagination that is sclerotized and is between the external aperture of the spiracle and the distal end of the trachea.

label: spina
Defs: The apophysis that is located medially on the spinasternum.

label: genal patch
Defs: The setiferous patch that is located on the gena.

label: saturated red
Defs: A color consisting of red hue and high saturation.

label: medial vein
Defs: The wing vein that is posterior to the radial vein and is connected to the anterior margin of the anterior median plate.

label: periepistomal striation
Defs: The anatomical cluster that composed of carinae radiating from the pleurostomal condyle.

label: eosinophilic
Defs: An affinity inhering in a tissue constituent by virtue of the bearer exhibiting a molecular interaction for eosin dye.

label: proximodistal anatomical line
Defs: The anatomical line that extends between the proximal and distal margins of an anatomical structure.

label: wholly posterioralized
Defs: A posterioralized quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s gross morphology containing only what are normally posterior structures.

label: lobed
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being partly divided into a determinate number of regions.

label: originates from
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of some aspect of that bearer beginning from a position on another entity.

label: medial pectal fossa of the coxa
Defs: The pectal fossa of the coxa that accommodates the median coxal condyle of the pleuron.

label: metepisternal depression
Defs: The scrobe that is located anteroventrally on the mesopectus and accommodates the mesocoxa.

label: Waterston's evaporatorium
Defs: The evaporatorium that is located medially on the acrotergite of abdominal tergite 7.

label: cup-shaped apodeme of metabasalare
Defs: The apodeme that is cup shaped and recieves the site of insertion of the metabasalar muscles.

label: arachnose
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being characterized by fine, entangled hairs giving the appearance of cobweb.

label: lateral profemoro-protibial muscle
Defs: The intrinsic leg muscle that arises laterally (dorsally)  from the profemur and inserts laterally (dorsally) on the dorsal process of the protibia.

label: patients section
Defs: A part of a document about the patients that participated in a study.

label: graph
Defs: A diagram that presents one or more tuples of information by mapping those tuples in to a two dimensional space in a non arbitrary way.

label: neonatal
Defs: A maturity quality inhering to a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being at the point or short after birth.

label: abdominal segment 4
Defs: The abdominal segment that is located between abdominal segment 3 and abdominal segment 5.

label: metasomal spiracle
Defs: The spiracle that is located on the metasoma.

label: limaciform
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s resembling a slug.

label: striate-angular
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being marked by narrow lines, usually parallel, with at least one salient angle on the margin

label: 6th abdominal spiracle
Defs: The abdominal spiracle that is located in the abdominal segment 6.

label: arcus
Defs: The sclerite that encircles ventrolaterally the proximal part of the arolium.

label: lateral suspensor of the mouth
Defs: The hypopharyngeal muscle that arises from the distal end of the anterior tentorial arm or from the inner surface of the head capsule and inserts on the lateral surface of the proximolateral processes of the sitophore.

label: third tarsomere of hind leg
Defs: The tarsomere that is distal to and connected to the second tarsomere of the hind leg.

label: having extra processual parts
Defs: A quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having additional processual parts.

label: third axillary sclerite of the hind wing
Defs: The third axillary sclerite that is located on the metathorax.

label: acantha
Defs: The process that corresponds to a single epidermal cell.

label: inferior pronotal spine
Defs: The spine that is located laterally on the anterior margin of the pronotum.

label: horizontal plate
Defs: The flange that extends dorsolaterally from the mesodiscrimenal lamella.

label: radiation absorbed dose
Defs: A radiation exposure quality inhering in a substance by virtue of the radiation energy "deposited" in a kilogram of a substance.

label: amount
Defs: The number of entities of this type that are part of the whole organism.

label: symmetry
Defs: A pattern quality of inhering in a bearer by virtue of the correspondence in size, shape, and relative position of the bearer\'s parts on opposite sides of a dividing line or median plane or about a center or axis.

label: posterolateral mesoscutellar area
Defs: The area delimited by the posterolateral mesoscutellar carina and the ventral margin of the mesoscutellum

label: fringed
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having an ornamental border consisting of short straight or twisted threads or strips hanging from cut or raveled edges or from a separate band.

label: second valvifer-genital membrane muscle
Defs: The ovipositor muscle that arises anteriorly from the dorsal flange of the second valvifer and inserts anteriorly on the dorsal part of the genital membrane.

label: pleurostomal ridge
Defs: The ridge that extends between the pleurostomal fossa and pleurostomal condyle and delimits the lateral margin of the pleurostoma.

label: mesotibia
Defs: The tibia that is located on the mid leg.

label: edible
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being suitable for use as food.

label: metepimeron
Defs: The depression that is concave and is located at the anterior end of the metapleural sulcus.

label: pronotal ridge
Defs: The carina that delimits the pronotal plate posterolaterally.

label: mono-colored
Defs: A color pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having one hue.

label: mesepimeral inflection
Defs: The inflection that extends along the dorsal margin of the mesopectus.

label: fatigability
Defs: A strength quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to lose strength.

label: external area of the scape
Defs: The area of the scape that faces away from the cranial surface in fully caudal scape position.

label: cell projection
Defs: A prolongation or process extending from a cell, e.g. a flagellum or axon.

label: fore wing vein
Defs: The wing vein that is on the fore wing.

label: prototrophic
Defs: A nutritional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s ability to synthesize a particular organic compound required for its growth.

label: disease
Defs: A disposition (i) to undergo pathological processes that (ii) exists in an organism because of one or more disorders in that organism.

label: conspicuousness
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of its visibility.

label: mesotarsal pegs
Defs: The row of spurs that extends laterally along the tarsomere of the mesotarsus.

label: third mesopleuro-third axillary sclerite of fore wing muscle
Defs: The fore wing third axillary muscle that originates posterolaterally from the mesopleuron.

label: degree of pigmentation
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having or lacking of substances produced by living organisms that have a color resulting from selective color absorption.

label: density plot
Defs: A density plot is a report graph which is a graphical representation of data where the tint of a particular pixel corresponds to some kind of function corresponding the the amount of data points relativelly with their distance from the the pixel.

label: hermaphroditic organism
