Defs: Multi-cellular organism that can produce both male and female gametes.

label: temporal distribution quality
Defs: A temporal distribution pattern of process occurrences within a regulation/reference process.

label: intrinsic muscle of the 9th sternum
Defs: The sternal muscle that connects the lateral margins of the abdominal tergum 9 and extends internally of the external male genitalia.

label: subspherical
Defs: A spheroid shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being nearly, but not perfectly, spherical.

label: radio-medial cross vein
Defs: The wing vein that connects the radial vein with the medial vein.

label: metapleural apodeme
Defs: The pleural apodeme that is connected with the metafurca.

label: abdominal tergum
Defs: The tergum that is located in the abdomen.

label: decreased weight
Defs: A weight which is relatively low.

label: syntergal translucent patch
Defs: The translucent patch that is located submedially on the syntergum.

label: apical row of spines
Defs: The row of spurs that is located on the internal margin of the calcar distally of the velum.

label: keratinous
Defs: A composition quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s consisting of keratin.

label: mesonoto-metanoto-mesopecto-metapecto-propodeal complex
Defs: The sclerite that is connected to the pronotum, propleura, fore, middle and hind legs and the petiole via conjunctiva.

label: posterior mesepimeral inflection
Defs: The inflection that extends along the posterior margin of the mesepimeron, posteriorly of the subalar pit to the coxal articulation.

label: banding pattern
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the strongly sclerotised areas corresponding with the annuli and less strongly sclerotised areas situated between them.

label: posterior lobe of scutellum
Defs: The part of the mesoscutellum that protrudes posteriorly as a distinct shape beyond any smooth or straight posterior outline, especially when protruding posteriorly past the anterior margin of the metanotum

label: normal diameter
Defs: A diameter which is relatively normal or average

label: fasciculated
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s forming a bundle of aligned anatomical fibers, as of muscle or nerve.

label: well differentiated
Defs: A cellular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of its having most of the cellular characteristics of the tissue of origin.

label: light yellow brown
Defs: A color consisting of yellow and brown hue and high brightness.

label: intertarsomeral joint
Defs: The monocondylic joint that is composed of two tarsomeres.

label: up
Defs: A directional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s direction from a lower to a higher point.

label: mechanosensory hair
Defs: The aporous sensillum that has a hairlike cuticular component.

label: sparse
Defs: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being scattered; spread irregularly, and at a distance from each other.

label: coxal corium
Defs: The conjunctiva that connects the coxa to the pectus.

label: insoluble in
Defs: A solubility quality inhering in a substance by virtue of the bearer\'s inability of a substance to dissolve in a liquid.

label: impermeable
Defs: A permeability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being incapable of being permeated or pervaded by a gas or liquid (as by osmosis or diffusion).

label: male genitalia muscle
Defs: The abdominal muscle that inserts on the male genitalia.

label: proximal-distal axis
Defs: An axis that extends from the point of attachment of a structure (proximal) to the  point furthest away from the plane of attachment (distal).

label: whorled
Defs: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being in opposition round a common axis.

label: template generated ontology module
Defs: An ontology module that is automatically generated from a template specification and fillers for slots in that template.

label: vaporizability
Defs: A quality which inheres in a substance by virtue of the ease with which the substance can be changed into a gaseous state.

label: ventral invagination of the metapleural carina
Defs: The invagination that is at the ventral end of the of the metapleural carina.

label: mesospinasterno-metafurcal muscle
Defs: The metafurcal muscle that arises from the mesospinasternum and inserts on the metafurca.

label: haplodiploid
Defs: A diploidy quality inhering in a bearer in by virtue of belonging in a species whose one of the sexes has haploid cells and the other has diploid cells.

label: increased photosensitivity
Defs: A photosensitivity which is relatively high.

label: pre-publication history section
Defs: A part of the document about the publication history of a document. This section typically details dates of document submission to a journal and dates of any re-submissions as well as reviewer comments and responses to reviewers by the authors.

label: mesotibio-pretarsus of mesotarsus muscle
Defs: The flexor of the pretarsal claws of the middle leg muscle that arises from the mesotibia.

label: closed
Defs: A morphological quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s affording blocked passage or view.

label: contractility
Defs: A physical quality that is the ability to contract or shrink.

label: shattered
Defs: A broken quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being broken into multiple contiguous wholes.

label: interstipital sclerite
Defs: The sclerite that is located on the interstipital area and is connected to the prementum via conjunctiva.

label: uncoordinated
Defs: A coordination quality of inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking skillful and effective interaction of movement.

label: variability of shape
Defs: A variability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer exhibits shape variation or change.

label: laterodistal cardinal ridge
Defs: The cardinal ridge that arises distally from the basal cardinal ridge and is oriented distolaterally.

label: shortened
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s length being notably lower than its width.

label: lateral pronotal area
Defs: The area of the pronotum that is lateral and delimited medially by the epomial carina.

label: alutaceous
Defs: The reticulate that is composed of flat scutes.

label: area
Defs: The anatomical structure of the cuticle that is delimited by material or immaterial anatomical entities.

label: setting datum
Defs: A settings datum is a datum that denotes some configuration of an instrument.

label: torular head width
Defs: The anatomical line between the intersections of the cranium contour and transverse torular line line in frontal view. dorsal head width

label: maxillar muscle
Defs: The head muscle that inserts on the maxilla.

label: hairy ring of the metasoma
Defs: The setiferous patch that extends along the second metasomal tergum.

label: stepped
Defs: Having a shape or form that resembles a step of a stairway (e.g., a ledge or offset margin).

label: primary gonopore
Defs: The anatomical space that is the transition from the ductus ejaculatorius to the endophallus and therefore the transition from the internal to the external male genitalia.

label: postorbital carina
Defs: The carina that extends posteriorly from the genal sulcus.

label: condensed
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being thicker or more closely packed together; pressed tightly together.

label: spayed female
Defs: Female quality of being incapable to reproduce because of functional loss of the ovaries and/or uterus from surgical removal.

label: nucha
Defs: The area that is raised and surrounds the propodeal foramen.

label: increased accumulation
Defs: An increased number of physical objects that are accumulated within another physical object usually as a result of a failure to break down or remove objects in a timely manner.

label: apical tooth of mandible
Defs: The tooth that is located apically on the external margin of the mandible.

label: length of hypopygium
Defs: The median anatomical line of the hypopygium in ventral view.

label: cardo
Defs: The sclerite that is articulated with the cranium at the cranio-cardinal articulation, is connected to the stipes distolaterally via the stipitocardinal hinge and receives the site of attachment of the occipito-cardinal muscle.

label: projection
Defs: The process that is located on an edge.

label: splayed dorsal
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curved outwards from the back or upper surface of an organism.

label: carpel-like
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s similarity to the appearance of a carpel.

label: subligular process
Defs: The area of the prementum that is located between the labial palpal excisions and is limited posteriorly by the anatomical line extending between the proximalmost points of the excisions.

label: acropleuron
Defs: The area that corresponds with the site of origin of the third mesopleuro-mesonotal and first mesopleuro-third axillary sclerite of fore wing muscle.

label: posterior mesonoto-metanotal muscle
Defs: The mesonoto-metanotal muscle that arises from the mesoscutellum.

label: interstice
Defs: The area that is unsculptured and is delimited by striae or punctures.

label: anterior mesopleural sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that extends between the lateral end of the acetabular carina and the dorsal margin of the mesopleuron anterior to the mesopleural wing articulation.

label: normal osmolarity
Defs: An osmolarity which is relatively normal or average odor.

label: anal vein
Defs: The wing vein that articulates proximally with the third axillary sclerite and is located just posteriorly of the claval fold.

label: posterior side
Defs: An anatomical region that is the entire part of an anatomical structure posterior to a transverse plane and bounded on one side by the same transverse plane.

label: femoral condyle of the protibia
Defs: The femoral condyle of the tibia that is located on the protibia.

label: obsolete_report element
Defs: A report element is a narrative object in which information is presented and consumed by a human being, and is part of a report. Examples of report elements are figure (dot plot), table, text portion (may include a movie or audio clip on a web page).

label: upper ocular sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that is limited medially by the intersection of the frontofacial sulcus and the scrobal sulcus.

label: facial triangle
Defs: The area that is raised and  extends from between the antennal foramina to the posterior margin of the clypeus.

label: obsolete bright grey
Defs: A color consisting of grey color and high saturation.

label: ventral metafurcal lamella
Defs: The ridge that is located ventrally on the metafurcal arm.

label: osmolarity
Defs: A concentration quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s amount of osmoles of solute per liter of solution.

label: cellularity
Defs: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s consisting cells.

label: fertility
Defs: A reproductive quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s initiating, sustaining, or supporting reproduction.

label: dorsal orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed dorsally.

label: dorso-pleural line
Defs: The anatomical line that is located between the dorsum and the pleuron.

label: pronotal shoulder
Defs: The corner that is located anterolaterally on the horizontal part of the collar.

label: male-specific
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being present in males and absent from females in members of the same species.

label: trilobed
Defs: A lobed quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being divided into or having three lobes.

label: laterosternite
Defs: The sternite that is located laterally on an abdominal sternum.

label: mesepimeral sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that extends along the posterior margin of the mesopectus, delimits the mesepimeral area and corresponds to the mesepimeral ridge.

label: ligament
Defs: The area that is resilin rich.

label: epipharynx
Defs: The lobe that is located distally on the epipharyngeal wall.

label: transverse suture
Defs: The impression that delimits anteriorly the transverse trabecula.

label: intrinsic muscle of the mesopleuron
Defs: The mesopleural muscle that arises from the mesopleuron.

label: young
Defs: An age which is relatively low.

label: epipharyngeal muscle
Defs: The head muscle that inserts on the epipharyngeal wall.

label: Venn diagram
Defs:
A Venn diagram is a report graph showing all hypothetically possible
logical relations between a finite collection of sets.

label: prearticular incisure
Defs: The notch that is located on the margin of the second valvifer immediately anterior to the basal articulation of the second valvulae.

label: protandrous hermaphroditic organism
Defs: Sequential hermaphroditic organism that produces gametes first of the male sex, and then later of the female sex.

label: symbol
Defs: An information content entity that is a mark(s) or character(s) used as a conventional representation of another entity.

label: abdominal laterotergite 7
Defs: The laterotergite that is located on abdominal tergum 7.

label: magenta
Defs: A color consisting of red and blue hues.

label: partially dislocated
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being slightly out of its usual or proper place, or position.

label: pleural ridge
Defs: The ridge that extends between the pleural wing process and the lateral coxal articulation and marks the border between the episternum and epimeron.

label: increased temperature
Defs: A temperature which is relatively high.

label: mesometapleural suture
Defs: The line of separation that is located between the mesopectus and the metapectus.

label: split
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being divided or broken up into parts or divisions.

label: decreased male fertility
Defs: A male fertility which is relatively low.

label: unguitractor plate of the protarsus
Defs: The unguitractor plate that is located on the protarsus.

label: posterior tentorial arm
Defs: The apodeme that extends between the site of origin of the tentorial bridge and the posterior tentorial pit.

label: ipsilateral to
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being on the same side in relation to another structure.

label: supplementary material to a document
Defs: A part of a document that is segregated from the rest of the document due to its size

label: anterior pronotal slope
Defs: The concave area anteriorly on the mesosoma that accommodates the posterior area of the cranium.

label: dorsal projection of the second valvifer
Defs: The projection that is located on the second valvifer and corresponds to the proximal end of the rachis.

label: proximodorsal apodeme of cupula
Defs: The median apodeme on the proximodorsal region of the cupula.

label: quality of a substance
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of its constitution.

label: lateral coxal articular process of the metapleuron
Defs: The articular process that is located on the lateroventral margin of the metapectus and bears the lateral coxal condyle of the metapleuron.

label: T8
Defs: The tergite that is connected posteriorly to T9 via muscles.

label: fertile
Defs: A fertility quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being capable of initiating, sustaining, or supporting reproduction.

label: separating
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being in a position that produces a separation in, or acting to separate, another entity.

label: basal region
Defs: Anatomical region located basally on the body or body part.

label: decreased length
Defs: A length quality which is relatively small.

label: mislocalised laterally
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being positioned towards the side of an organism.

label: lacking processual parts
Defs: A quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking a processual part as specified by the additional entity.

label: flagellomere
Defs: The annulus that is located distally of the pedicel.

label: light grey
Defs: A color consisting of grey color and high brightness.

label: metascutellum
Defs: The area that is located posteromedially on the metanotum, is delimited laterally by the metanotal trough and corresponds to the reservoir of the dorsal vessel.

label: phosphorylated
Defs: A quality inhering in a protein or a molecule by virtue of the bearer\'s having a phosphate (PO4) group.

label: vertexal sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that is horizontal and extends between the compound eye and the lateral ocellus.

label: A1 flap
Defs: The carina that is located distally on the scape, that envelopes the proximal pedicel.

label: decreased elasticity
Defs: An elasticity which is relatively low.

label: centrally registered identifier registry
Defs: A CRID registry is a dataset of CRID records, each consisting of a CRID symbol and additional information which was recorded in the dataset through a assigning a centrally registered identifier process.

label: electric potential
Defs: A quality that is equal to the potential energy per unit charge associated with a static (time-invariant) electric field, also called the electrostatic potential.

label: ventral cibarial dilatator
Defs: The hypopharyngeal muscle that is unpaired and arises from the median anterior part of the tentorial bridge and inserts on the proximal part of the ventral wall of the cibarium or on the proximal margin of the sitophore, immediately distally to the point where the alimentary canal passes between the lateral arms of the sitophore.

label: sufficient
Defs: A wholeness quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s has enough functionality.

label: low brightness
Defs: A color brightness which is relatively low.

label: setal line
Defs: The row of setae that is located on the fore wing.

label: blade
Defs: The area that is located distally on the mandible.

label: normal coordination
Defs: A coordination which is relatively normal or average.

label: parapsidal hair line of mesoscutum
Defs: The row of setae that extends along the parapsidal line.

label: cardinal fragmentum
Defs: The sclerite that is elongate, paired, is lateral to the cardo and is articulated with the cardo and with the stipes.

label: interorbital space
Defs: The interocular distance that is the shortest between the inner margin of compound eyes.

label: metasomal tergum
Defs: The abdominal tergum that is located in the metasoma.

label: medial to
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located toward the middle relative to another entity.

label: pronotal side
Defs: The area that is located on the pronotum and that is vertical.

label: anterior surface
Defs: Anatomical surface that is located on the anterior side of the body or body part.

label: postalar process
Defs: The process that is located anterolaterally on the mesoscutellar-axillar complex and separates the site of origin of the fore wing from the site of origin of the hind wing.

label: diagonal petiolar length
Defs: The anatomical line that extends between the distalmost point of the subpetiolar process and the global minima of the contour line of the dorsal region of the posterior petiolar constriction in lateral view when the specimen is rotated until the contour line became as symmetric as possible.

label: mesepimeron
Defs: The epimeron that is located on the mesopleuron.

label: face
Defs: The area that is located ventrally of the ventral margin of the antennal foramen, medially of the malar sulcus and the inner orbit and dorsally of the epistomal sulcus.

label: mesothoracic venter
Defs: The area that is located ventrally of the mesopectus and limited dorsally by any line.

label: radiation emitting intensity quality
Defs: A radiation emitting quality which obtains by the intensity of the bearer emitted radiation.

label: decreased elevation
Defs: An elevation which is relatively low.

label: swollen
Defs: A structure quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting transient abnormal enlargement, not due to cell proliferation.

label: genome announcement textual entity
Defs: A textual entity that describes the generation and public release of a novel, draft genome sequence.

label: ventral impressed area of metanotum
Defs: The area that is median and is delimited anteriorly by the metascutellar arms and the metascutelum.

label: posterior section of dorsal flange of second valvifer
Defs: The area of the dorsal flange of the second valvifer that is posterior to the to the site of origin of the basal line.

label: abdominal laterotergite 4
Defs: The laterotergite that is located on abdominal tergum 4.

label: non-functional
Defs: A disfunctional quality held by the bearer when the latter is unable to perform a regular function(s).

label: pygidial plate
Defs: The area that is located posteriorly on the tergum of the last externally visible segment of the abdomen.

label: measurement methods section
Defs: A methods section that describes details of data assessment methods (data measurement).

label: postgenal ridge
Defs: The ridge that extends ventrally of the posterior tentorial pit and that is continuous with the tentorium.

label: cardinal lever
Defs: The process that receives the site of attachment of the cranio-cardinal muscle.

label: axillular spine
Defs: The spine on the distal margin of the axillula.

label: apical flagellomere
Defs: The flagellomere that is located distally on the flagellum.

label: sensillar patch
Defs: The patch that differs from surrounding region by presence of sensilla.

label: postocular contour line
Defs: The contour line of the postocular area in frontal view.

label: deep pink
Defs: Pink color having medium brightness and moderate saturation.

label: subcylindrical
Defs: A cylindrical shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being imperfectly cylindrical or approximately cylindrical.

label: anatomical surface
Defs: A 2D surface of an anatomical continuant.

label: rhythmic
Defs: A rhythm quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having rhythm.

label: absorption quality
Defs: A scalar EM radiation quality which obtains by the capacity of the bearer to retain radiation.

label: third mesopleuro-mesonotal muscle
Defs: The mesonotal muscle that originates from the ventral apodeme of the first phragma and inserts on the acropleural apodeme of the mesopleuron.

label: posterior trochanteral condyle of the metacoxa
Defs: The condyle that is located on the posterior trochanteral articular process of the metacoxa and inserts into the posterior coxal fossa of the metatrochanter.

label: temple
Defs: The area that is located on the gena, posterior to the compound eye.

label: muscle bearing process of the metanotum
Defs: The apodeme that corresponds to the site of insertions of the lateral metapleuro-metanotal muscles.

label: sitophore
Defs: The sclerite that is located in the proximal part of the hypopharygeal wall delimited distally by the functional mouth and proximally by the proximal boundary of the cibarium. The tentorio-hypopharyngeal muscle inserts on the proximal margin of the sitophore.

label: located in class
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s location within another entity.

label: portion of tissue
Defs: Anatomical structure, that consists of similar cells and intercellular matrix, aggregated according to genetically determined spatial relationships.

label: unidirectional
Defs: A directional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having one direction only.

label: anterolateral mesopectal projection
Defs: The projection that is located anterolaterally on the epicnemial carina.

label: decreased velocity
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s decreased rate of change of the position.

label: flexor apodeme
Defs: The apodeme that is located dorsally on the anterior margin of the metapectal-propodeal complex and corresponds to the site of origin of the metapleuro-third axillary sclerite of the hind wing muscle.

label: pretarsus of metatarsus
Defs: The pretarsus that is located in the metatasrus.

label: papillary
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s resembling small nipple like projection.

label: gonostyle
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of sclerites located distally of the cupula dorsolaterally of the volsella, and that surround the aedeagus.

label: author role
Defs: A role inhering in a person or organization that is realized when the bearer participates in the work which is the basis of the document, in the writing of the document, and signs it with their name.

label: parapsidal ridge
Defs: The carina that extends along the parapsidal line.

label: postero-medial margin
Defs: Anatomical margin that is located on the postero-medial region of the body or body part.

label: dilator muscle of the 8th abdominal spiracle
Defs: The spiracular muscle that arises anteroventrally from the tergal spiracular plate and inserts on the 8th abdominal spiracle.

label: high saturation
Defs: A color saturation which is of high purity.

label: flux
Defs: A physical quality that exists by virtue of the rate of flow of the bearer across a given surface.

label: acropleural sulcus
Defs: The line that delimits posteroventrally the acropleuron.

label: pleural wing process
Defs: The fossa that is located on the dorsal margin of the pleuron and accommodates the second axillary sclerite.

label: structure, cavities
Defs: A structural quality that inheres in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing hollow areas.

label: longitudinal scutellar carina
Defs: The carina that is longitudinal and extends between the anterior and posterior margins of the mesoscutellar-axillar complex.

label: epicoxal lobe
Defs: The area that is located posteroventrally on the propleuron and is delimited anteriorly by the epicoxal sulcus.

label: document title
Defs: A textual entity that names a document

label: protruding out of
Defs: A quality inhering into a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s extending out above or beyond its surface or boundary and outwards in relation to the physical space occupied by another entity.

label: cranial fossa of the cardo
Defs: The fossa that is located on the cardo and articulates with the cardinal condyle of the cranium.

label: lateral to
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located toward the side relative to another entity.

label: lateral mesofemoro-mesotibial muscle
Defs: The intrinsic leg muscle that arises laterally (dorsally) of the mesofemur and inserts on the dorsal process of the mesotibia.

label: hermaphrodite
Defs: A biological sex quality inhering in an organism or a population with both male and female sexual organs in one individual.

label: table of figures
Defs: A table that relates figures in a document to specific locations in that document (usually page numbers).  This is also a document part (subsumption there should be inferred).

label: decreased sensitivity of a process
Defs: A sensitivity of a process which is lower than normal or average.

label: postoccipital suture
Defs: The line that delimits the postocciput from the cranium.

label: increased fragility
Defs: A fragility which is relatively high.

label: fifth tarsomere of hind leg
Defs: The tarsomere that is distal to the fourth tarsomere of the hind leg.

label: 3rd abdominal spiracle
Defs: The abdominal spiracle that is located in the abdominal segment 3.

label: uncoiled
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being not curled or wound (especially in concentric rings or spirals).

label: genital membrane
Defs: The conjunctiva that connects the ventral margins of the second valvifers arching above the second valvula.

label: torulo-clypeal carina
Defs: The carina that is connects the clypeus with the antennal rim.

label: medial conjunctiva of the first valvula
Defs: The conjunctiva that extends medially along the first valvula.

label: increased circumference
Defs: A circumference which is relatively high.

label: fluorescence
Defs: A luminous flux quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s emitting longer wavelength light following the absorption of shorter wavelength radiation; fluorescence is common with aromatic compounds with several rings joined together.

label: radiation emitting quality
Defs: A scalar EM radiation quality which obtains by the capacity of the bearer to emit radiation.

label: genuflexor apodeme
Defs: The cuticular invagination at the distal end of the genuflexor sclerite that is adjacent to (articulates with) the outerwall of the tibia.

label: dysplastic growth
Defs: A growth quality of occurrent in which the growth of an organism, structure or group of organisms is abnormal.

label: parapsis
Defs: The area that is delimited medially by the parapsidal line and laterally by the parascutal carina.

label: membrane protein complex
Defs: Any protein complex that is part of a membrane.

label: vannal region
Defs: The area that is delimited by the vannal veins, or veins that articulates with the third axillary sclerite.

label: obsolete decreased action potential
Defs: An action potential which is relatively low.

label: erect
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being upright in position or posture.

label: decreased curvature
Defs: A curvature which is relatively low.

label: sternaular area
Defs: The area that is located between the epicnemial carina and the anterior margin of the femoral depression.

label: metasomal depression
Defs: The acetabulum that is concave, surrounds the nucha and accommodates the base of the metasoma.

label: lilac
Defs: A purple color which has low saturation and low brightness.

label: mesonoto-mesotrochantinal muscle
Defs: The mesotrochantinal muscle that originates from the mesonotum.

label: anteroventral depression of pronotum
Defs: The groove along the anteroventral border of the pronotum.

label: quadrangular
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having four angles and four sides.

label: conditional specification
Defs: A directive information entity that specifies what should happen if the trigger condition is fulfilled.

label: adipose system
Defs: An organ system pertaining to fat.

label: basal longitudinal carinae of the syntergum
Defs: The anteroposteriorly oriented carinae that arise posteriorly from the transverse carina on petiole.

label: transepisternal line
Defs: The line  that is longitudinal, extends ventrolaterally on the mesopleuron and corresponds with the site of origin of the second and third mesopleuro-third axillary sclerite of fore wing muscle and the second mesopleuro-mesonotal muscle.

label: angular velocity
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the rate of the bearer\'s angular movement about an axis; the angle rotated in a given time.

label: h plus
Defs: A S. pombe mating type determined by the mat1-Pc and mat1-Pi on the mat1 locus.

label: ligamentous
Defs: Having the nature or characteristic of, a ligament; composed of the tissue proper to ligaments.

label: triploid
Defs: A polyploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing three homologous sets of chromosomes.

label: anterior proximal process of the mesobasitarsus
Defs: The process that is located anteriorly on the proximal margin of the mesobasitarsus and corresponds to the site of insertion of the anterior mesotibio-mesobasitarsal muscle.

label: ipsilateral side
Defs: On the same side

label: labiomaxillary complex
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the labium and maxillae.

label: ventral ridge of clypeus
Defs: The ridge that arises medially from the pleurostomal condyle and corresponds to the site of attachment of the labrum.

label: pectus
Defs: The sclerite that is located ventrally of the thoracic segment and bears the furca and the lateral coxal condyle of the pleuron.

label: anteromedian pronotal ridge
Defs: The ridge that extends parallel to the anterior (ventral) margin of the pronotum and delimits dorsally the site of origin of the pronoto-propleural arm muscles.

label: sensitivity to oxygen
Defs: A sensitivity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s dependence on oxygen.

label: normal radiopacity
Defs: A radiopacity which is relatively normal or average

label: acinar
Defs: Pertaining to the individual parts making up an aggregate fruit like a many-lobed "berry," such as a raspberry.

label: gaseus configuration
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s parts having the arrangement which exhibits characteristics of gases.

label: median tentorio-scapal muscle
Defs: The antennal muscle that arises anteriorly from the anterior tentorial arm anteromedially of the site of origin of the anterior tentorio-scapal muscle and inserts medially on the proximal part of the scape.

label: claval fold
Defs: The wing fold that is located on the fore wing, parallels the anal vein, and extends to the claval notch on the wing margin.

label: anterolateral metacoxo-metatrochanteral muscle
Defs: The metatrochanteral muscle that arises anteriorly from the metacoxa and inserts on the articular membrane of the metacoxo-metatrochanteral joint laterally of the anterior metacoxo-metatrochanteral articulation.

label: abdominal tergite 10
Defs: The tergite that is located on the abdominal tergum 10.

label: blue
Defs: A color hue with low wavelength of that portion of the visible spectrum lying between green and indigo, evoked in the human observer by radiant energy with wavelengths of approximately 420 to 490 nanometers.

label: posterior lacinial fimbriae
Defs: The row of setae that traverses the lacinia along its posterior margin.

label: dorsal length of pronotum
Defs: The median anatomical line of the pronotum in dorsal view.

label: rotated
Defs: An oriented quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being relocated around an axis.

label: normal adhesivity
Defs: A adhesivity which is relatively normal or average.

label: increased frequency
Defs: A frequency which is relatively high.

label: pointleted
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s terminating abruptly in a little point.

label: proliferative
Defs: A cellular quality inhering in a cell that arises by virtue of whether the bearer exhibits the ability to grow and proliferate in number through cell division.

label: gonopod
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the gonostipites, volsellae and harpes.

label: viscosity
Defs: A physical quality of a liquid inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to internal resistance to flow.

label: import ontology module
Defs: A subset ontology module that is intended to be imported from another ontology.

label: distance
Defs: A quality that is the extent of space between two entities.

label: appendage segment
Defs: The segment that is metameric along the proximal-distal axis and is part of an appendage.

label: normal frequency
Defs: A frequency which is relatively normal.

label: median bridge of the second valvifers
Defs: The area that connects posterodorsally the second valvifers and is the site of attachment for the posterior T9-second valvifer muscle.

label: posterioralized
Defs: A malformed quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s gross morphology containing what are normally posterior structures and missing some or all of what are normally anterior structures.

label: in contact with
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s touching another entity.

label: capitate peg sensillum
Defs: Mushroom-shaped sensory structure on the flagellum, particularly theclava; sometimes called the sensilla ampullacea.

label: odorless
Defs: An odor quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking odour.

label: paraspiracular carina
Defs: The carina that extends along the lateral margin of the paraspiracular sulcus.

label: obsolete decreased consumption
Defs: A consumption which is relatively low.

label: aporous sensillum
Defs: The sensillum whose cuticular component is without any opening.

label: bulbous
Defs: A convex 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s resembling a teardrop.

label: distal fossa of the tarsomere
Defs: The fossa that is located distodorsally on the tarsomere and accommodates the proximal condyle of the subsequent tarsomere.

label: distal hypopharyngeal invagination
Defs: The invagination on the distal hypopharynx that id adjacent to the concavities of the hypopharyngeal rods.

label: increased amount
Defs: An amount which is relatively high.

label: protibio-pretarsus of the protarsus muscle
Defs: The flexor of the pretarsal claws of the fore leg muscle that arises from the protibia.

label: disomy
Defs: An aneuploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing only two chromosome from a pair in a cell\'s nucleus.

label: decreased affinity
Defs: An affinity which is relatively low.

label: facial striae
Defs: The anatomical cluster anterior to the malar sulcus that is composed of carinae radiating from the pleurostomal condyle.

label: inactive
Defs: A quality of a physical object that is currently realizing none of its functions.

label: table of abbreviations
Defs: A table where the constituent texts are abbreviations and their expansions

label: decreased porosity
Defs: An decrease in porosity.

label: postmarginal vein
Defs: The abscissa that is marginal and located distal to the marginal vein.

label: postal code
Defs: An identifier that denotes some postal delivery route, some aggregate of postal delivery routes or a geographical region and was created for the purpose of sorting and delivering mail.

label: first valvula
Defs: The area of the first valvifer-first valvula complex that is delimited distally by the proximal margin of the aulax.

label: dark green

label: femoral condyle of the tibia
Defs: The condyle that is located proximally on the tibia and inserts into the tibial fossa of the femur.

label: mediodistal cardinal ridge
Defs: The cardinal ridge that arises distally from the basal cardinal ridge and is oriented distomedially.

label: decreased osmolarity
Defs: A osmolarity which is relatively low.

label: processus articularis
Defs: The process that extends laterally from the proximal part of the second valvula and forms the median part of the basal articulation, and corresponds to the site of attachment for the anterior second valvifer-second valvula muscle.

label: compatibility
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to harmonious coexistence.

label: ventral head width
Defs: The anatomical line between the intersections of the cranium contour and ventral head line in frontal view. dorsal head width

label: compound organ
Defs: Anatomical structure that has as its parts two or more multi-tissue structures of at least two different types and which through specific morphogenetic processes forms a single distinct structural unit demarcated by bona fide boundaries from other distinct anatomical structures of different types.

label: lamnium
Defs: The area that is located on the lateral wall of the first and second valvulae and is subdivided by annuli.

label: time
Defs: A quality in which events occur in sequence.

label: anatomical point
Defs: Non-material anatomical entity of zero dimension, which forms a boundary of an anatomical line or surface.

label: tolerant to
Defs: A resistance quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of its disposition to endure or being insensitive to a stimulus.

label: chronological age
Defs: An age quality that exists by virtue of the time (years and months) that the bearer has existed.

label: 7th abdominal spiracle
Defs: The abdominal spiracle that is located in the abdominal segment 7.

label: responsive to
Defs: A response quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to react to a stimulus or an agent.

label: unpaired
Defs: The bearer of this quality has_part n=1 of the indicated entity type, where n is bilaterally paired for a comparable organism..

label: glandular
Defs: A morphology quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhbiting the morphological characteristics of a gland.

label: occipital arch
Defs: The area that is located on the cranium and is delimited anteriorly by the occipital suture and posteriorly by the postoccipital sutures.

label: decreased mass
Defs: A mass which is lower than normal or average.

label: T7+8
Defs: The distal region of the female abdomen whose posterior portion bears the cerci and the anterior portion is part of female T9.

label: carina
Defs: The process that is elongate and external.

label: obsolete_survival curve
Defs: A survival curve is a report graph which is a graphical representation of data where the percentage of survival is plotted as a function of time.

label: radiation equivalent dose
Defs: A radiation exposure quality inhering in a tissue by virtue of the relation between the absorbed dose to the effective biological damage of the radiation to that tissue.

label: premental arm
Defs: The area of the lateral premental face that receives the site of origin of the dorsal premento-salivarial muscle.

label: acrotergite
Defs: The area that is located anteriorly of the antecosta on the tergum.

label: antennal condyle of the cranium
Defs: The condyle that is located on the antennifer and inserts into the basal knob.

label: normal size
Defs: A size quality which is relatively normal or average

label: posterior metacoxo-metatrochanteral articulation of the metacoxa
Defs: The articulation that is composed of the posterior trochanteral condyle of the metacoxa and the posterior coxal fossa of the metatrochanter.

label: tarsal claw
Defs: The spur that is curved and projects from the apex of the last tarsal segment on either side of the arolium of the pretarsus.

label: numeral
Defs: A symbol that denotes a number.

label: decreased susceptibility toward
Defs: A susceptibility toward an external stimulus which is lower than normal/average.

label: anepisternum
Defs: The area of the episternum delimited by the paracoxal suture, basalar cleft and anapleural cleft.

label: decussate
Defs: A pattern quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s consisting of paired parts that alternately cross each other.

label: petiolar lamina
Defs: The evagination that is located on the posterior margin of the petiole, paired and overlaps the anterior region of the first gastral sternite.

label: setal pit
Defs: The impression with a centered seta.

label: ventral metapleural area
Defs: The area that is located on the metapleuron anteroventrally of the metapleural sulcus.

label: thickness
Defs: A 1-D extent quality which is equal to the dimension through an object as opposed to its length or width.

label: dorsolateral cupulo-gonostyle/volsella complex muscle
Defs: The cupulo-gonostyle/volsella complex muscle that arises from the dorsolateral part of the cupula, just laterally of the site of origin of the dorsomedian cupulo-gonostipal muscle, and inserts on the dorsolateral part of the gonostipes.

label: female-specific
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being present in females and absent from males in members of the same species.

label: laterosternite 2
Defs: The laterosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 2.

label: median metatrochantero-metafemoral articulation
Defs: The articulation that is composed of the femoral fossa of the metatrochanter and the trochanteral condyle of the metafemur.

label: fenestrated
Defs: A structure quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s delimited by a surface with holes.

label: data format specification
Defs:
A data format specification is the information content borne by the document published defining the specification.
Example: The ISO document specifying what encompasses an XML document; The instructions in a XSD file

label: epipygium
Defs: The flange that is located on abdominal tergum 10, between the cerci.

label: Proximodorsal inflection of cupulal margin
Defs: The median area at the  proximodorsal cupulal margin that is inflected and serves as the site of origin of the  dorsomedial cupulo-gonostipal muscles.

label: lacks parts or has fewer parts of type
Defs: The bearer of this quality has_part < n of the indicated entity type, where n is the normal amount for a comparable organism. Note that the bearer of the quality is the whole, not the part. Formally: If a bearer entity e has fewer parts of type X at time t, then the number of instances x of X at t such that x part_of e is < n, where n is either the normal number for comparable entities, or n is stated explicitly. This case includes the limit case, where the bearer lacks all parts of the specified type.

label: intrinsic muscle of the harpe
Defs: The male genitalia muscle that arises from the proximal margin of the lateral surface of the harpe and inserts proximally on the median surface of the harpe.

label: pigmented
Defs: A degree of pigmentation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having substances produced by living organisms that have a color resulting from selective color absorption.

label: ventral clypeal margin
Defs: The margin that delimits the clypeus distally (ventrally or anteriorly depending on the orientation of the head).

label: trochanteral articular process of the metafemur
Defs: The articular process that is located posteromedially on the proximal margin of the metafemur and bears the trochanteral condyle of the metafemur.

label: sterile
Defs: A fertility quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being incapable of initiating, sustaining, or supporting reproduction.

label: violet
Defs: A color hue with very low wavelength of that portion of the visible spectrum lying between reddish blue or bluish purple, evoked in the human observer by radiant energy with wavelengths of approximately 420 to 380 nanometers.

label: conflict of interest textual entity
Defs: A textual entity that expresses a situation involving one or more of the authors, or the funding source of a document whereby the authors or funding source stand to potentially gain (typically financially) from the results reported in the document.

label: central region
Defs: Anatomical region centrally located on the body or body part.

label: tibia
Defs: The leg segment that is proximal to the tarsus and distal to the femur.

label: mislocalised medially
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being positioned towards the middle of an organism.

label: apiceps
Defs: The area that is the distal part of the gonossiculus and is connected to the parossiculus via membranous conjunctiva.

label: abdominal laterotergite 9
Defs: The laterotergite that is located on abdominal tergum 9.

label: red
Defs: A color hue with high wavelength of the long-wave end of the visible spectrum, evoked in the human observer by radiant energy with wavelengths of approximately 630 to 750 nanometers.

label: normal anterior-posterior diameter
Defs: An anterior-posterior diameter which is relatively normal or average

label: preaxillar carina
Defs: The carina that extends across the preaxilla and separates the articulation area for the tegula.

label: mesometapleuron
Defs: The sclerite that is comprised of the fused meso- and metapleura.

label: monstrous
Defs: A malformed quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s all-encompassing, grotesque morphological defects.

label: table of contents
Defs: A table that relates document parts to specific locations in a document (usually page numbers).  This is also a document part (subsumption there should be inferred).

label: prodiscrimenal lamella
Defs: The discrimenal lamella that is located in the prothorax.

label: anterior section of dorsal flange of second valvifer
Defs: The area of the dorsal flange of the second valvifer that is anterior to the site of origin of the basal line.

label: meltability
Defs: A quality which inheres in a substance by virtue of the ease with which the substance can be changed from a solid to a liquid state especially by the application of heat.

label: galeal comb
Defs: The galeal fringe that is on the lateral margin of the apicolateral galeal plate.

label: partial trisomy
Defs: A trisomy quality inhering in a bearer when part of the bearer\'s extra chromosome is attached to one of the other chromosomes, or if one of the bearer\'s chromosomes has two copies of part of its chromosome.

label: Weber length
Defs: The anatomical line that is the distance from the posteroventral corner of the metapleuron to the anteriormost part of the mesoscutum, measured in lateral view.

label: larval head
Defs: The larval tagma that is located anterior to the thorax.

label: hamulus
Defs: The seta that is located on the anterior margin of the hind wing and interlocks with the recurved posterior edge of the fore wing in Hymenoptera during flight, making them functionally one winged.

label: posterior surface
Defs: Anatomical surface that is located on the posterior side of the body or body part.

label: caudal cylinder
Defs: The petiolar area posterior to the posterior petiolar constriction.

label: anterodistal orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed anterodistally.

label: supraclypeal depression
Defs: The median impression on the frons that is dorsal to the intertorular carina and is not a scrobe for receiving the scape.

label: vertical lobe of mesoscutum
Defs: The inflection that extends ventrally along the anterolateral margin of the mesoscutum.

label: increased resistance to
Defs: A resistance to a stimulus which is relatively high.

label: light magenta
Defs: A color consisting of magenta color and high brightness.

label: mesotrochanteral apodeme
Defs: The sclerite that is located on the proximomedial margin of the mesotrochanter and corresponds to the site of insertion of the mesocoxo-mesotrochanteral muscles.

label: increased phosphorylation
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being phosphorylated to a more than normal extent, or fully saturated with phosphate groups.

label: radial vein
Defs: The wing vein that is connected to the second axillary sclerite and extends posterior to the subcosta.

label: anatomical structure
Defs: Material anatomical entity which has inherent 3D shape and is generated by coordinated expression of the organism\'s own genome.

label: setose
Defs: A hairy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being covered with setae.

label: partially broken
Defs: A broken quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being still one contiguous whole but structurally damaged such that in danger of become two or more.

label: femoro-tibial joint
Defs: The dicondylic joint that is composed of the femur and the tibia.

label: Stipital articular surface of the postmentum
Defs: The articular surface that articulates with the madial margin of the stipes.

label: spade-shaped
Defs: A shape that is in the form of a spade.

label: intact female
Defs: Female quality of having complete, unaltered reproductive organs

label: sensillar patch of the male flagellomere
Defs: The sensillar patch that is located on the ventral surface of the male flagellomere.

label: fore leg
Defs: The leg that is located on the prothorax.

label: insufficient
Defs: A wholeness quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacks enough functionality.

label: two dimensional cartesian spatial coordinate datum
Defs: A cartesion spatial coordinate datum that  uses two values to specify a position within a two dimensional spatial region

label: ninth flagellomere
Defs: The flagellomere that is located immediately distal to the eighth flagellomere.

label: low saturation
Defs: A color saturation which is of low purity.

label: dorsal length of mesoscutum
Defs: The mesoscutum length in dorsal view.

label: body
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the whole organism but which excludes the antennae, legs and wings.

label: normal curvature
Defs: A curvature which is relatively normal or average.

label: anatomical margin
Defs: Fiat anatomical region extending a short distance from the boundary of an object inwards.

label: postpectal carina
Defs: The carina that delimits anterolaterally the mesocoxal depression.

label: abdominal mediotergite 2
Defs: The mediotergite that is located on abdominal tergum 2.

label: abdominal sternum 7
Defs: The abdominal sternum that is located on abdominal segment 7.

label: brochidodromous
Defs: A branched quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having secondary branches joined together in a series of prominent arches.

label: neoplastic, spontaneous
Defs: A disposition inhering in a tumour by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to spontaneously arise.

label: balance
Defs: A behavioral quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of having physical steadiness.

label: dorsal prepectal inflection
Defs: The inflection that extends along the dorsal margin of the prepectus.

label: hyperresponsive to
Defs: A response quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s excessive reaction to a stimulus or an agent.

label: dorsal mesofurco-profurcal muscle
Defs: The profurcal muscle that originates from the lateral part of the lateral mesofurcal arm and inserts on the posterior surface of the posterior profurcal lamella.

label: splayed lateral
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curved outwards from the side.

label: insusceptible toward
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking susceptibilty toward an external stimulus.

label: optical quality
Defs: An EM radiation quality in which the EM radiation is within the fiat range of the spectrum visible deemed to be light.

label: data item extraction from journal article
Defs: A planned process in which journal articles are read or processed and data items are extracted, typically for further analysis or indexing

label: endocuticle
Defs: The procuticle that is not tanned (sclerotised, proteins scarcely crosslinked) and located between the Schmidt\'s layer and the exocuticle.

label: facial midridge
Defs: The carina that is median and extends between the torular space and the epistomal sulcus.

label: luminance
Defs: A quality that exists by virtue of the luminous intensity per unit area projected in a given direction.

label: dorsal plate
Defs: The sclerite that is paired, is located distal to the manubrium and is connected laterally with the arcus.

label: distal surface
Defs: Anatomical surface that is located on the distal side of the body or body part.

label: second valvifer-second valvula-third valvula complex
Defs: The area that is connected to the ninth tergite and the first valvifer via conjunctiva, is articulated to the first tergite, and bears the aulax.

label: punctate
Defs: A pattern inhering in a surface by virtue of the bearer\'s being marked by the presence of dots, punctures, points or pits.

label: pleurite
Defs: The sclerite that is located on the pleuron.

label: research settings section
Defs: A document part that describes the physical/social/cultural conditions around a research trial.

label: profurcal muscle
Defs: The thoracic muscle that inserts on the profurca.

label: cardino-stipital hinge
Defs: The conjunctiva that is between the stipes and cardo.

label: surrounded by
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being enclosed on all sides by another entity.

label: postocular head width
Defs: The anatomical line between the posteriormost points of the postocular contour lines.

label: dark purple
Defs: A color consisting of purple color and low brightness.

label: transscutal ridge
Defs: The ridge that is adjacent posteriorly to the transscutal articulation.

label: cup-shaped
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s shape form resembling the shape of a cup.

label: third phragmo-second abdominal tergal muscle
Defs: The second abdominal tergal muscle that arises from the metaphragma and inserts on the dorsal surface of the second abdominal tergum.

label: posterior coxal fossa of the protrochanter
Defs: The fossa that is located posteriorly on the proximal margin of the protrochanter accommodating the posterior trochanteral condyle of the procoxa.

label: musculus retractor unguis
Defs: The intrinsic leg muscle that originates within the tibia and femur and has a long tendon that inserts through the terminal tarsomere onto the unguitractor.

label: increased sensitivity of a process to oxygen
Defs: A sensitivity of occurrent to oxygen which is higher than normal or average.

label: transscutal impression
Defs: The sulcus that extends along the transscutal line.

label: bi-directional
Defs: A directional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having two directions.

label: paraocular carina
Defs: The carina that surrounds the compound eye.

label: petiolar scrobe
Defs: The scrobe that is located ventrally of the propodeal foramen and accommodates the proximal area of the petiole.

label: increased age
Defs: An age which is high relative to the normal or average.

label: pretarsus of mesotarsus
Defs: The pretarsus that is located on the mesotarsus.

label: sleep pattern
Defs: A sleep quality defined by the mathematic properties of the relative time frames of the sleep cycle.

label: parapsidal furrow
Defs: The impression that extends along the parapsidal line.

label: centered
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located in a position equidistant from edges.

label: postero-lateral margin
Defs: Anatomical margin that is located on the postero-lateral region of the body or body part.

label: dilator of the propodeal spiracle muscle
Defs: The first abdominal tergal spiracle muscle that does not extend between the dorsal and ventral spiraclar apodeme but attaches to one of these apodemes.

label: plasma membrane protein complex
Defs: Any protein complex that is part of the plasma membrane.

label: vas deferens
Defs: The duct that connect the testis with the ejaculatory duct.

label: discontinuous
Defs: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being marked by breaks or interruptions.

label: plasma membrane bounded cell projection
Defs: A prolongation or process extending from a cell and that is bounded by plasma membrane, e.g. a cilium, lamellipodium, or axon.

label: elasticity
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to recover its size and shape after deformation in any way.

label: acrosternite
Defs: The area that is located anteriorly of the antecosta of a sternum.

label: metasternum
Defs: The eusternum that is located in the metathorax.

label: decreased temperature
Defs: A temperature which is relatively low.

label: longitudinal ridge on the posterior surface of metatibia
Defs: The carina that extends along the posterior surface of the metatibia between the distal and proximal ends of the metatibia.

label: epicoxal sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that is dorsal to the coxal foramen.

label: postmento-premental muscle
Defs: The labial muscle that is unpaired, arises from the postmentum and inserts on the proximal margin of the prementum.

label: hyporesponsive to
Defs: A response quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s limited reaction to a stimulus or an agent.

label: decreased fertility
Defs: A fertility which is relatively low.

label: a mating type (yeast)
Defs: A S. cerevisiae mating type cells that secrete a pheromone that in alpha haploids stimulates processes that lead to mating.

label: lateral mesocoxo-mesotrochanteral muscle
Defs: The mesotrochanteral muscle that arises laterally from the mesocoxa and inserts anteriorly on the trochanter anterolaterally of the posterior mesocoxo-mesotrochanteral articulation.

label: unguitractor plate of the metatarsus
Defs: The unguitractor plate that is located in the metatarsus.

label: normal variability of rate
Defs: A variability of rate which is relatively normal or average

label: running title
Defs: A shorter version of a document title

label: metadiscrimen
Defs: The discrimen that is located in the metathorax and corresponds to the metadiscrimenal lamella.

label: split laterally
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being split asymmetrically on one side.

label: compression-fractured
Defs: A fractured quality that is caused by a loss of bone mass (osteoporosis) that occurs as part of aging.

label: scute-like
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being shaped like a scute or an osteoderm.

label: radicle
Defs: The area that is located proximally on the scape, is limited distally by a constriction and bears proximally the basal knob.

label: digital spine
Defs: The projection that is located apically on the gonossiculus.

label: catalytic activity
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a catalyst by virtue of the amount of the catalyst\'s action.

label: posterior carina of subaxillular bar
Defs: The carina that delimits posteriorly the subaxillular bar.

label: decreased fragility
Defs: A fragility which is relatively low.

label: 5th abdominal spiracle
Defs: The abdominal spiracle that is located in the abdominal segment 5.

label: T9
Defs: The tergite that is connected to S9 via muscles .

label: dorsal profurco-procoxal muscle
Defs: The procoxal muscle that arises from along the dorsal profurcal lamella.

label: length of dorsal projection
Defs: The anatomical line that is parallel with the longitudinal body axis and the shortest among the anatomical line that extends between the anterior and posterior margins of the dorsal projection of the second valvifer.

label: decreased circumference
Defs: A circumference which is relatively low.

label: anterior proximal process of the metabasitarsus
Defs: The process that is located anteriorly on the proximal margin of the metabasitarsus and corresponds to the site of insertion of the anterior metatibio-metabasitarsal muscle.

label: anteroventral pronotal inflection
Defs: The inflection that is located on the anteroventral margin of the pronotum.

label: metapecto-propodeal conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva that connects the lateral end of the antecostal sulcus of the first abdominal tergum with the anterior margin of the metanoto-propodeo-metapecto-mesopectal complex.

label: having extra function
Defs: A functionality quality which is held by the bearer when the latter is able to perform additional or different function(s).

label: trinucleate
Defs: A nucleate quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having three nuclei.

label: parascrobal area
Defs: The area that is located on the upper face, is delimited medially by the antennal scrobe and laterally by the inner orbit.

label: database extract, transform, and load process
Defs: A planned process which takes as input a database and fills another database by extracting concretizations of information entities from the first, transforming them, and loading the transformed concretizations into the second.

label: flagellum
Defs: The anatomical cluster composed of flagellomeres.

label: exserted
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s protruding or projecting from the body.

label: arched
Defs: A concave quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s forming or resembling an arch.

label: prospinasterno-profurcal muscle
Defs: The profurcal muscle that arises form the prospinasternum.

label: left side
Defs: The side of an organism that is left of the sagittal plane.

label: preorbital suture
Defs: The sulcus that extends along the median margin of the preorbital trabecula.

label: obsolete plant growth hormone sensitivity value
identifier
Defs: An identifier is an information content entity that is the outcome of a dubbing process and is used to refer to one instance of entity shared by a group of people to refer to that individual entity.

label: normal resistance to
Defs: A resistance to a stimulus which is relatively normal or average

label: pharynx
Defs: The anatomical space that is located proximal to the cibarium.

label: sensillum trichodeum curvatum
Defs: The sensillum that is curved.

label: ventral edge of propleuron
Defs: The edge that sets off the ventral vertical lobe of the propleuron from the ventral propleural area.

label: attached to
Defs: An attachment quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s connection or association with another entity.

label: notaular ridge
Defs: The ridge that corresponds with the notaulus.

label: posteriorly rotated
Defs: A rotation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of being rotated towards the rear of organism.

label: infiltrative
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s penetrating or permeating another substance or area.

label: tibial fossa of the profemur
Defs: The tibial fossa of the femur that is located on the protibia.

label: mesobasicoxite
Defs: The basicoxite that is located on the mesocoxa.

label: F mating type
Defs: A bacterial mating type indicating the presence of F plasmid in a bacterial cell.

label: length of petiolar node
Defs: The anatomical line that is the shortest between the center of the petiolar spiracle and the posterior margin of the petiole in lateral view.

label: anterior metafurcal arm
Defs: The apodeme that is located anteromedially on the lateral metafurcal arm and corresponds to the site of origin of the lateral metafurco-mesofurcal muscle.

label: pronotal suprahumeral sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that extends along the dorsal margin of the pronotum and delimits the dorsal pronotal area.

label: brush-like shape
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s resembling the end of a brush with a multitude of bristles.

label: metafurco-metacoxal muscle
Defs: The metacoxal muscle that originates from the metafurca and inserts on the posterior margin of the metacoxa.

label: ventralized
Defs: A malformed quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s gross morphology containing what are normally ventral structures and missing some or all of what are normally dorsal structures.

label: postclypeus
Defs: The area that is located on the clypeus and is delimited by the epistomal sulcus and a medial transverse anatomical line.

label: postoccipital carina
Defs: The rim that surrounds the occipital foramen.

label: ventral row of spines
Defs: The row that is composed of spines and is located ventrally on the apex of the calcar.

label: coordinated
Defs: A coordination quality of inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having skillful and effective interaction of movement.

label: mesotibial apical peg
Defs: The row of spurs that extends along the distal margin of the mesotibia.

label: pedicel
Defs: The antennal segment that is connected proximally to the scape and distally to the flagellum.

label: textual entity
Defs: A textual entity is a part of a manifestation (FRBR sense), a generically dependent continuant whose concretizations are patterns of glyphs intended to be interpreted as words, formulas, etc.

label: dislocated
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being out of its usual or proper place, or position.

label: lateral margin
Defs: Anatomical margin that is located on the lateral side of the body or body part.

label: aerobic
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s dependence on oxygen.

label: avidity
Defs: A molecular quality that arises from the synergistic strength of bond affinities between multiple bond interactions.

label: uniparental disomy
Defs: A disomy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing two copies of the chromosome from one of the parents (with no contribution from the other parent).

label: abdominal laterotergite 5
Defs: The laterotergite that is located on abdominal tergum 5.

label: posterior projection of mesoscutellum
Defs: The paired process that is located posteriorly on the dorsal surface of the mesoscutellum.

label: spiracle
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the distal end of the trachea and the margin of the sclerite or conjunctiva surrounding the spiracular opening.

label: dissociated from
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking physically interaction with another entity.

label: papillomatous
Defs: A round or lobulated protruding form resembling a nipple.

label: claval lobe
Defs: The wing region that is posterior to the claval furrow and anterior to the jugal fold.

label: constitutively active

label: prepalpal ventral premental area

label: arolium

label: contour line
Defs: The boundary of the orthographic projection of a defined side of the anatomical structure.

label: second intrinsic muscle of the maxillary palp

label: interocular separation

label: laterocervical muscle

label: anus

label: quality of an aerosol
Defs: A physical quality inhering in an entity by virtue of the bearer\'s solid or liquid constituents being suspended in a gas.

label: prodiscrimen

label: sensitive toward

label: senescent
Defs: A time quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s growing old; aging.

label: multiple
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being present in more than two copies.

label: occipital carina

label: parallel to

label: symmetrical

label: head+mesosoma length

label: medial coxal condyle of the pectus
Defs: The coxal condyle of the pectus that inserts into the medial pectal fossa of the coxa.

label: role

label: torulus

label: ventral premental face
Defs: The area of the prementum that is delimited laterally by the lateral premental face.

label: cupula
Defs: The sclerite that is connected via conjunctiva and attached via muscles to abdominal tergum 9 and the gonostyle/volsella complex.

label: dorsal-ventral polarity
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s location of features or characteristics along the dorsal-ventral axis.

label: anterior-posterior polarity
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s location of features or characteristics along the anterior-posterior axis.

label: median longitudinal furrow of mesoscutellum

label: annellus

label: plica vannalis

label: tibial condyle of the mesobasitarsus

label: displaced

label: increased distribution

label: normal distance

label: abdominal mediotergite 4
Defs: The mediotergite that is located on abdominal tergum 4.

label: postphragma
