Defs: The laterotergite that is located on abdominal tergum 10.

label: spur
Defs: The process that is surrounded by conjunctiva and evaginated and that is basally sclerotized.

label: posterior metanoto-metacoxal muscle
Defs: The metacoxal muscle that arises from the metanotum posterior to the site of origin of the anterior metanoto-metacoxal muscle.

label: probasitarsus
Defs: The basitarsus that is located on the protarsus.

label: D-shaped
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a strait side and an arched side giving the bearer the form of the letter D.

label: diagram
Defs: A figure that expresses one or more propositions

label: apical setae of T3
Defs: The row of setae that is transverse and located distally on the third metasomal mediotergite and is composed of setae at least 2 times as long as other setae on the metasoma.

label: apical process of the labrum
Defs: The process that located distomedially on the labrum.

label: metatarsus
Defs: The tarsus that is located in the hind leg.

label: internal median longitudinal scutoscutellar ridge
Defs: The ridge that is median and is at the posterior region of the mesoscutellum.

label: phenotypic sex
Defs: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s physical expression of sexual characteristics.

label: albedo
Defs: A reflective quality restricted to a particular wavelength.

label: propodeo-second abdominal segment muscle
Defs: The muscle that arises from the propodeum and inserts laterally on the second abdominal segment.

label: truncated
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s terminating abruptly by having or as if having an end or point cut off.

label: dorsomedial orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed dorsomedially.

label: tentorial arm
Defs: The apodeme that extends between the posterior tentorial pit and the anterior tentorial pit.

label: metatarsal claw
Defs: The tarsal claw that is located in the hind leg.

label: netrion
Defs: The area that is located posteroventrally on the pronotum and corresponds to the site of origin of first flexor of the fore wing muscle.

label: dephosphorylated
Defs: A quality inhering in a protein or a molecule by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking a phosphate (PO4) group.

label: circling direction
Defs: A directional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s direction approximating the shape of a circle.

label: distal gonostipo-parossiculal muscle
Defs: The gonostyle/parossiculal muscle that arises distally of the lateral part of the gonostipes and inserts on the distal part of the parossiculus distally of the site of origin of the proximal gonostipo-parossiculal muscle.

label: length of malar sulcus
Defs: The straight anatomical line between the proximal and distal ends of the malar sulcus.

label: prepecto-procoxal muscle
Defs: The procoxal muscle that arises from the prepectus.

label: distended
Defs: A size quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being abnormally expanded or increased in size.

label: mesonoto-mesocoxal muscle
Defs: The mesocoxal muscle that arises from the mesonotum and inserts on the posterior margin of the mesocoxa.

label: simple
Defs: A complexity quality in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having few parts or being complicated or compound.

label: hardness
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s resistance to pressure, being broken, or pierced

label: dorso-medial margin
Defs: Anatomical margin that is located on the dorso-medial region of the body or body part.

label: mesolaterophragma
Defs: The area that is well sclerotised, composes the lateral part of the mesophragma and is continuous with the dorsal and ventral mesopostnotal flanges, is connected distally with the subalare and ventrally bears the mesopostnotal apodeme.

label: phase
Defs: A quality that exists by virtue of being a particular point in the time of a cycle.

label: dorsal submedian impression of cupula
Defs: The impression that is located dorsolaterally on the cupula and corresponds to the site of origin of the lateral cupulo-gonostipal muscle.

label: normal tonicity
Defs: A tonicity which is relatively normal or average

label: brachydont
Defs: A 3-D shape inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having dentition characterized by low-crowned teeth. Human teeth are brachydont.

label: propleuro-procoxal muscle
Defs: The procoxal muscle that arises from along the posterodorsal margin of the propleuron and inserts on the procoxa.

label: demyelinated
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s loss of myelin sheath.

label: circumference
Defs: An 1-D extent quality which is equal to the length of the closed curve of a circle.

label: metacoxal muscle
Defs: The leg muscle that inserts on the metacoxa.

label: proximal to
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located more centrally than another entity.

label: anterior extension of mesofurca
Defs: The area that is located distally on the lateral mesofurcal arm and corresponds to the site of origin of the lateral anterior mesopleuro-mesofurcal muscle.

label: Saccharomyces cerevisiae mating type
Defs: A S. cerevisiae mating type.

label: posterior extension of preaxilla
Defs: The area that is located on the posteroventral corner of the preaxilla and articulates with the anterior extension of the lateral axillar area.

label: robust
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being strong, thick or sturdy.

label: independent continuant
Defs: b is an independent continuant = Def. b is a continuant which is such that there is no c and no t such that b s-depends_on c at t. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [017-002])

label: distal hypopharynx
Defs: The area that is located on the anterior surface of the hypopharyngeal wall and is delimited proximally by the infrabuccal pouch or the distal margin of the sitophore, distally by the salivarial orifice and laterally by the lateral parts of the prementum and the hypopharyngeal rods.

label: proximomedian apodeme of the harpe
Defs: The apodeme that is on the proximomedian margin of the harpe that is the site of insertion of the proximal and distal gonostyle/volsella complex-harpal muscles.

label: abdominal mediotergite 3
Defs: The mediotergite that is located on abdominal tergum 3.

label: increased area
Defs: An area which is relatively high.

label: heat conductivity
Defs: A conductivity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to spontaneous transfer of thermal energy from a region of higher temperature to a region of lower temperature.

label: scrobe
Defs: The area that is impressed and is for the reception or concealment of another sclerite.

label: aromatic
Defs: A molecular quality that inheres in a molecular entity when it possesses at least one ring that is aromatic, i.e. A conjugated ring of unsaturated bonds, lone pairs, or empty orbitals that exhibit a stabilization stronger than would be expected by the stabilization of conjugation alone.

label: edematous
Defs: A structural quality which is held by a bearer when the latter exhibits an excessive accumulation of extracellular fluid.

label: first sclerite of the labial palp
Defs: The sclerite that is ringlike and is connected distolaterally to the prementum via conjunctiva and muscle.

label: author summary section
Defs: A part of a document, distinct from the abstract, that describes the significance and broader context of the document content. The author summary is often written in a non-technical manner and is aimed at both scientists and non-scientist readers.

label: tibial extensor muscle
Defs: The intrinsic leg muscle that arises laterally (dorsally) of the femur and inserts on the dorsal process of the tibia.

label: third axillary
Defs: The axillary sclerite that corresponds to the site of insertion of the mesopleuro-third axillary sclerite muscles and is connected proximally with the fourth axillary sclerite.

label: sagittal plane
Defs: Anatomical plane that divides a bilateral body into left and right parts, not necessarily of even size.

label: cheek
Defs: The area that is located ventrally in between the eye and the oral foramen.

label: fibrotic
Defs: Fibrosis is the formation of excess fibrous connective tissue in an organ or tissue in a reparative or reactive process.

label: anterior mesofemoro-mesotibial articulation
Defs: The anterior femoro-tibial articulation that is composed of the anterior tibial condyle and fossa of the mesofemur and the anterior femoral condyle and fossa of the mesotibia.

label: secondary
Defs: A quality in which the effect or outcome is not primary or the focus of the observation.

label: tentorial bridge
Defs: The apodeme that connects medially the tentorial arms.

label: lateral metapleuro-metanotal muscle
Defs: The muscle that arises laterally from the metapleuron and iserts on the muscle bearing process of the metanotum.

label: harpe width
Defs: The width of the harpe in lateral view.

label: fragility
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to being damaged or destroyed.

label: inserted into
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s becoming joined together with an additional entity.

label: secretory pore
Defs: The anatomical space that corresponds to the distal end of an exocrine gland.

label: depth
Defs: A 1-D extent quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s downward or backward or inward dimenision.

label: clypeogenal sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that corresponds to the clypeo-pleurostomal line.

label: ochre
Defs: A moderate yellow-orange to orange color.

label: increased width and length
Defs: A width and length quality that is relatively large, where both width and length are increased.

label: mesofurco-profurcal muscle
Defs: The profurcal muscle that arises from the mesofurca.

label: furca
Defs: The apodeme that arises medially from the ventral part of the thorax and corresponds to the site of origin of interfurcal and coxal muscles.

label: biscupidate
Defs: A cuscpidate quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer possessing two cusps.

label: asynchronous
Defs: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s not occurring or existing at the same time or having the same period or phase.

label: maximum cephalic length in median line
Defs: The median anatomical line that extends between the posterior margin of the cranium and the distal margin of the clypeus in frontal view.

label: documenting
Defs: A planned process in which a document is created or added to by including the specified input in it.

label: deep-superficial gradient
Defs: Anatomical gradient that is distributed along the deep-superficial axis.

label: spiracular muscle
Defs: The muscle that inserts to the spiracle.

label: mesofurcal bridge
Defs: The apodeme that connects the lateral mesofurcal arms and corresponds to the site of origin of the dorsal mesofurco-profurcal muscle.

label: inner cardinal process
Defs: The articular process that is located distomedially on the cardo and articulates with the stipes.

label: sturdy spines of the hind femur
Defs: The spine that is located on the ventral face of the metafemur.

label: articulation
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of two adjacent articular surfaces.

label: flush
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being level or even with another surface.

label: dorsal petiolar profile contour line
Defs: The contour line of the dorsal petiolar profile in lateral view.

label: labral compressor
Defs: The epipharyngeal muscle that arises from the proximal part of the labrum and inserts on the distal epipharyngeal wall.

label: ventral salivarial dilatator
Defs: The salivarial muscle that arises from the proximal end of the ventral part of the prementum and inserts on the salivarial sclerite.

label: penisvalva
Defs: The sclerite that is in the middle of the external male genitalia, surrounds the distal part of the ductus ejaculatorius and the endophallus.

label: requirements textual entity
Defs: A textual entity that expresses the requirements necessary to use a resource, e.g. software.

label: first phragmo-second phragmal muscle
Defs: The mesophragmal muscle that extends between the prophragma and mesophragma.

label: dark brown
Defs: A color consisting of brown hue and low brightness.

label: posterior scutellar depression
Defs: The line that extends just posterior of the posterior mesoscutellar ridge/mesoscutellar arms and delimits the posterior margin of the mesoscutellar pulsatory organ and the anterior margin of the mesopostscutellum.

label: anaerobic
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s independence on oxygen.

label: hypostoma
Defs: The area that extends on the posterior (ventral) margin of the oral foramen along the site of attachments of the conjunctiva connecting the cranium with the maxillae and is delimited laterally by the pleurostomal fossa.

label: nervous system
Defs: The organ system that is composed of neurons and glial cells.

label: radiation quality
Defs: A quality that inheres in an bearer by virtue of how that bearer interacts with radiation.

label: divergent from
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having two or more entities that extend from a common point in different directions.

label: closure
Defs: A morphological quality pertaining to the degree to which an object contains an opening, aperture, orifice or vent.

label: neotenous growth
Defs: A paedomorphic growth quality which is due to a reduced rate.

label: cylindrical
Defs: A convex 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting a consistently-sized round cross section.

label: postspiracular furrow
Defs: The groove that is longitudinal and is immediately posterior or postero-medial to the first abdominal spiracle.

label: leg segment
Defs: The segment that is part of a leg.

label: mixed
Defs: A composition quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being composed of more than one identifiable entities.

label: depression
Defs: The area that is external, concave, point-like and does not correspond to an apodeme.

label: stipito-premental conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva that extends along the posterior (dorsal) margin of the premental arm and the proximal margin of the medial stipital wall.

label: basitarsal articular process of the mesotibia
Defs: The articular process that is located distodorsally on the mesotibia and bears the basitarsal fossa of the protiba.

label: second tarsomere of fore leg
Defs: The tarsomere that is distal to and connected to the probasitarsus.

label: normal age
Defs: An age which is relatively normal or average.

label: posterior stipital wall
Defs: The area that is limited medially by the medial stipital wall and proximolaterally by the margin of the posterior stipital sclerite.

label: campaniform stipital sensillum
Defs: The campaniform sensillum on the stipes.

label: equilateral triangular
Defs: A triangular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having all sides of the same length.

label: prepecto-anterior thoracic spiracle muscle
Defs: The anterior thoracic spiracle occlusor muscle that originates from the prepectus and inserts on the mesothoracic spiracle.

label: longitudinal vein
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of abscissae extending along the long axis of the wing.

label: pronotal flange
Defs: The evagination that extends along the anterior margin of the pronotum and overlaps the head-propectus articulation.

label: antero-ventral region
Defs: Anatomical region that overlaps the anterior and ventral regions of a body or body part.

label: anteclypeal setal pair
Defs: The setae that are paired and are located laterally on the ventral rim of clypeus.

label: revolute
Defs: A curled quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s edges of its surface being rolled backwards spirally on each side.

label: duct
Defs: The cavitated compound organ that is canal-like, layered with epithelial cells and leads from an exocrine gland or organ.

label: ocular suture
Defs: The sulcus that extends along the margin of compound eye and corresponds to the circumocular ridge.

label: slender
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being small or narrow in circumference or width in proportion to length or height.

label: metafemoro-metatibial joint
Defs: The femoro-tibial joint that is composed of the metafemur, the metatibia and the articular membrane of the metafemoro-metatibial joint.

label: postscutellum
Defs: The area that is located medially on the dorsellum and bears the metanotal flange.

label: basal margin
Defs: Anatomical margin that is located on the basal side of the body or body part.

label: anterolateral depression of the petiole
Defs: The depression that is located anterolaterally on the abdominal tergum 2 and accommodates the propodeal tooth.

label: trumpet-shaped
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s shape form resembling the shape of a trumpet.

label: abdominal sternum 10
Defs: The abdominal sternum that is located on abdominal segment 10.

label: minimum width
Defs: The width that is the shortest.

label: ventral side
Defs: An anatomical region that is the entire part of an anatomical structure ventral to a horizontal plane and bounded on one side by the same horizontal plane.

label: genuflexor plate of the mid leg
Defs: The genuflexor plate that is located in the mid leg.

label: mesoscutal suprahumeral sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that extends along the anterior margin of the mesoscutum between the anterior-most point of the preaxilla and the anteroadmedian line and corresponds to the vertical lobe of the mesoscutum.

label: lysed
Defs: The breakdown, disintegration, destruction of an entity due to the breaking of cell membranes by any means.

label: increased stability
Defs: An increase in stability.

label: metalaterophragma
Defs: The area that is located laterally on the metaphragma.

label: postdisplaced growth
Defs: A paedomorphic growth quality which is due to a delayed onset.

label: platelike
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being roundish, flattish shape, possibly with a slightly angled edge.

label: posterior glossal sclerite
Defs: The sclerite of the posterior glossal plate that is paired.

label: abdominal sternum 2
Defs: The abdominal sternum that is located on abdominal segment 2.

label: submedial flange of occipital carina
Defs: The flange that is submedial and is on the occipital carina.

label: tentorium
Defs: The apodeme that has its sites of origin marked by the anterior and posterior tentorial pits and gular sulci.

label: photosensitivity
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to being sensitivity to the action of radiant energy.

label: brood viability
Defs: A reproductive quality inhering in the young of an animal by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to survive and develop normally.

label: increased duration
Defs: A duration quality of a process which is relatively high.

label: antennal scrobe
Defs: The scrobe that is located dorsally of the antennal foramen and is for the reception of the antenna.

label: chalaza
Defs: The seta that is located on a process.

label: rate of occurence
Defs: The number of repeated events per unit time, occurring in a repeating series. (e.g. the number of heart beats occurring over 1 minute)

label: sequentially ordered entity
Defs: Any entity that is ordered in discrete units along a linear axis.

label: prism shaped
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s resembling a prism.

label: subtorular carina
Defs: The carina that extends ventrally from the lateral margin of the antennal rim.

label: procuticle
Defs: The cuticle that containes chitin fibrils and is located between the Schmidt\'s layer and the epicuticle.

label: homeostatic
Defs: Pertaining to the ability or tendency of an organism or cell to maintain internal equilibrium by adjusting its physiological processes.

label: scaly
Defs: A texture quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being covered or partially covered with scales.

label: anterior flange of the first valvifer
Defs: The flange that extends anteriorly on the first valvifer and overlaps with the posterior margin of the anterior area of the second valvifer.

label: anterior scutellum
Defs: The area that is located anteriorly on the mesoscutellum and is delimited posteriorly by a the frenal line.

label: mandibular muscle
Defs: The head muscle that inserts on the mandible.

label: head length
Defs: The median anatomical line of the head in dorsal view.

label: submarginal carina of abdominal tergite
Defs: The carina that extends laterally on the abdominal tergite.

label: posterior mesoscutellar ridge
Defs: The ridge that delimits posteriorly the pulsatory organ of the mesoscutellum.

label: anterior propodeal projection
Defs: The projection that is located submedially on the anterior margin of the propodeum.

label: normal solubility
Defs: A solubility which is relatively normal or average

label: split medially
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being split along the median axis.

label: convex 3-D shape
Defs: A complete three dimensional shape in which for every line connecting pair of points on the object is within the object. Or: a shape lacking cavities. Contrast: concave.

label: condyle
Defs: The articular surface that is convex and is inserted into the fossa of an adjacent sclerite.

label: filamentous
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having thin filamentous extensions at its edge.

label: ventral vertical lobe of the propleuron
Defs: The area that is limited dorsally (anteriorly) by the ventral edge of the propleuron.

label: magnetism
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to exert an attractive or repulsive force on other entities.

label: second sterno-metacoxal muscle
Defs: The metacoxal muscle that arises from the second abdominal sternum.

label: flexible
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s ability of being turned, bowed, or twisted without breaking.

label: frontal lobe
Defs: The flange that is located on the frontal carina and obscures the antennal foramen.

label: pseudohermaphrodite
Defs: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population by virtue of having internal reproductive organs of one sex and external sexual characteristics of the other sex.

label: confluent with
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer flowing or coming together with another entity.

label: row of setae
Defs: The row that is composed of setae.

label: hind wing base
Defs: The wing base that is located in the hind wing.

label: S7
Defs: The sternite that is connected to the first valvula via muscles.

label: second lateral area
Defs: The area of propodeal-metapectal complex that is posterior to the first lateral area and medial to the lateral longitudinal carina.

label: abscissa
Defs: The wing vein that is delimited by its intersection with two other abscissae.

label: obtuse
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being roundish, a little inclining to be oblong.

label: venter
Defs: The area that is located between the left and right coxal foramina.

label: upper face
Defs: The area that is located dorsally of the ventral margin of the antennal rim and ventrally of the anterior ocellus medial to the inner margins of the eye and malar line.

label: moderate increased temperature
Defs: A temperature which is increased by a medium degree.

label: decreased behavioural activity
Defs: A behavioral quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting reduced activity.

label: wholly anterioralized
Defs: An anterioralized quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s gross morphology containing only what are normally anterior structures.

label: larval
Defs: A maturity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s indirect development, undergoing metamorphosis.

label: dilator muscle of the 3rd abdominal spiracle
Defs: The spiracular muscle that arises from the lateral sternal apodeme of the abdominal sternum 3 and inserts on the 3rd abdominal spiracle.

label: mesotibial spur
Defs: The tibial spur that is located on the mesotibia.

label: serial number
Defs: A serial number is an information content entity which is a unique sequence of characters borne by part of manufactured product or its packaging that is assigned to each individual in some class of products, and so can serve as a way to identify an individual product within the class. Serial numbers can be encoded in a variety of other information objects, such as bar codes, numerals, or patterns of dots.

label: stipital fossa of the cardo
Defs: The fossa that articulates with the basistipital process.

label: Distal mesal projection of cardo
Defs: The corner that is located medially on the distal margin of the cardo.

label: mesopleuron
Defs: The pleuron that is located in the mesothorax.

label: mesopleuron
Defs: The area that is located laterally of the mesodiscrimen.

label: decreased position
Defs: A positional which is relatively low.

label: potable
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being suitable for use as a safe means of hydration.

label: normal tendency
Defs: A tendency which is relatively normal or average

label: mineralized
Defs: A composition quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being composed of or possessing inorganic material.

label: separated from
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s not being in contact with another entity, or of no longer being connected or joined with another entity.

label: acrosternite 9
Defs: The acrosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 9.

label: mesotibial outer spur
Defs: The mesotibial spur that is located posteriorly on the distal margin of the mesotibia.

label: binucleate
Defs: A nucleate quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having two nuclei.

label: articular membrane
Defs: The conjunctiva that is located between two articulating sclerite.

label: prepectal carina
Defs: The carina that divides the prepectus for the vertical lateral portion and the horizontal, ventral prepectal shelf.

label: dorsal metapleural area
Defs: The area that is delimited posterodorsally by the metapleural carina and anteroventrally by the metapleural sulcus.

label: apical peg
Defs: The peg-shaped sensillum that is apical on the apicalmost sclerite of the labial palp.

label: normal fragility
Defs: A fragility which is relatively normal or average.

label: pronotal lobe
Defs: The area that is located dorsally on the posterior margin of the pronotum and overlaps the anterior thoracic spiracle.

label: ventro-lateral region
Defs: Anatomical region that overlaps the ventral and lateral regions of a body or body part.

label: wing base
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of the pteralia, humeral complex, tegula and axillary cord.

label: posterior cranio-mandibular muscle
Defs: The mandibular muscle that arises posterolaterally from the cranium and inserts on the tendon attached posteroproximal part of the mandible.

label: data about an ontology part
Defs: Data about an ontology part is a data item about a part of an ontology, for example a term

label: angle
Defs: An orientation inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s placement at an angle.

label: dark yellow
Defs: A color consisting of yellow hue and low brightness.

label: increased size
Defs: A size quality which is relatively high.

label: flexor of the pretarsal claws of the hind leg
Defs: The intrinsic leg muscle that arises from the metafemoro-metatibial joint and inserts on the unguitractor plate of the metatarsus.

label: metacoxo-metasubalar muscle
Defs: The metasubalare muscle that arises from the metacoxa and inserts on the metasubalare.

label: mid leg
Defs: The leg that is located on the mesothorax.

label: sclerite
Defs: The area of the cuticle that is less flexible than adjacent conjunctivae.

label: calcified
Defs: A composition quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being encrusted or impregnated with calcium carbonate (CHEBI:3311).

label: semicircular
Defs: A 2-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having shape or form of half a circle.

label: ridge
Defs: The apodeme that is elongate.

label: cell component
Defs: Anatomical structure that is a direct part of the cell.

label: profound intensity
Defs: An intensity which is characterized by being very severe.

label: genuflexor plate of the fore leg
Defs: The genuflexor plate that is located in the fore leg.

label: salivary gland
Defs: The gland that empties anterior to the prementum.

label: cervical apodeme
Defs: The apodeme that is located posteriorly of and continuous with the cervical prominence and corresponds to the site of insertion of laterocervical muscles.

label: second tarsomere
Defs: The tarsomere that is distal to the basitarsus and proximal to the third tarsomere.

label: third intrinsic muscle of the maxillary palp
Defs: The muscle that arises from the second sclerite of the maxillary palp and inserts on the third sclerite of the maxillary palp.

label: decreased propagation velocity
Defs: A propagation velocity that is lower than normal.

label: basophilic
Defs: An affinity inhering in a tissue constituent by virtue of the bearer exhibiting a molecular interaction for basic dyes under specific ph conditions.

label: transverse carina on T2
Defs: The carina that delimits the anterior vertical area of T2 from the posterior horizontal area.

label: axillar depression
Defs: The area that is located lateral to the mesoscutellar disc and is delimited posterolaterally by the mesoscutellar arm and anterolaterally by the scutoscutellar sulcus.

label: semi-viable
Defs: A viability quality inhering in a population by virtue of some of it\'s members\' ability to survive.

label: lateral surface

label: sequence bearer

Defs: A specialized eukaryotic organelle that consists of a filiform extrusion of the cell surface and of some cytoplasmic parts. Each cilium is largely bounded by an extrusion of the cytoplasmic (plasma) membrane, and contains a regular longitudinal array of microtubules, anchored to a basal body.

label: normal virulence

label: external angle

label: mesopleural epicoxal sulcus

label: proportionality to
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s magnitude in respect to a related entity.

label: obsolete2_report figure

label: irregular rhythm

label: frontal carina line

label: maroon

label: clypeal process

label: frenum

label: metapleuron

label: obo basic subset ontology module
Defs:
A subset ontology that is designed for basic applications to continue to make certain simplifying assumptions; many of these simplifying assumptions were based on the initial version of the Gene Ontology, and have become enshrined in many popular and useful tools such as term enrichment tools.

Examples of such assumptions include: traversing the ontology graph ignoring relationship types using a naive algorithm will not lead to cycles (i.e. the ontology is a DAG); every referenced term is declared in the ontology (i.e. there are no dangling clauses).

An ontology is OBO Basic if and only if it has the following characteristics:
DAG
Unidirectional
No Dangling Clauses
Fully Asserted
Fully Labeled
No equivalence axioms
Singly labeled edges
No qualifier lists
No disjointness axioms
No owl-axioms header
No imports

label: parallelogram
Defs:
A convex quadrilateral is a parallelogram if and only if any one of the following statements are true:
1. Each diagonal divides the quadrilateral into two congruent triangles with the same orientation.
2. The opposite sides are congruent in pairs.
3. The diagonals bisect each other.
4. The opposite angles are congruent in pairs.
5. The sum of the squares of the sides equals the sum of the squares of the diagonals. (This is the parallelogram law)
6.It possesses rotational symmetry.
7.One pair of opposite sides are parallel and congruent.
8.Two pairs of adjacent angles are supplementary.

label: basal surface

Defs: A lot number is an information content entity which is an identical sequence of character borne by part of manufactured product or its packaging for each instances of a product class in a discrete batch of an item. Manufacturing as a lot might be due to a variety of reasons, for example,  a single process during which many individuals are made from the same portion of source material. Defs: An increase in humidity.

label: transformed to
Defs: A morphological quality between two bearers inhering that one bearer is subject to change the nature, function, or condition of itself to become the other.

label: hypoproct
Defs: The area that is located in between the anal opening and the genitalia.

label: dorsal axillar area
Defs: The area that is located medially on the axilla and is delimited laterally by the axillar carina and posteromedially by scutoscutellar sulcus.

label: normal elasticity
Defs: An elasticity which is relatively normal or average.

label: postepomial sulcus
Defs: The sulcus along the dorsal margin of the transverse pronotal carina that is posterior to the epomial carina and ventral to the pronotal suprahumeral sulcus

label: abdominal mediotergite 6
Defs: The mediotergite that is located on the abdominal tergum 6.

label: galeal midrib
Defs: The carina that extends medially along the medial wall of the galeo-lacinial complex and that is longitudinal.

label: cuspidate
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being tapering gradually into a rigid point.

label: pronoto-mesobasalar muscle
Defs: The mesobasalar muscle that originates from the posterolateral part of the pronotum and inserts on the mesobasalare.

label: frontal sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that is transverse and extends just ventrally of the median ocellus and is never connected to the scrobal sulcus or depression or interantennal area.

label: metanotal spine
Defs: The median process on the metascutellum.

label: posterior T9-second valvifer muscle
Defs: The ovipositor muscle that arises medially from the posterodorsal part of female T9 and inserts on the median bridge of the second valvifers.

label: epicnemial pit
Defs: The cuticular invagination that is located at the lateral end of the epicnemial carina.

label: outer carina of the mandible
Defs: The carina that is longitudinal and extends anteriorly on the lateral surface of the mandible.

label: odorous
Defs: An odor quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having odour.

label: metatibio-metabasitarsal joint
Defs: The monocondylic joint that is composed of the metatibia, the metabasitarsus and the articular membrane of the metatibio-metabasitarsal joint.

label: precoxal sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that corresponds to the transepisternal line.

label: horizontal
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being in the plane of the horizon.

label: ventro-lateral margin
Defs: Anatomical margin that is located on the ventro-lateral region of the body or body part.

label: distolateral premental incision
Defs: The concavity on the distal margin of the prementum delimiting medially the site of attachment of the labial palp.

label: pteralia of the fore wing
Defs: The pteralia that is located on the fore wing.

label: anterior notch of the dorsal valve
Defs: The notch that is on the anterior region of the dorsal valve and accommodates the ventral ramus of the second valvula and the first valvula.

label: variable color
Defs: A color quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being uneven in color.

label: pharyngeal muscle
Defs: The head muscle that inserts on the pharynx.

label: median flange of occipital carina
Defs: The flange that is median and on the occipital carina.

label: basalar apodeme
Defs: The cup-shaped, sclerotised region et the apical portion of the tendon of the basalare that serves as the site of origin of the basalare muscles.

label: posterior ocellar line
Defs: The anatomical line that is the shortest between the margin of the lateral ocelli.

label: hyperoccipital carina
Defs: The carina that extends on the vertex between the outer orbits.

label: midsagittal plane
Defs: Sagittal plane that divides bilateral body into equal left and right parts.

label: repetitive
Defs: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s marked by tedious repetition.

label: reflectivity
Defs: A radiation reflective quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the ratio of the energy of a wave reflected from its surface to the energy possessed by the wave striking the bearer\'s surface.

label: mouth margin
Defs: The edge that is located on the cranium along the oral foramen.

label: case report textual entity
Defs: A textual entity that expresses a detailed account of a portion of the medical history for a specific patient.

label: epomial carina
Defs: The carina that is vertical, crosses the pronotum and separates the lateral pronotal area from the median pronotal area.

label: thoracic sternum
Defs: The sternum that is located on a thoracic segment.

label: organized
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting organisation.

label: netrion sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that  anteriorly delimits the netrion.

label: behavioural activity
Defs: A behavioral quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to exhibit marked activity.

label: abdominal sternum 9
Defs: The abdominal sternum that is located on abdominal segment 9.

label: movement quality
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s participation in movement.

label: terminal
Defs: A position quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s forming the end of another entity.

label: coordination
Defs: A behavioral quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having or lacking skillful and effective interaction of movement.

label: petiole neck
Defs: The anterior area of the petiole that is narrower than the posterior region in dorsal view.

label: precoxal carina
Defs: The carina that corresponds to the transepisternal line.

label: mesofurco-metabasalar muscle
Defs: The metabasalar muscle that originates from the mesofurca and inserts on the metabasalare.

label: sensillar plate of the aedeagus
Defs: The distal region of the aedeagus that is flat (delimited by an edge from the rest of the aedeagus) and bears four sensillum basiconicum.

label: supraclypeal area
Defs: The area that is located medially on the lower face between the dorsal margin of the clypeus and the anatomical line that connects the dorsalmost points of the left and right antennal rims.

label: 4th abdominal spiracle
Defs: The abdominal spiracle that is located in the abdominal segment 4.

label: dorsomedian apodeme of the aedeagus
Defs: The apodeme that is median and is oriented proximally.

label: cardo
Defs: The cardo that is a sclerite.

label: adult abdomen
Defs: The abdomen that is part of the adult.

label: scutellar plate
Defs: The area that is located medially on the mesoscutellum, flat and surrounds the scutellar midpit.

label: normal process quality
Defs: A quality of aprocess that has a value that is normal or average.

label: cranial condyle
Defs: The condyle that is located on the cranium.

label: epimeron
Defs: The area that is located on the pleuron and is delimited anteriorly by the pleural sulcus.

label: propleuron
Defs: The pleuron that is articulated with the fore leg, connected dorsolaterally (anterolaterally) with the pronotum and ventrally (posteriorly) with the prosternum.

label: preoccipital furrow
Defs: The sulcus that arises medially from the anterior margin of the occipital carina and extends towards the anterior ocellus.

label: structured
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having distinct structure.

label: propodeal areola
Defs: The area on the propodeum that is median and is delimited laterally by the median longitudinal carina.

label: refractivity
Defs: A physical quality that inheres in propagating wave (light or sound) virtue of the bearer\'s change in direction when passing from one medium to another.

label: mediosternite 4
Defs: The mediosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 4.

label: vertical to
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located at a right angle relative to another entity and to the horizon.

label: dorsal flange of the second valvifer
Defs: The flange that extends on the dorsal margin of the second valvifer. Part of the ventral T9-second valvifer muscle attaches to the flange.

label: abdominal laterotergite 8
Defs: The laterotergite that is located on abdominal tergum 8.

label: emmision wavelength
Defs: The specific wavelength of light emitted by a fluorescent molecule, such as a labelled probe, upon absorption of light at the (higher) excitation wavelength.

label: scutellar bridge
Defs: The apodeme that originates from the scutoscutellar ridge and fuses with the posterior part of the mesoscutellum.

label: third sclerite of the labial palp
Defs: The sclerite that is ringlike and is connected distally to the second sclerite of the labial palp via conjunctiva and muscle.

label: medial tooth of the mandible
Defs: The apical tooth of mandible that is between the dorsal tooth of mandible and the lower tooth.

label: spongy
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s resembling a sponge in elasticity, absorbency, or porousness.

label: circumocular ridge
Defs: The ridge that extends along the margin of the compound eye and corresponds to the ocular suture.

label: dilator muscle of the 6th abdominal spiracle
Defs: The spiracular muscle that arises from the lateral spiracular apodeme of the abdominal sternum 6 and inserts on the 6th abdominal spiracle.

label: mesotrochantero-mesobasalar muscle
Defs: The mesobasalar muscle that arises from the mesotrochanter.

label: ventral bridge of the pronotum
Defs: The area that extends between the ventral ends of the netrion on opposite sides of the pronotum.

label: zygomorphic
Defs: A symmetry quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being capable of division into symmetrical halves by only one longitudinal plane passing through the axis.

label: decreased solubility
Defs: A solubility which is relatively low.

label: lateralized
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being moved or displaced to one side so as to make lateral.

label: eusternum
Defs: The sclerite that is located on the thoracic sternum posteriorly of the spinasternum.

label: netted
Defs: A color pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of bearer\'s being covered with reticulated lines of a different hue or degree of saturation.

label: activity (of a radionuclide)
Defs: A radiation quality inhering in a radioactive substance by virtue of its transformation (disintegration) rate.

label: maximum diameter
Defs: The diameter that is the longest.

label: mesofemoro-pretarsus of the mesotarsus muscle
Defs: The flexor of the pretarsal claws of the middle leg muscle that arises from the mesofemur.

label: median clypeal notch depth
Defs: The anatomical line that is between the distal clypeal line and the proximalmost point of the distal clypeal notch in frontal view.

label: objective specification
Defs: A directive information entity that describes an intended process endpoint. When part of a plan specification the concretization is realized in a planned process in which the bearer tries to effect the world so that the process endpoint is achieved.

label: metafurcal arm
Defs: The apodeme that arises ventromedially form the metapectus, extends towards the metapleural apodeme and corresponds to the site of origin of metacoxal and metatrochanteral muscles.

label: normal velocity
Defs: A velocity which is relatively normal or average

label: fibrillary
Defs: A composition quaity inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing of or pertaining to fibrils, or nanoscale fibers.

label: parossiculo-penisvalval muscle
Defs: The male genitalia muscle that arises from the proximal apex of the parossiculus and inserts on the medially on the penisvalva. The muscle inserts on the ergot if present.

label: irregular duration
Defs: A duration quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s duration which has irregular start and/or end times.

label: cardinal direction
Defs: The four cardinal directions or cardinal points are the directions north, east, south, and west, commonly denoted by their initials, N, E, S, W. East and west are at right angles to north and south, with east being in the clockwise direction of rotation from north and west being directly opposite east.

label: metapleuron
Defs: The area of the metapectal-propodeal complex that is located anterior to the metapleural carina and the ventral propodeal carina and lateral to the metadiscrimen.

label: dorsal propodeal inflection
Defs: The inflection that extends along the dorsal margin of the propodeum and accommodates the metanotum.

label: anterior mesopleuro-mesofurcal muscle
Defs: The mesofurcal muscle that originates from the mesopleuron and inserts distally on the mesofurca.

label: pilosity
Defs: The anatomical cluster that is composed of setae.

label: median antecostal projection
Defs: The projection that extends over the median portion of the antecostal sulcus.

label: normal permeability
Defs: A permeability which is relatively normal or average.

label: pronoto-postoccipital muscle
Defs: The postoccipital muscle that arises from the pronotum and inserts on the postocciput.

label: decreased volume
Defs: A volume which is relatively low.

label: superelliptic
Defs: A shape constituting a transition between a rectangle and a circle; a closed curve, of which the circle and ellipse are special cases, whose parametric equation is x = a.cos2/rt, y = b.cos2/rt

label: wrinkled
Defs: A grooved texture quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being marked by one or more creases in a normally smooth surface.

label: ovariectomized female
Defs: A female fertility quality inhering in a female by virtue of the bearer\'s not being capable of reproducing because of surgical removal of ovaries.

label: posterior second valvifer-second valvula muscle
Defs: The ovipositor muscle that arises posteroventrally from the second valvifer and inserts on the processus musculares of the second valvula.

label: labrum
Defs: The sclerite that is situated along the distal margin of the clypeus and is connected along its proximal margin with the distal margin of the epipharyngeal wall.

label: aversion
Defs: A preference quality in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disliking a perceived stimulus.

label: obsolete pale grey
Defs: A color consisting of grey color and low saturation.

label: penisvalvo-gonossiculal muscle
Defs: The gonossiculal muscle that arises from the penisvalva.

label: multicellular
Defs: A cellularity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s consisting of more than one cell.

label: notaulus
Defs: The line that extends submedially along the mesoscutum and corresponds to the median border of the site of origin of the first mesopleuro-mesonotal muscle.

label: velocity
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s rate of change of the position.

label: sensitivity of a process to oxygen
Defs: A sensitivity of a process quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s unfolding in a location with or without oxygen.

label: realizable entity
Defs: A specifically dependent continuant  that inheres in continuant  entities and are not exhibited in full at every time in which it inheres in an entity or group of entities. The exhibition or actualization of a realizable entity is a particular manifestation, functioning or process that occurs under certain circumstances.

label: scaphoid
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being shaped like a boat.

label: has increased age-specific mortality rate
Defs: Then percentage of organisms in a population that die during some specified age range (age-specific mortality rate), minus the percentage that die in during the same age range in a wild-type population.

label: ipsilateral to
Defs: On the same side as. For example, the left arm is ipsilateral to the left leg.

label: disease has basis in feature
Defs: A relation that holds between the disease and a feature (a phenotype or other disease) where the physical basis of the disease is the feature.

label: immediately distal to
Defs: x immediately distal to y iff x distal to y and x is contiguous with y.

label: parallel to
Defs: x is parallel t y iff x and y are lines or planes which when extended indefinitely do not cross.

label: is start sequence of
Defs: inverse of has start sequence

label: is causal somatic mutation in
Defs: Relates a gene to condition, such that a mutation in this gene is sufficient to produce the condition but that cannot be passed on to offspring[modified from orphanet].

label: has synaptic IO throughout
Defs: A relationship between a neuron and a region, where the neuron has a functionally relevant number of input and/or output synapses distributed throughout that region (rather than confined to a subregion).

label: produces
Defs: a produces b if some process that occurs_in a has_output b, where a and b are material entities. Examples: hybridoma cell line produces monoclonal antibody reagent; chondroblast produces avascular GAG-rich matrix.

label: main stem of
Defs: x main_stem_of y if y is a branching structure and x is a channel that traces a linear path through y, such that x has higher capacity than any other such path.

label: in right side of
Defs: X in right side of Y <=> if Y is subdivided into two left and right portions, X is part of the right portion.

label: derives into
Defs: a relation between two distinct material entities, the old entity and the new entity, in which the new entity begins to exist when the old entity ceases to exist, and the new entity inherits the significant portion of the matter of the old entity

label: directly positively regulates activity of
Defs:
The entity A, immediately upstream of the entity B, has an activity that positively regulates an activity performed by B.
For example, A and B may be gene products and binding of B by A positively regulates the kinase activity of B.

label: in pseudoparalogy relationship with
Defs: Xenology that involves genes that ended up in a given genome as a result of a combination of vertical inheritance and horizontal gene transfer.

label: in orthology relationship with
Defs: Historical homology that involves genes that diverged after a speciation event.

label: contributes to severity of condition
Defs: A relationship between an entity (e.g. a genotype, genetic variation, chemical, or environmental exposure) and a condition (a phenotype or disease), where the entity influences the severity with which a condition manifests in an individual.

label: in homotopy relationship with
Defs: Structural homology that involves structures with the same or similar relative positions.

label: has eggs laid on by
Defs: inverse of lays eggs on

label: has_specified_output
Defs: A relation between a planned process and a continuant participating in that process. The presence of the continuant at the end of the process is explicitly specified in the objective specification which the process realizes the concretization of.

label: in deep part of
Defs: X superficial part of Y <=> if Y is subdivided into two superficial and deep portions, X is part of the deep portion.

label: synapsed_by_via_type_Ib_bouton
Defs: Relation between a muscle and a motor neuron that synapses to it via a type Ib bouton.

label: capable of upregulating or causing pathological process
Defs: Holds between a material entity c and a pathological process p if and only if c is capable of some activity a, where a negatively regulates p.

label: supplies
Defs: Relation between an arterial structure and another structure, where the arterial structure acts as a conduit channeling fluid, substance or energy.

label: in reversal relationship with
Defs: Homoplasy that involves phenotypes similar to those seen in ancestors within the lineage.

label: in gametology relationship with
Defs: Historical homology that involves not recombining and subsequently differentiated sex chromosomes.

label: has 2D boundary
Defs: a relation between a material entity and a 2D immaterial entity (the boundary), in which the boundary delimits the material entity

label: is causal germline mutation in
Defs: Relates a gene to condition, such that a mutation in this gene is sufficient to produce the condition and that can be passed on to offspring[modified from orphanet].

label: indirectly regulates activity of
Defs: The entity A is not immediately upstream of the entity B but A has an activity that regulates an activity performed by B.

label: is about
Defs: A (currently) primitive relation that relates an information artifact to an entity.

label: in protein structural homology relationship with
Defs: Structural homology that is detected at the level of the 3D protein structure, but maybe not at the level of the amino acid sequence.

label: has part that occurs in
Defs: p has part that occurs in c if and only if there exists some p1, such that p has_part p1, and p1 occurs in c.

label: directly develops from
Defs: Candidate definition: x directly_develops from y if and only if there exists some developmental process (GO:0032502) p such that x and y both participate in p, and x is the output of p and y is the input of p, and a substantial portion of the matter of x comes from y, and the start of x is coincident with or after the end of y.

label: is carrier of
Defs: *b* is carrier of *c* at time *t* if and only if *c* *g-depends on* *b* at *t*

label: quality of
Defs: a relation between a quality and an independent continuant (the bearer), in which the quality specifically depends on the bearer for its existence

label: has active ingredient
Defs: A relationship that holds between a substance and a chemical entity, if the chemical entity is part of the substance, and the chemical entity forms the biologically active component of the substance.

label: in biological homology relationship with
Defs: Homology that is defined by sharing of a set of developmental constraints, caused by locally acting self-regulatory mechanisms of differentiation, between individualized parts of the phenotype.

label: anterior to
Defs: x anterior to y iff x is further along the antero-posterior axis than y, towards the head. An antero-posterior axis is an axis that extends through an organism from head end to opposite end of body or tail.

label: has allergic trigger
Defs: A relation between a condition (a phenotype or disease) of a host and a material entity, in which the material entity is not part of the host, and is considered harmless to non-allergic hosts, and the condition results in pathological processes that include an abnormally strong immune response against the material entity.

label: in progenesis relationship with
Defs: Paedomorphosis that is produced by precocious sexual maturation of an organism still in a morphologically juvenile stage.

label: determined by part of
Defs: s \'determined by part of\' w if and only if there exists some f such that (1) s \'determined by\' f and (2) f part_of w, or f=w.

label: regulates activity of
Defs: The entity A has an activity that regulates an activity of the entity B. For example, A and B are gene products where the catalytic activity of A regulates the kinase activity of B.

label: directly regulates
Defs: Process(P1) directly regulates process(P2) iff: P1 regulates P2 via direct physical interaction between an agent executing P1 (or some part of P1) and an agent executing P2 (or some part of P2).  For example, if protein A has protein binding activity(P1) that targets protein B and this binding  regulates the kinase activity (P2) of protein B then P1 directly regulates P2.

label: in in-paralogy relationship with
Defs: Paralogy that results from a lineage-specific duplication subsequent to a given speciation event.

label: different_in_magnitude_relative_to
Defs: q1 different_in_magnitude_relative_to q2 if and only if magnitude(q1) NOT =~ magnitude(q2). Here, magnitude(q) is a function that maps a quality to a unit-invariant scale.

label: biotically interacts with
Defs: An interaction relationship in which at least one of the partners is an organism and the other is either an organism or an abiotic entity with which the organism interacts.

label: child nucleus of in hermaphrodite
Defs: A child nucleus relationship in which the cells are part of a hermaphroditic organism

label: expressed in
Defs: x expressed in y if and only if there is a gene expression process (GO:0010467) that occurs in y, and one of the following holds: (i) x is a gene, and x is transcribed into a transcript as part of the gene expression process (ii) x is a transcript, and the transcription of x is part of the gene expression process (iii) x is a mature gene product such as a protein, and x was translated or otherwise processes from a transcript that was transcribed as part of this gene expression process

label: has anatomical participant
Defs: p has anatomical participant c iff p has participant c, and c is an anatomical entity

label: has_cross_section
Defs: s3 has_cross_section s3 if and only if : there exists some 2d plane that intersects the bearer of s3, and the impression of s3 upon that plane has shape quality s2.

label: in deep homology relationship with
Defs: Homocracy that involves morphologically and phylogenetically disparate structures that are the result of parallel evolution.

label: is quality measurement of
Defs: m is a quality measurement of q at t. When q is a quality, there is a measurement process p that has specified output m, a measurement datum, that is about q

label: directly negatively regulates quantity of
Defs: The entity A has an activity that directly negatively regulates the quantity of B.

label: electrically_synapsed_to
Defs: A relation that holds between two neurons that are electrically coupled via gap junctions.

label: bounds sequence of
Defs: x bounds the sequence of y iff the upstream-most part of x is upstream of or coincident with the upstream-most part of y, and the downstream-most part of x is downstream of or coincident with the downstream-most part of y

label: has derived by descendant
Defs: inverse of derived by descent from

label: is autoimmune trigger for
Defs: A relation between a material entity and a condition (a phenotype or disease) of a host, in which the material entity is part of the host itself, and the condition results in pathological processes that include an abnormally strong immune response against the material entity.

label: determines
Defs: inverse of determined by

label: skeleton of
Defs: inverse of has skeleton

label: proper tributary of
Defs: x proper_tributary_of y iff x tributary_of y and x does not originate from y

label: in many to many homology relationship with
Defs: Historical homology that involves two members of a larger set of homologs.

label: ectoparasite of
Defs: A sub-relation of parasite-of in which the parasite lives on or in the integumental system of the host

label: synapsed_by_via_type_III_bouton
Defs: Relation between a muscle and a motor neuron that synapses to it via a type III bouton.

label: has model
Defs: Inverse of is-model-of

label: has symptom
Defs: A relation that holds between a disease or an organism and a phenotype

label: ubiquitously expressed in
Defs: x is ubiquitously expressed in y if and only if x is expressed in y, and the majority of cells in y express x

label: surrounds
Defs: inverse of surrounded by

label: existence ends with
Defs: x existence ends with y if and only if the time point at which x ends is equivalent to the time point at which y ends. Formally: x existence ends with y iff ω(x) = ω(y).

label: ameliorates condition
Defs: A relationship between an entity (e.g. a genotype, genetic variation, chemical, or environmental exposure) and a condition (a phenotype or disease), where the presence of the entity reduces or eliminates some or all aspects of the condition.

label: in branching relationship with
Defs: A relationship that holds between two material entities in a system of connected structures, where the branching relationship holds based on properties of the connecting network.

label: has prototype
Defs: x has prototype y if and only if x is an instance of C and y is a prototypical instance of C. For example, every instance of heart, both normal and abnormal is related by the has prototype relation to some instance of a "canonical" heart, which participates in blood circulation.

label: results in organization of
Defs: p results in organization of c iff p results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of c

label: in hypermorphosis relationship with
Defs: Peramorphosis that is produced by a delay in the offset of development.

label: indirectly negatively regulates quantity of
Defs: The entity A does not physically interact with the entity B, and A has an activity that down-regulates the quantity or abundance or concentration of B.

label: acts on population of
Defs: p acts on population of c iff c\' is a collection, has members of type c, and p has participant c

label: is causal susceptibility factor for
Defs: Relates a gene to condition, such that a mutation in this gene predisposes to the development of a condition  and that is necessary but not sufficient to develop the condition[modified from orphanet].

label: is consecutive sequence of
Defs: x is a consecutive sequence of y iff x has subsequence y, and all the parts of x are made of zero or more repetitions of y or sequences as the same type as y.

label: determined by
Defs: s determined by f if and only if s is a type of system, and f is a material entity that is part of s, such that f exerts a strong causal influence on the functioning of s, and the removal of f would cause the collapse of s.

label: results in transport to from or in
mentions
Defs: An information artifact IA mentions an entity E exactly when it has a component/part that denotes E

label: transitively provides input for
Defs: transitive form of directly_provides_input_for

label: has output
Defs: p has output c iff c is a participant in p, c is present at the end of p, and c is not present at the beginning of p.

label: has muscle antagonist
Defs: m1 has_muscle_antagonist m2 iff m1 has_muscle_insertion s, m2 has_muscle_insection s, m1 acts in opposition to m2, and m2 is responsible for returning the structure to its initial position.

label: transmitted by
Defs: A relationship that holds between a disease and organism

label: right of
Defs: Closer to the right side of the organism. Example: The dorsal fin is right of the left pectoral fin, but is left of the right eye. On the type level: X left of Y <=> every instance x of X is right of some instance y of Y, and there exists some organism o such that x part of o and y part of o.

label: has primary output
Defs: p has primary output c if (a) p has output c and (b) the goal of process is to modify, produce, or transform c.

label: has measurement datum
Defs: relates a time stamped measurement datum to the measurement datum that was measured

label: related via localization to
Defs: A relationship that holds via some process of localization

label: increased_in_magnitude_relative_to
Defs: q1 increased_in_magnitude_relative_to q2 if and only if magnitude(q1) > magnitude(q2). Here, magnitude(q) is a function that maps a quality to a unit-invariant scale.

label: results in development of
Defs: p \'results in development of\' c if and only if p is a developmental process and p results in the state of c changing from its initial state as a primordium or anlage through its mature state and to its final state.

label: in syntenic homology relationship with
Defs: Structural homology that is detected by similarity in content and organization between chromosomes.

label: derived from ancestral fusion of
Defs: x has_fused_element y iff: there exists some z : x has_part z, z homologous_to y, and y is a distinct element, the boundary between x and z is largely fiat

label: obligate parasite of
Defs: A sub-relation of parasite-of in which the parasite that cannot complete its life cycle without a host.

label: interacts with via parasite-host interaction
Defs: An interaction relationship between two organisms living together in more or less intimate association in a relationship in which association is disadvantageous or destructive to one of the organisms (GO).

label: in postdisplacement relationship with
Defs: Paedomorphosis that is produced by delayed growth of immature structures into the adult form.

label: realized in response to stimulus
Defs: A relationship between a realizable entity R (e.g. function or disposition) and a material entity M where R is realized in response to a process that has an input stimulus of M.

label: is marker for
Defs: c is marker for d iff the presence or occurrence of d is correlated with the presence of occurrence of c, and the observation of c is used to infer the presence or occurrence of d. Note that this does not imply that c and d are in a direct causal relationship, as it may be the case that there is a third entity e that stands in a direct causal relationship with c and d.

label: sequentially adjacent to
Defs: x is sequentially adjacent to y iff x and y do not overlap and if there are no base units intervening between x and y

label: inversely_associated_with
Defs: q1 inversely_associated_with q2 iff q1 is dependent on q2, and the magnitude of q1 decreases if the magnitude of q2 is increased, or the magnitude of q1 increases if the magnitude of q2 is decreased. The relationship is not necessarily linear.

label: has primary input or output
Defs: p \'has primary input ot output\' c iff either (a) p \'has primary input\' c or (b) p \'has primary output\' c.

label: obsolete downstream in neural circuit with
Defs: OBSOLETE A relation that holds between a neuron that is synapsed_by another neuron or a neuron that is connected indirectly to another by a chain of neurons, each synapsed_by the next, in which the direction is from the last to the first.

label: has muscle insertion
Defs: m has_muscle_insertion s iff m is attaches_to s, and it is the case that when m contracts, s moves. Insertions are usually connections of muscle via tendon to bone.

label: ventral to
Defs: x ventral to y iff x is further along the dorso-ventral axis than y, towards the front. A dorso-ventral axis is an axis that extends through an organism from back (e.g. spinal column) to front (e.g. belly).

label: ubiquitinates
Defs: An interaction relation between x and y in which x catalyzes a reaction in which one or more ubiquitin groups are added to y

label: is evidence for
Defs:
A relationship between a piece of evidence a and some entity b, where b is  an information content entity, material entity or process, and
the a supports either the existence of b, or the truth value of b.

label: is substance that treats
Defs: c is a substance that treats d if c is a material entity (such as a small molecule or compound) and d is a pathological process, phenotype or disease, and c is capable of some activity that negative regulates or decreases the magnitude of d.

label: is upstream of sequence of
Defs: inverse of downstream of sequence of

label: has exposure stressor
Defs: A broad relationship between an exposure event or process and any agent, stimulus, activity, or event that causes stress or tension on an organism and interacts with an exposure receptor during an exposure event.

label: has autoimmune trigger
Defs: A relation between a condition (a phenotype or disease) of a host and a material entity, in which the material entity is part of the host itself, and the condition results in pathological processes that include an abnormally strong immune response against the material entity.

label: causally downstream of
Defs: inverse of upstream of

label: receives synaptic input throughout
Defs: A relationship between a neuron and a region, where the neuron has a functionally relevant number of input synapses distributed throughout that region (rather than confined to a subregion).

label: participates in
Defs: a relation between a continuant and a process, in which the continuant is somehow involved in the process

label: directly positively regulated by
Defs: Process(P2) is directly postively regulated by process(P1) iff: P1 positively regulates P2 via direct physical interaction between an agent executing P1 (or some part of P1) and an agent executing P2 (or some part of P2).  For example, if protein A has protein binding activity(P1) that targets protein B and this binding positively regulates the kinase activity (P2) of protein B then P2 is directly postively regulated by P1.

label: acts upstream of, negative effect
Defs: c \'acts upstream of, negative effect\' p if c is enables f, and f is causally upstream of p, and the direction of f is negative

label: epiphyte of
Defs: An interaction relationship wherein a plant or algae is living on the outside surface of another plant.

label: disease has basis in disruption of
Defs: A relation that holds between the disease and a process where the physical basis of the disease disrupts execution of a key biological process.

label: preceded by
Defs: x is preceded by y if and only if the time point at which y ends is before or equivalent to the time point at which x starts. Formally: x preceded by y iff ω(y) <= α(x), where α is a function that maps a process to a start point, and ω is a function that maps a process to an end point.

label: innervates
Defs:
Relation between a \'neuron projection bundle\' and a region in which one or more of its component neuron projections either synapses to targets or receives synaptic input.
T innervates some R
Expands_to: T has_fasciculating_neuron_projection that synapse_in some R.

label: reciprocal_of
Defs: q1 reciprocal_of q2 if and only if : q1 and q2 are relational qualities and a phenotype e q1 e2 mutually implies a phenotype e2 q2 e.

label: location of
Defs: a relation between two independent continuants, the location and the target, in which the target is entirely within the location

label: has primary substance added
Defs: \'has primary substance added\' indicates that an entity has had the given substance added to it in a proportion greater than any other added substance.

label: in 1 to many homology relationship with
Defs: Historical homology that involves a structure that has no other homologs in the species in which it is defined, and several homologous structures in another species.

label: ribosomal translation of
Defs: x is the ribosomal translation of y if and only if a ribosome reads x through a series of triplet codon-amino acid adaptor activities (GO:0030533) and produces y

label: branching part of
Defs: x is a branching part of y if and only if x is part of y and x is connected directly or indirectly to the main stem of y

label: has target end location
Defs: This relationship holds between p and l when p is a transport or localization process in which the outcome is to move some cargo c from a an initial location to some destination l.

label: results in morphogenesis of
Defs: The relationship that links an entity with the process that results in the formation and shaping of that entity over time from an immature to a mature state.

label: acts upstream of, positive effect
Defs: c \'acts upstream of, positive effect\' p if c is enables f, and f is causally upstream of p, and the direction of f is positive

label: in non functional homology relationship with
Defs: Structural homology that involves a pseudogenic feature and its functional ancestor.

label: regulates
Defs: process(P1) regulates process(P2) iff: P1 results in the initiation or termination of P2 OR affects the frequency of its initiation or termination OR affects the magnitude or rate of output of P2.

label: mutualistically interacts with
Defs: An interaction relationship between two organisms living together in more or less intimate association in a relationship in which both organisms benefit from each other (GO).

label: in synology relationship with
Defs: Xenology that results, not from the transfer of a gene between two species, but from a hybridization of two species.

label: fasciculates with
Defs: relationship between a neuron and a neuron projection bundle (e.g.- tract or nerve bundle) that one or more of its projections travels through.

label: in superficial part of
Defs: X superficial part of Y <=> if Y is subdivided into two superficial and deep portions, X is part of the superficial portion.

label: gene product of
Defs: definition "x has gene product of y if and only if y is a gene (SO:0000704) that participates in some gene expression process (GO:0010467) where the output of that process is either y or something that is ribosomally translated from x"

label: spatially disjoint from
Defs: A is spatially_disjoint_from B if and only if they have no parts in common

label: indirectly positively regulates activity of
Defs: The entity A is not immediately upstream of the entity B and has an activity that up-regulates an activity performed by B.

label: in hemiplasy relationship with
Defs: Historical homology that is characterized by topological discordance between a gene tree and a species tree attributable to the phylogenetic sorting of genetic polymorphisms across successive nodes in a species tree.

label: regulates quantity of
Defs: The entity A has an activity that regulates the quantity or abundance or concentration of the entity B.

label: obsolete_specifically denotes
Defs:
c specifically denotes r =def
r is a portion of reality
& c is a particular quality
& c depends specifically on some independent continuant b
& b acquired c as the result of the achievement of an objective to enable pointing to r repeatedly.

Marked means there is a changed or additional quality of the bearer - the  quality is the information carrier.

Case 1
Memory trace as mark created when reading some description of some friend. The trace can denote.

Case 2
Pattern of ink arrayed on paper as mark when writing down a friend\'s name

Case 3
Pattern of magnetic domains on scattered pieces of a hard disk platter as mark when saving a file.

label: has branching part
Defs: inverse of branching part of

label: in paedomorphorsis relationship with
Defs: Heterochronous homology that is produced by a retention in adults of a species of traits previously seen only in juveniles.

label: transcribed from
Defs: x is transcribed from y if and only if x is synthesized from template y

label: in iterative homology relationship with
Defs: Biological homology that involves parts of the same organism.

label: has direct input
Defs: p has direct input c iff c is a participant in p, c is present at the start of p, and the state of c is modified during p.

label: starts with
Defs: x starts with y if and only if x has part y and the time point at which x starts is equivalent to the time point at which y starts. Formally: α(y) = α(x) ∧ ω(y) < ω(x), where α is a function that maps a process to a start point, and ω is a function that maps a process to an end point.

label: approximately perpendicular to
Defs: Crosses at an angle that is 90 degrees, or close to 90 degrees. In any non-linear organism, the main axes are rarely perpendicular when taken through the organism as a whole.

label: obsolete actively participates in
Defs: OBSOLETE x actively participates in y if and only if x participates in y and x realizes some active role

label: contributes to morphology of
Defs: p contributes to morphology of w if and only if a change in the morphology of p entails a change in the morphology of w. Examples: every skull contributes to morphology of the head which it is a part of. Counter-example: nuclei do not generally contribute to the morphology of the cell they are part of, as they are buffered by cytoplasm.

label: in syngeny relationship with
Defs: Homocracy that involves recognizably corresponding characters that occurs in two or more taxa, or as a repeated unit within an individual.

label: child nucleus of in male
Defs: A child nucleus relationship in which the cells are part of a male organism

label: mereotopologically related to
Defs: A mereological relationship or a topological relationship

label: has exposure receptor
Defs: A broad relationship between an exposure event or process and any entity (e.g., an organism, organism population, or an organism part) that interacts with an exposure stimulus during the exposure event.

label: has negative regulatory component activity
Defs: A relationship that holds between a GO molecular function and a component of that molecular function that negatively regulates the activity of the whole.  More formally, A \'has regulatory component activity\' B iff :A and B are GO molecular functions (GO_0003674), A has_component B and A is negatively regulated by B.

label: in similarity relationship with
Defs: Relation between biological objects that resemble or are related to each other sufficiently to warrant a comparison.

label: has part structure that is capable of
Defs: s \'has part structure that is capable of\' p if and only if there exists some part x such that s \'has part\' x and x \'capable of\' p

label: indirectly negatively regulates activity of
Defs: The entity A is not immediately upstream of the entity B and has an activity that down-regulates an activity performed by B.

label: is treated by substance
Defs: Inverse of \'is substance that treats\'

label: has end location
Defs: x \'has end location\' y if and only if there exists some process z such that x \'ends with\' z and z \'occurs in\' y

label: in paramorphism relationship with
Defs: Iterative homology that involves two structures, one of which originated as a duplicate of the other and co-opted the expression of patterning genes of the ancestral structure.

label: has time stamp
Defs: relates a time stamped measurement datum to the time measurement datum that denotes the time when the measurement was taken

label: similar_in_magnitude_relative_to
Defs: q1 similar_in_magnitude_relative_to q2 if and only if magnitude(q1) =~ magnitude(q2). Here, magnitude(q) is a function that maps a quality to a unit-invariant scale.

label: capable of negatively regulating
Defs: Holds between c and p if and only if c is capable of some activity a, and a negatively regulates p.
