label: lays eggs on
Defs: An interaction relationship in which organism a lays eggs on the outside surface of organism b. Organism b is neither helped nor harmed in the process of egg laying or incubation.

label: disposition of
Defs: inverse of has disposition

label: molecularly interacts with
Defs: An interaction relationship in which the two partners are molecular entities that directly physically interact with each other for example via a stable binding interaction or a brief interaction during which one modifies the other.

label: contains process
Defs: [copied from inverse property \'occurs in\'] b occurs_in c =def b is a process and c is a material entity or immaterial entity& there exists a spatiotemporal region r and b occupies_spatiotemporal_region r.& forall(t) if b exists_at t then c exists_at t & there exist spatial regions s and s’ where & b spatially_projects_onto s at t& c is occupies_spatial_region s’ at t& s is a proper_continuant_part_of s’ at t

label: disease has location
Defs: A relationship between a disease and an anatomical entity where the disease has one or more features that are located in that entity.

label: immediately superficial to
Defs: x immediately superficial to y iff x superficial to y and x is contiguous with y.

label: is downstream of sequence of
Defs: x is downstream of the sequence of y iff either (1) x and y have sequence units, and all units of x are downstream of all units of y, or (2) x and y are sequence units, and x is either immediately downstream of y, or transitively downstream of y.

label: in plesiomorphy relationship with
Defs: Historical homology that is based on distant shared ancestry.

label: is small molecule regulator
Defs: a relation between a continuant and a process, in which the continuant is a small molecule that regulates the process

label: is immediately upstream of sequence of
Defs: inverse of immediately downstream of

label: dendrite synapsed in
Defs: Relation between a neuron and some structure  (e.g.- a brain region) in which its dendrite receives synaptic input.

label: has biological role
Defs: c has-biological-role r iff c has-role r and r is a biological role (CHEBI:24432)

label: proper distributary of
Defs: x proper_distributary_of y iff x distributary_of y and x does not flow back into y

label: is evidence with support from
Defs: A relationship between a piece of evidence and an entity that plays a role in supporting that evidence.

label: has start location
Defs: x \'has starts location\' y if and only if there exists some process z such that x \'starts with\' z and z \'occurs in\' y

label: in distal side of
Defs: x in distal side of y <=> if y is subdivided into two proximal and distal portions, y is part of the distal portion.

label: in homoeology relationship with
Defs: Synology that results from allopolyploidy.

label: has component
Defs: w \'has component\' p if w \'has part\' p and w is such that it can be directly disassembled into into n parts p, p2, p3, ..., pn, where these parts are of similar type.

label: disease has feature
Defs: A relationship between a disease and some feature of that disease, where the feature is either a phenotype or an isolated disease.

label: immediately proximal to
Defs: x immediately proximal to y iff x proximal to y and x is contiguous with y.

label: directly positively regulates quantity of
Defs: The entity A has an activity that directly positively regulates the quantity of B.

label: has small molecule inhibitor
Defs: a relation between a process and a continuant, in which the process is inhibited by the small molecule continuant

label: left of
Defs: Closer to the left side of the organism. Example: The dorsal fin is right of the left pectoral fin, but is left of the right eye. On the type level: X left of Y <=> every instance x of X is left of some instance y of Y, and there exists some organism o such that x part of o and y part of o.

label: in proximal side of
Defs: x in proximal side of y <=> if y is subdivided into two proximal and distal portions, y is part of the proximal portion.

label: surrounded by
Defs: x surrounded_by y if and only if (1) x is adjacent to y and for every region r that is adjacent to x, r overlaps y (2) the shared boundary between x and y occupies the majority of the outermost boundary of x

label: disease has inflammation site
Defs: A relationship between a disease and an anatomical entity where the disease is triggered by an inflammatory response to stimuli occurring in the anatomical entity

label: part of structure that is capable of
Defs: this relation holds between c and p when c is part of some c\', and c\' is capable of p.

label: in homoplasy relationship with
Defs: Similarity that results from independent evolution.

label: derived by descent from
Defs: d derived_by_descent_from a if d is specified by some genetic program that is sequence-inherited-from a genetic program that specifies a.

label: cell expresses
Defs: A relation that applies between a cell(c) and a gene(g) , where the process of \'transcription, DNA templated (GO_0006351)\' is occuring in in cell c and that process has input gene g.

label: in anterior side of
Defs: X anterior side of Y <=> if Y is subdivided into two anterior and posterior portions, X is part of the anterior portion.

label: has characteristic
Defs: a relation between an independent continuant (the bearer) and a specifically dependent continuant (the dependent), in which the dependent specifically depends on the bearer for its existence

label: indirectly regulates quantity of
Defs: The entity A is not immediately upstream of the entity B, but A has an activity that regulates the quantity or abundance or concentration of B.

label: has positive regulatory component activity
Defs: A relationship that holds between a GO molecular function and a component of that molecular function that positively regulates the activity of the whole.  More formally, A \'has regulatory component activity\' B iff :A and B are GO molecular functions (GO_0003674), A has_component B and A is positively regulated by B.

label: causally downstream of or within
Defs: inverse of causally upstream of or within

label: helper property (not for use in curation)
has habitat
Defs: x \'has habitat\' y if and only if: x is an organism, y is a habitat, and y can sustain and allow the growth of a population of xs.

label: in many to many orthology relationship with
Defs: Orthology that involves two genes that experienced duplications more recent than the species split that created them.

label: coincident with
Defs: A relation that holds between two linear structures that are approximately parallel to each other for their entire length and where either the two structures are adjacent to each other or one is part of the other.

label: participates in a biotic-biotic interaction with
has chemical role
Defs: c has-chemical-role r iff c has-role r and r is a chemical role (CHEBI:51086)

label: biomechanically related to
Defs: A relation that holds between elements of a musculoskeletal system or its analogs.

label: has input
Defs: p has input c iff: p is a process, c is a material entity, c is a participant in p, c is present at the start of p, and the state of c is modified during p.

label: has potential to develop into
Defs: x has the potential to develop into y iff x develops into y or if x is capable of developing into y

label: results in developmental progression of
Defs: p results in the developmental progression of s iff p is a developmental process and s is an anatomical structure and p causes s to undergo a change in state at some point along its natural developmental cycle (this cycle starts with its formation, through the mature structure, and ends with its loss).

label: directly negatively regulated by
Defs: Process(P2) is directly negatively regulated by process(P1) iff: P1 negatively regulates P2 via direct physical interaction between an agent executing P1 (or some part of P1) and an agent executing P2 (or some part of P2).  For example, if protein A has protein binding activity(P1) that targets protein B and this binding  negatively regulates the kinase activity (P2) of protein B then P2 directly negatively regulated by P1.

label: existence ends during or before
Defs: x existence ends during or before y if and only if the time point at which x ends is before or equivalent to the time point at which y ends.

label: develops in
Defs: x develops_in y if x is located in y whilst x is developing

label: directly regulates quantity of
Defs: The entity A, immediately upstream of B, has an activity that directly regulates the quantity of B.

label: has parasitoid
Defs: inverse of parasitoid of

label: under-expressed in
Defs: g is under-expressed in t iff g is expressed in t, and the expression level of g is decreased relative to some background.

label: has small molecule activator
Defs: a relation between a process and a continuant, in which the process is activated by the small molecule continuant

label: dorsal to
Defs: x dorsal to y iff x is further along the dorso-ventral axis than y, towards the back. A dorso-ventral axis is an axis that extends through an organism from back (e.g. spinal column) to front (e.g. belly).

label: destabilizes quantity of
Defs: An entity A directly interacts with B and A has an activity that decreases the amount of an entity B by degradating it.

label: bounding layer of
Defs:
X outer_layer_of Y iff:
. X :continuant that bearer_of some PATO:laminar
. X part_of Y
. exists Z :surface
. X has_boundary Z
. Z boundary_of Y

has_boundary: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002002
boundary_of: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002000

label: results in specification of
Defs: The relationship linking a cell and its participation in a process that results in the fate of the cell being specified. Once specification has taken place, a cell will be committed to differentiate down a specific pathway if left in its normal environment.

label: results in determination of
Defs: p \'results in determination of\' c if and only if p is a developmental process and c is a cell and p results in the state of c changing to be determined. Once a cell becomes determined, it becomes committed to differentiate down a particular pathway regardless of its environment.

label: transcribed to
Defs: inverse of transcribed from

label: in ohnology relationship with
Defs: Paralogy that results from a whole genome duplication event.

label: obsolete upstream in neural circuit with
Defs: OBSOLETE A relation that holds between a neuron that is synapsed_to another neuron or a neuron that is connected indirectly to another by a chain of neurons, each synapsed_to the next, in which the direction is from the last to the first.

label: involved in
Defs: c involved_in p if and only if c enables some process p\', and p\' is part of p

label: has muscle origin
Defs: m has_muscle_origin s iff m is attached_to s, and it is the case that when m contracts, s does not move. The site of the origin tends to be more proximal and have greater mass than what the other end attaches to.

label: develops from part of
Defs: x develops from part of y if and only if there exists some z such that x develops from z and z is part of y

label: commensually interacts with
Defs: An interaction relationship between two organisms living together in more or less intimate association in a relationship in which one benefits and the other is unaffected (GO).

label: causal relation between material entity and a process
Defs: A relationship that holds between a material entity and a process in which causality is involved, with either the material entity or some part of the material entity exerting some influence over the process, or the process influencing some aspect of the material entity.

label: interacts with
Defs: A relationship that holds between two entities in which the processes executed by the two entities are causally connected.

label: has soma location
Defs: Relation between a neuron and an anatomical structure that its soma is part of.

label: has developmental contribution from
Defs: x has developmental contribution from y iff x has some part z such that z develops from y

label: connected to
Defs: a is connected to b if and only if a and b are discrete structure, and there exists some connecting structure c, such that c connects a and b

label: developmentally related to
Defs: A relationship that holds between entities participating in some developmental process (GO:0032502)

label: in taxon
Defs: x is in taxon y if an only if y is an organism, and the relationship between x and y is one of: part of (reflexive), developmentally preceded by, derives from, secreted by, expressed.

label: does not overlap sequence of
Defs: x does not overlaps the sequence of x if and only if there is no z such that x has a subsequence z and z is a subsequence of y.

label: has subsequence
Defs: x has subsequence y iff all of the sequence parts of x are sequence parts of y

label: in ventral side of
Defs: X ventral side of Y <=> if Y is subdivided into two dorsal and ventral portions, X is part of the ventral portion.

label: directly negatively regulates
Defs: Process(P1) directly negatively regulates process(P2) iff: P1 negatively regulates P2 via direct physical interaction between an agent executing P1 (or some part of P1) and an agent executing P2 (or some part of P2).  For example, if protein A has protein binding activity(P1) that targets protein B and this binding  negatively regulates the kinase activity (P2) of protein B then P1 directly negatively regulates P2.

label: aboral to
Defs: nearer to the aboral opening of the organism, on the oral-aboral axis.

label: has potential to developmentally contribute to
Defs: x has potential to developmentrally contribute to y iff x developmentally contributes to y or x is capable of developmentally contributing to y

label: has presynaptic terminal in
Defs: Relation between a neuron and some structure (e.g.- a brain region) in which it receives (chemical) synaptic input.

label: has host
Defs: X \'has host\' y if and only if: x is an organism, y is an organism, and x can live on the surface of or within the body of y

label: genomically related to
Defs: holds between two entities when some genome-level process such as gene expression is involved. This includes transcriptional, spliceosomal events. These relations can be used between either macromolecule entities (such as regions of nucleic acid) or between their abstract informational counterparts.

label: in functional equivalence relationship with
Defs: Similarity that is characterized by interchangeability in function.

label: occurs across
Defs: A relationship between a process and a barrier, where the process occurs in a region spanning the barrier. For cellular processes the barrier is typically a membrane. Examples include transport across a membrane and membrane depolarization.

label: hyperparasite of
Defs: x is a hyperparasite of y iff x is a parasite of a parasite of the target organism y

label: exacerbates condition
Defs: A relationship between an entity (e.g. a chemical, environmental exposure, or some form of genetic variation) and a condition (a phenotype or disease), where the presence of the entity worsens some or all aspects of the condition.

label: starts
Defs: inverse of starts with

label: distributary of
Defs: x distributary_of y if and only if x is capable of channeling the flow of a substance to y, where y channels less of the substance than x

label: capable of part of
Defs: c stands in this relationship to p if and only if there exists some p\' such that c is capable_of p\', and p\' is part_of p.

label: has connecting branch
Defs: inverse of connecting branch of

label: synapsed_via_type_Is_bouton_to
Defs: A relation between a motor neuron and a muscle that it synapses to via a type Is bouton.

label: immediately ventral to
Defs: x immediately ventral to y iff x ventral to y and x is contiguous with y.

label: has exposure stimulus
Defs: A relationship between an exposure event or process and any agent, stimulus, activity, or event that causally effects an organism and interacts with an exposure receptor during an exposure event.

label: causally upstream of or within, negative effect
causal relation between processes
Defs: p is causally related to q if and only if p or any part of p and q or any part of q are linked by a chain of events where each event pair is one of direct activation or direct inhibition. p may be upstream, downstream, part of or a container of q.

label: is_specified_output_of
Defs: A relation between a planned process and a continuant participating in that process. The presence of the continuant at the end of the process is explicitly specified in the objective specification which the process realizes the concretization of.

label: acts upstream of or within, negative effect
connecting branch of
Defs: b connecting-branch-of s iff b is connected to s, and there exists some tree-like structure t such that the mereological sum of b plus s is either the same as t or a branching-part-of t.

label: obsolete related via dependence to
Defs: A relationship that holds between two entities, where the relationship holds based on the presence or absence of statistical dependence relationship. The entities may be statistical variables, or they may be other kinds of entities such as diseases, chemical entities or processes.

label: sequentially related to
Defs: A relation that holds between two entities that have the property of being sequences or having sequences.

label: indirectly activates
Defs: p indirectly activates q if and only if p is upstream of q and there is a chain of directly activates relationships connecting p and q, where the chain is of length greater than one.

label: synapsed to
Defs: Relation between a neuron and an anatomical structure (including cells) that it chemically synapses to.

label: has member
Defs: has member is a mereological relation between a collection and an item.

label: in heterochronous homology relationship with
Defs: Biological homology that is characterized by changes, over evolutionary time, in the rate or timing of developmental events of homologous structures.

label: co-roosts with
Defs: Two or more individuals sharing the same roost site (cave, mine, tree or tree hollow, animal burrow, leaf tent, rock crack, space in man-made structure, etc.). Individuals that are sharing a communal roost may be said to be co-roosting. The roost may be either a day roost where the individuals rest during daytime hours, or a night roost where individuals roost to feed, groom, or rest in between flights and/or foraging bouts.  Communal roosting as thus defined is an umbrella term within which different specialized types -- which are not mutually exclusive -- may be recognized based on taxonomy and the temporal and spatial relationships of the individuals that are co-roosting.

label: in latent homology relationship with
Defs: Parallelism that involves morphologically very similar structures, occurring only within some members of a taxon and absent in the common ancestor (which possessed the developmental basis to develop this character).

label: has regulatory component activity
Defs: A \'has regulatory component activity\' B if A and B are GO molecular functions (GO_0003674), A has_component B and A is regulated by B.

label: has_part
Defs: Q1 has_part Q2 if and only if: every instance of Q1 is a quality_of an entity that has_quality some Q2.

label: stabilizes quantity of
Defs: An entity A physically interacts with B and A has an activity that increases the amount of an entity B by stabilizing it.

label: located in
Defs: a relation between two independent continuants, the target and the location, in which the target is entirely within the location

label: sends synaptic output to
Defs: A relationship between a neuron and a region, where the neuron has a functionally relevant number of output synapses in that region.

label: derives from
Defs: a relation between two distinct material entities, the new entity and the old entity, in which the new entity begins to exist when the old entity ceases to exist, and the new entity inherits the significant portion of the matter of the old entity

label: in register with
existence overlaps
Defs: x existence overlaps y if and only if either (a) the start of x is part of y or (b) the end of x is part of y. Formally: x existence starts and ends during y iff (α(x) >= α(y) & α(x) <= ω(y)) OR (ω(x) <= ω(y) & ω(x) >= α(y))

label: has start point
Defs: A relation between an axis and a part of an organism, in which the part defines the initial point of the axis.

label: obsolete has active participant
Defs: x has participant y if and only if x realizes some active role that inheres in y

label: capable of regulating
Defs: Holds between c and p if and only if c is capable of some activity a, and a regulates p.

label: directly negatively regulates activity of
Defs:
The entity A, immediately upstream of the entity B, has an activity that negatively regulates an activity performed by B.
For example, A and B may be gene products and binding of B by A negatively regulates the kinase activity of B.

label: has disposition
Defs: a relation between an independent continuant (the bearer) and a disposition, in which the disposition specifically depends on the bearer for its existence

label: disease has basis in dysfunction of
Defs: A relation that holds between the disease and a material entity where the physical basis of the disease is a disorder of that material entity that affects its function.

label: superficial to
Defs: Near the outer surface of the organism. Thus, skin is superficial to the muscle layer.

label: ecologically related to
Defs: A relationship that is mediated in some way by the environment or environmental feature (ENVO:00002297)

label: attached to part of
Defs: a is attached to part of b if a is attached to b, or a is attached to some p, where p is part of b.

label: in homology relationship with
Defs: Similarity that results from common evolutionary origin.

label: related via exposure to
Defs: Any relationship between an exposure event or process and any other entity.

label: inheres in part of
Defs: q inheres in part of w if and only if there exists some p such that q inheres in p and p part of w.

label: results in catabolism of
Defs: p results in catabolism of c if and only if p is a catabolic process, and the execution of p results in c being broken into smaller parts with energy being released.

label: in within-species paralogy relationship with
Defs: Paralogy that involves genes from the same species.

label: is causal loss of function germline mutation of in
Defs: Relates a gene to condition, such that a mutation in this gene in a germ cell impairs the function of the corresponding product and that is sufficient to produce the condition and that can be passed on to offspring[modified from orphanet].

label: is immediately downstream of sequence of
Defs: x is immediately downstream of the sequence of y iff either (1) x and y have sequence units, and all units of x are downstream of all units of y, and x is sequentially adjacent to y, or (2) x and y are sequence units, in which case the immediately downstream relation is primitive and defined by context: for DNA bases, y would be adjacent and 5\' to y

label: increases expression of
Defs: Holds between entity A (a transcription factor) and nucleic acid B if and only if A up-regulates the expression of B. The nucleic acid can be a gene or mRNA.

label: in partial homology relationship with
Defs: Structural homology that involves complex structures from which only a fraction of the elements that can be isolated are separately homologous.

label: anabranch of
Defs: x anabranch_of y if x is a distributary of y (i.e. it channels a from a larger flow from y) and x ultimately channels the flow back into y.

label: deep to
Defs: Further away from the surface of the organism. Thus, the muscular layer is deep to the skin, but superficial to the intestines.

label: directly regulates activity of
Defs:
The entity A, immediately upstream of the entity B, has an activity that regulates an activity performed by B. For example, A and B may be gene products and binding of B by A regulates the kinase activity of B.

A and B can be physically interacting but not necessarily. Immediately upstream means there are no intermediate entity between A and B.

label: in tandem paralogy relationship with
Defs: Paralogy that is characterized by duplication of adjacent sequences on a chromosome segment.

label: synapsed by
Defs: Relation between an anatomical structure (including cells) and a neuron that chemically synapses to it.

label: immediately posterior to
Defs: x immediately posterior to y iff x posterior_to y and x is contiguous with y.

label: connects
Defs: c connects a if and only if there exist some b such that a and b are similar parts of the same system, and c connects b, specifically, c connects a with b. When one structure connects two others it unites some aspect of the function or role they play within the system.

label: develops from
Defs: x develops from y if and only if either (a) x directly develops from y or (b) there exists some z such that x directly develops from z and z develops from y

label: in historical homology relationship with
Defs: Homology that is defined by common descent.

label: denotes
Defs: A primitive, instance-level, relation obtaining between an information content entity and some portion of reality. Denotation is what happens when someone creates an information content entity E in order to specifically refer to something. The only relation between E and the thing is that E can be used to \'pick out\' the thing. This relation connects those two together. Freedictionary.com sense 3: To signify directly; refer to specifically

label: is end sequence of
Defs: inverse of has end sequence

label: orthogonal to
Defs: crossing at right angles

label: intersects midsagittal plane of
Defs: X intersects median plane of iff X crosses the midine plane of Y.

label: condition exacerbated by
Defs: A relationship between a condition (a phenotype or disease) and an entity (e.g. a chemical, environmental exposure, or some form of genetic variation) where some or all aspects of the condition are worsened by the presence of the entity.

label: 2D boundary of
Defs: a relation between a 2D immaterial entity (the boundary) and a material entity, in which the boundary delimits the material entity

label: in chromosomal homology relationship with
Defs: Historical homology that involves the chromosomes able to pair (synapse) during meiosis.

label: results in developmental induction of
Defs: p results in developmental induction of c if and only if p is a collection of cell-cell signaling processes that signal to a neighbouring tissue that is the precursor of the mature c, where the signaling results in the commitment to cell types necessary for the formation of c.

label: represses expression of
Defs: Holds between entity A (a transcription factor) and a nucleic acid B if and only if A down-regulates the expression of B. The nucleic acid can be a gene or an mRNA.

label: in peramorphosis relationship with
Defs: Heterochronous homology that is produced by a maturation of individuals of a species past adulthood, which take on hitherto unseen traits.

label: has application role
Defs: c has-application-role r iff c has-role r and r is an application role (CHEBI:33232)

label: is duration of
Defs: relates a process to a time-measurement-datum that represents the duration of the process

label: oral to
Defs: nearer to the oral opening of the organism, on the oral-aboral axis.

label: has potential to developmentally induce
Defs: x has potential to developmentally induce y iff x developmentally induces y or x is capable of developmentally inducing y

label: in interology relationship with
Defs: Historical homology that involves orthologous pairs of interacting molecules in different organisms.

label: contributes to condition
Defs: A relationship between an entity (e.g. a genotype, genetic variation, chemical, or environmental exposure) and a condition (a phenotype or disease), where the entity has some contributing role that influences the condition.

label: contralateral to
Defs: On the opposite side from. For example, the left arm is contralateral to the right arm (and the right leg).

label: has intercellular endoparasite
Defs: inverse of intercellular endoparasite of

label: child nucleus of
Defs: c is a child nucleus of d if and only if c and d are both nuclei and parts of cells c\' and d\', where c\' is derived from d\' by mitosis and the genetic material in c is a copy of the generic material in d

label: role of
Defs: a relation between a role and an independent continuant (the bearer), in which the role specifically depends on the bearer for its existence

label: over-expressed in
Defs: g is over-expressed in t iff g is expressed in t, and the expression level of g is increased relative to some background.

label: results in breakdown of
Defs: p results in breakdown of c if and only if the execution of p leads to c no longer being present at the end of p

label: has small molecule regulator
Defs: a relation between a process and a continuant, in which the process is regulated by the small molecule continuant

label: results in acquisition of features of
Defs: The relationship that links a specified entity with the process that results in an unspecified entity acquiring the features and characteristics of the specified entity

label: distal to
Defs: x distal to y iff x is further along the proximo-distal axis than y, towards the appendage tip. A proximo-distal axis extends from tip of an appendage (distal) to where it joins the body (proximal).

label: is allergic trigger for
Defs: A relation between a material entity and a condition (a phenotype or disease) of a host, in which the material entity is not part of the host, and is considered harmless to non-allergic hosts, and the condition results in pathological processes that include an abnormally strong immune response against the material entity.

label: causally upstream of or within, positive effect
produced by
Defs: a produced_by b iff some process that occurs_in b has_output a.

label: results in transport along
Defs: Holds between p and l when p is a transportation or localization process and the outcome of this process is to move c from one location to another, and the route taken by c follows a path that is aligned_with l

label: causally related to
Defs: This relation groups causal relations between material entities and causal relations between processes

label: in posterior side of
Defs: X posterior side of Y <=> if Y is subdivided into two anterior and posterior portions, X is part of the posterior portion.

label: has postsynaptic terminal in
Defs: Relation between a neuron and some structure (e.g.- a brain region) in which it receives (chemical) synaptic input.

label: existence ends during
Defs: x existence ends during y if and only if the time point at which x ends is before or equivalent to the time point at which y ends and after or equivalent to the point at which y starts. Formally: x existence ends during y iff ω(x) <= ω(y) and ω(x) >= α(y).

label: causes or contributes to condition
Defs: A relationship between an entity (e.g. a genotype, genetic variation, chemical, or environmental exposure) and a condition (a phenotype or disease), where the entity has some causal or contributing role that influences the condition.

label: creates habitat for
Defs: An interaction relationship wherein one organism creates a structure or environment that is lived in by another organism.

label: occurs in
Defs: b occurs_in c =def b is a process and c is a material entity or immaterial entity& there exists a spatiotemporal region r and b occupies_spatiotemporal_region r.& forall(t) if b exists_at t then c exists_at t & there exist spatial regions s and s’ where & b spatially_projects_onto s at t& c is occupies_spatial_region s’ at t& s is a proper_continuant_part_of s’ at t

label: passes through
Defs: Intersects at two points.

label: is small molecule inhibitor
Defs: a relation between a continuant and a process, in which the continuant is a small molecule that inhibits the process

label: in dorsal side of
Defs: X dorsal side of Y <=> if Y is subdivided into two dorsal and ventral portions, X is part of the dorsal portion.

label: has developmental potential involving
Defs: x has developmental potential involving y iff x is capable of a developmental process with output y. y may be the successor of x, or may be a different structure in the vicinity (as for example in the case of developmental induction).

label: related via evidence or inference to
existence starts and ends during
Defs: x exists during y if and only if: 1) the time point at which x begins to exist is after or equal to the time point at which y begins and 2) the time point at which x ceases to exist is before or equal to the point at which y ends. Formally: x existence starts and ends during y iff α(x) >= α(y) & α(x) <= ω(y) & ω(x) <= ω(y) & ω(x) >= α(y)

label: has role in modeling
Defs: A relation between a biological, experimental, or computational artifact and an entity it is used to study, in virtue of its replicating or approximating features of the studied entity.

label: involved in positive regulation of
Defs: c involved in regulation of p if c is involved in some p\' and p\' positively regulates some p

label: in between-species paralogy relationship with
Defs: Paralogy that involves genes from different species.

label: preys on
Defs: An interaction relationship involving a predation process, where the subject kills the target in order to eat it or to feed to siblings, offspring or group members

label: immediately deep to
Defs: x immediately deep to y iff x deep_to y and x is contiguous with y.

label: in apparent orthology relationship with
Defs: Between-species paralogy that involves single copy paralogs resulting from reciprocal gene loss.

label: parasitoid of
Defs: A parasite that kills or sterilizes its host

label: has synaptic IO in
Defs: A relationship between a neuron and a region, where the neuron has a functionally relevant number of input and/or output synapses in that region.

label: has material basis in loss of function germline mutation in
denoted by
Defs: inverse of the relation \'denotes\'

label: has ligand
Defs: A relationship that holds between between a receptor and an chemical entity, typically a small molecule or peptide, that carries information between cells or compartments of a cell and which binds the receptor and regulates its effector function.

label: in convergence relationship with
Defs: Homoplasy that involves different underlying mechanisms or structures.

label: ribosomally translates to
Defs: inverse of ribosomal translation of

label: is bound by sequence of
Defs: inverse of bounds sequence of

label: shares ancestor with
Defs: two individual entities d1 and d2 stand in a shares_ancestor_with relation if and only if there exists some a such that d1 derived_by_descent_from a and d2 derived_by_descent_from a.

label: directly provides input for
Defs: p1 directly provides input for p2 iff there exists some c such that p1 has_output c and p2 has_input c

label: in 1 to 1 orthology relationship with
Defs: Orthology that involves two genes that did not experience any duplication after the speciation event that created them.

label: hemiparasite of
Defs: A sub-relation of parasite-of in which the parasite is a plant, and the parasite is parasitic under natural conditions and is also photosynthetic to some degree. Hemiparasites may just obtain water and mineral nutrients from the host plant. Many obtain at least part of their organic nutrients from the host as well.

label: synapsed_by_via_type_Is_bouton
Defs: Relation between a muscle and a motor neuron that synapses to it via a type Is bouton.

label: positively regulated by
Defs: inverse of positively regulates

label: results in ending of
Defs: p results in the end of s if p results in a change of state in s whereby s either ceases to exist, or s becomes functionally impaired or s has its fate committed such that it is put on a path to be degraded.

label: in syntenic paralogy relationship with
Defs: Paralogy that involves sets of syntenic blocks.

label: tributary of
Defs: x tributary_of y if and only if x a channel for the flow of a substance into y, where y is larger than x. If x and y are hydrographic features, then y is the main stem of a river, or a lake or bay, but not the sea or ocean. If x and y are anatomical, then y is a vein.

label: ends
Defs: inverse of ends with

label: participates in a abiotic-biotic interaction with
Defs: A biotic interaction relationship in which one partner is an organism and the other partner is inorganic. For example, the relationship between a sponge and the substrate to which is it anchored.

label: indirectly positively regulates quantity of
Defs: The entity A does not physically interact with the entity B, and A has an activity that up-regulates the quantity or abundance or concentration of B.

label: synapsed_via_type_Ib_bouton_to
Defs: A relation between a motor neuron and a muscle that it synapses to via a type Ib bouton.

label: has consumer
Defs: \'has consumer\' is a relation between a material entity and an organism in which the former can normally be digested or otherwise absorbed by the latter without immediate or persistent ill effect.

label: causally upstream of
Defs: p is causally upstream of q if and only if p precedes q and p and q are linked in a causal chain

label: acts upstream of or within
Defs: c acts upstream of or within p if c is enables f, and f is causally upstream of or within p. c is a material entity and p is an process.

label: results in movement of
Defs: Holds between p and c when p is locomotion process and the outcome of this process is the change of location of c

label: stem parasite of
Defs: A parasite-of relationship in which the host is a plant and the parasite that attaches to the host stem (PO:0009047)

label: has skeleton
Defs: A relation between a segment or subdivision of an organism and the maximal subdivision of material entities that provides structural support for that segment or subdivision.

label: regulated by
Defs: inverse of regulates

label: in plerology relationship with
Defs: Paralogy that is characterized by extra similarity between paralogous sequences resulting from concerted evolution.

label: spatially coextensive with
Defs: x spatially_coextensive_with y if and inly if x and y have the same location

label: has effector activity
Defs: A \'has effector activity\' B if A and B are GO molecular functions (GO_0003674),  A \'has component activity\' B and B is the effector (output function) of B.  Each compound function has only one effector activity.

label: directly develops into
Defs: inverse of directly develops from

label: in paralogy relationship with
Defs: Historical homology that involves genes that diverged after a duplication event.

label: facultative parasite of
Defs: A sub-relations of parasite-of in which the parasite that can complete its life cycle independent of a host.

label: has plasma membrane part
Defs: Holds between a cell c and a protein complex or protein p if and only if that cell has as part a plasma_membrane[GO:0005886], and that plasma membrane has p as part.

label: has fasciculating neuron projection
Defs: The relation between a neuron projection bundle and a neuron projection that is fasciculated with it.

label: evolutionarily related to
Defs: A relationship that holds via some environmental process

label: has mesoparasite
Defs: inverse of mesoparasite of

label: develops into
Defs: inverse of develops from

label: process has causal agent
Defs: Inverse of \'causal agent in process\'

label: has exposure transport path
Defs: A broad relationship between an exposure event or process and the course takes from the source to the target.

label: results in adhesion of
Defs: The relationship that links anatomical entities with a process that results in the adhesion of two or more entities via the non-covalent interaction of molecules expressed in, located in, and/or adjacent to, those entities.

label: transports or maintains localization of
Defs: Holds between p and c when p is a localization process (localization covers maintenance of localization as well as its establishment)  and the outcome of this process is to regulate the localization of c.

label: directly activates
Defs: p directly activates q if and only if p is immediately upstream of q and p is the realization of a function to increase the rate or activity of q

label: immersed in
Defs: "immersed in" is a relation between a (physical) entity and a fluid substance in which the entity is wholely or substantially surrounded by the substance.

label: member of
Defs: is member of is a mereological relation between a item and a collection.

label: has material basis in somatic mutation in
decreased_in_magnitude_relative_to
Defs: q1 decreased_in_magnitude_relative_to q2 if and only if magnitude(q1) < magnitude(q2). Here, magnitude(q) is a function that maps a quality to a unit-invariant scale.

label: enabled by
Defs: inverse of enables

label: concretizes
Defs: A relationship between a specifically dependent continuant and a generically dependent continuant, in which the generically dependent continuant depends on some independent continuant in virtue of the fact that the specifically dependent continuant also depends on that same independent continuant. Multiple specifically dependent continuants can concretize the same generically dependent continuant.

label: symbiotically interacts with
Defs: A biotic interaction in which the two organisms live together in more or less intimate association.

label: has_specified_input
Defs: A relation between a planned process and a continuant participating in that process that is not created during  the process. The presence of the continuant during the process is explicitly specified in the plan specification which the process realizes the concretization of.

label: kleptoparasite of
Defs: A sub-relation of parasite of in which a parasite steals resources from another organism, usually food or nest material

label: overlaps
Defs: x overlaps y iff they have some part in common.

label: is active in
Defs: c executes activity in d if and only if c enables p and p occurs_in d.  Assuming no action at a distance by gene products, if a gene product enables (is capable of) a process that occurs in some structure, it must have at least some part in that structure.

label: axon synapses in
Defs: Relation between a neuron and some structure its axon forms (chemical) synapses in.

label: developmentally induced by
Defs: t1 induced_by t2 if there is a process of developmental induction (GO:0031128) with t1 and t2 as interacting participants. t2 causes t1 to change its fate from a precursor anatomical structure type T to T\', where T\' develops_from T

label: composed primarily of
Defs: x composed_primarily_of y if and only if more than half of the mass of x is made from y or units of the same type as y.

label: phenotype of
Defs: inverse of has phenotype

label: has end point
Defs: A relation between an axis and a part of an organism, in which the part defines the initial point of the axis.

label: has substance removed
Defs: "has substance removed" is a relation existing between two physical entities in which the first entity has had the second entity (a substance) removed from it at some point in time.

label: condition ameliorated by
Defs: A relationship between a condition (a phenotype or disease) and an entity (e.g. a chemical, environmental exposure, or some form of genetic variation) where some or all aspects of the condition are reduced or eliminated by the presence of the entity.

label: receives synaptic input in
Defs: A relationship between a neuron and a region, where the neuron has a functionally relevant number of input synapses in that region.

label: has participant
Defs: a relation between a process and a continuant, in which the continuant is somehow involved in the process

label: directly_associated_with
Defs: q1 directly_associated_with q2 iff q1 is dependent on q2, and the magnitude of q1 increases if the magnitude of q2 is increased, or the magnitude of q1 decreases if the magnitude of q2 is decreased. The relationship is not necessarily linear.

label: causes condition
Defs: A relationship between an entity (e.g. a genotype, genetic variation, chemical, or environmental exposure) and a condition (a phenotype or disease), where the entity has some causal role for the condition.

label: ecologically co-occurs with
Defs: An interaction relationship describing organisms that often occur together at the same time and space or in the same environment.

label: intercellular endoparasite of
Defs: A sub-relation of endoparasite-of in which the parasite inhabits the spaces between host cells.

label: immediately right of
Defs: x immediately right of y iff x right of y and x is contiguous with y.

label: is causal gain of function germline mutation of in
Defs: Relates a gene to condition, such that a mutation in this gene in a germ cell provides a new function of the corresponding product and that is sufficient to produce the condition and that can be passed on to offspring[modified from orphanet].

label: towards
Defs: q towards e2 if and only if q is a relational quality such that q inheres-in some e, and e != e2 and q is dependent on e2

label: imports
Defs: Holds between p and c when p is a transportation or localization process and the outcome of this process is to move c to a destination that is part of some s, where the start location of c is part of the region that surrounds s.

label: lumen of
Defs: x lumen_of y iff x is the space or substance that is part of y and does not cross any of the inner membranes or boundaries of y that is maximal with respect to the volume of the convex hull.

label: is quality specification of
Defs: A relation between a data item and a quality of a material entity where the material entity is the specified output of a material transformation which achieves an objective specification that indicates the intended value of the specified quality.

label: ends with
Defs: x ends with y if and only if x has part y and the time point at which x ends is equivalent to the time point at which y ends. Formally: α(y) > α(x) ∧ ω(y) = ω(x), where α is a function that maps a process to a start point, and ω is a function that maps a process to an end point.

label: in paraxenology relationship with
Defs: Xenology that is characterized by multiple horizontal transfer events, resulting in the presence of two or more copies of the foreign gene in the host genome.

label: results in maturation of
Defs: The relationship that links an entity with a process that results in the progression of the entity over time that is independent of changes in it\'s shape and results in an end point state of that entity.

label: in syntenic orthology relationship with
Defs: Syntenic homology that involves chromosomes of different species.

label: kleptoparasitized by
Defs: inverse of kleptoparasite of

label: disease causes disruption of
Defs: A relationship between a disease and a process where the disease process disrupts the execution of the process.

label: has quality
Defs: a relation between an independent continuant (the bearer) and a quality, in which the quality specifically depends on the bearer for its existence

label: in structural homology relationship with
Defs: Homology that is defined by similarity with regard to selected structural parameters.

label: in semi-orthology relationship with
Defs: 1:many orthology that involves a gene in species A and its ortholog in species B, when duplications more recent than the species split have occurred in species A but not in species B.

label: disease has infectious agent
Defs: A relationship between a disease and an infectious agent where the material basis of the disease is an infection with some infectious agent.

label: postaxial to
Defs: x preaxial to y iff x is further along the preaxial-postaxial axis than y, towards the postaxial side.

label: in 1 to 1 homology relationship with
Defs: Historical homology that involves two members sharing no other homologs in the lineages considered.

label: trophically interacts with
Defs: An interaction relationship in which the partners are related via a feeding relationship.

label: has phenotype
Defs: A relationship that holds between a biological entity and a phenotype. Here a phenotype is construed broadly as any kind of quality of an organism part, a collection of these qualities, or a change in quality or qualities (e.g. abnormally increased temperature). The subject of this relationship can be an organism (where the organism has the phenotype, i.e. the qualities inhere in parts of this organism), a genomic entity such as a gene or genotype (if modifications of the gene or the genotype causes the phenotype), or a condition such as a disease (such that if the condition inheres in an organism, then the organism has the phenotype).

label: proximalmost part of
Defs: X proximalmost part of Y <=> X is in proximal side of Y and X is adjacent to the proximal boundary of Y

label: functionally related to
Defs: A grouping relationship for any relationship directly involving a function, or that holds because of a function of one of the related entities.

label: in parallelism relationship with
Defs: Homoplasy that involves homologous underlying mechanisms or structures.

label: intracellular endoparasite of
Defs: A sub-relation of endoparasite-of in which the parasite inhabits host cells.

label: in apomorphy relationship with
Defs: Historical homology that is based on recent shared ancestry, characterizing a monophyletic group.

label: in 1 to many orthology relationship with
Defs: Orthology that involves two genes when duplications more recent than the species split have occurred in one species but not the other.

label: has material basis in gain of function germline mutation in
in regulogy relationship with
Defs: Historical homology that involves orthologous pairs of transcription factors and downstream regulated genes in different organisms.

label: has evidence
Defs: inverse of is evidence for

label: inheres in
Defs: a relation between a specifically dependent continuant (the dependent) and an independent continuant (the bearer), in which the dependent specifically depends on the bearer for its existence

label: in homeosis relationship with
Defs: Biological homology that involves an ectopic structure and the normally positioned structure.

label: capable of positively regulating
Defs: Holds between c and p if and only if c is capable of some activity a, and a positively regulates p.

label: developmentally succeeded by
Defs: Inverse of developmentally preceded by

label: developmentally induces
Defs: Inverse of developmentally induced by

label: existence starts during
Defs: x existence starts during y if and only if the time point at which x starts is after or equivalent to the time point at which y starts and before or equivalent to the time point at which y ends. Formally: x existence starts during y iff α(x) >= α(y) & α(x) <= ω(y).

label: drains
Defs: Relation between an collecting structure and another structure, where the collecting structure acts as a conduit channeling fluid, substance or energy away from the other structure.

label: has component process
Defs: w \'has process component\' p if p and w are processes,  w \'has part\' p and w is such that it can be directly disassembled into into n parts p, p2, p3, ..., pn, where these parts are of similar type.

label: increases by expression quantity of
Defs:
The entity A has an activity that up-regulates by expression the quantity of B. The up-regulation is due to A having an effect on an intermediate entity (typically a DNA or mRNA element) which can produce B.

For example, protein A (transcription factor) indirectly increases by expression the quantity of protein B (gene product) if and only if A positively regulates the process of transcription or translation of a nucleic acid element that produces B.

label: in homocracy relationship with
Defs: Similarity that is characterized by the organization of anatomical structures through the expression of homologous or identical patterning genes.

label: posterior to
Defs: x posterior to y iff x is further along the antero-posterior axis than y, towards the body/tail. An antero-posterior axis is an axis that extends through an organism from head end to opposite end of body or tail.

label: is small molecule activator
Defs: a relation between a continuant and a process, in which the continuant is a small molecule that activates the process

label: directly positively regulates
Defs: Process(P1) directly postively regulates process(P2) iff: P1 positively regulates P2 via direct physical interaction between an agent executing P1 (or some part of P1) and an agent executing P2 (or some part of P2).  For example, if protein A has protein binding activity(P1) that targets protein B and this binding positively regulates the kinase activity (P2) of protein B then P1 directly positively regulates P2.

label: has intermediate
Defs: p has intermediate c if and only if p has parts p1, p2 and p1 has output c, and p2 has input c

label: results in transport across
Defs: Holds between p and m when p is a transportation or localization process and the outcome of this process is to move c from one location to another, and the route taken by c follows a path that crosses m.

label: has modifier
Defs: A relation that holds between an attribute or a qualifier and another attribute.

label: immediately causally upstream of
Defs: p is immediately causally upstream of q iff both (a) p immediately precedes q and (b) p is causally upstream of q. In addition, the output of p  must be an input of q.

label: causally influences
Defs: The entity or characteristic A is causally upstream of the entity or characteristic B, A having an effect on B. An entity corresponds to any biological type of entity as long as a mass is measurable. A characteristic corresponds to a particular specificity of an entity (e.g., phenotype, shape, size).

label: in mimicry relationship with
Defs: Convergence that results from co-evolution usually involving an evolutionary arms race.

label: root parasite of
Defs: A parasite-of relationship in which the host is a plant and the parasite that attaches to the host root (PO:0009005)

label: in lateral side of
Defs: X in lateral side of Y <=> if X is in left side of Y or X is in right side of Y. X is often, but not always a paired structure

label: negatively regulated by
Defs: inverse of negatively regulates

label: disease arises from structure
Defs: A relationship between a disease and an anatomical structure where the material basis of the disease is some pathological change in the structure.

label: involved in regulation of
Defs: c involved in regulation of p if c is involved in some p\' and p\' regulates some p

label: existence starts during or after
Defs: x existence starts during or after y if and only if the time point at which x starts is after or equivalent to the time point at which y starts. Formally: x existence starts during or after y iff α (x) >= α (y).

label: disease relationship
Defs: This relation groups  relations between diseases and any other kind of entity.

label: has end sequence
Defs: x has end sequence y if the end of x is identical to the end of y, and x has y as a subsequence

label: has intracellular endoparasite
Defs: inverse of intracellular endoparasite of

label: active ingredient in
Defs: inverse of has active ingredient

label: results in structural organization of
Defs: A relationship between a process and an anatomical entity such that the process contributes to the act of creating the structural organization of the anatomical entity.

label: luminal space of
Defs: s is luminal space of x iff s is lumen_of x and s is an immaterial entity

label: in neoteny relationship with
Defs: Paedomorphosis that is produced by a retardation of somatic development.

label: results in commitment to
Defs: p \'results in commitment to\' c if and only if p is a developmental process and c is a cell and p results in the state of c changing such that is can only develop into a single cell type.

label: acts upstream of
Defs: c acts upstream of p if and only if c enables some f that is involved in p\' and p\' occurs chronologically before p, is not part of p, and affects the execution of p. c is a material entity and f, p, p\' are processes.

label: quality is specified as
Defs: inverse of the relation of is quality specification of

label: obsolete in neural circuit with
Defs: OBSOLETE A relation that holds between two neurons connected directly via a synapse, or indirectly via a series of synaptically connected neurons.

label: has potential to directly develop into
Defs: x has potential to directly develop into y iff x directly develops into y or x is capable of directly developing into y

label: in equivalogy relationship with
Defs: Historical homology that involves functional equivalent genes with retention of the ancestral function.

label: preyed upon by
Defs: inverse of preys on

label: ubiquitously expresses
Defs: inverse of ubiquiotously expressed in

label: attached to
Defs: a is attached to b if and only if a and b are discrete objects or object parts, and there are physical connections between a and b such that a force pulling a will move b, or a force pulling b will move a

label: contributes to frequency of condition
Defs: A relationship between an entity (e.g. a genotype, genetic variation, chemical, or environmental exposure) and a condition (a phenotype or disease), where the entity influences the frequency of the condition in a population.

label: adjacent to
Defs: x adjacent to y if and only if x and y share a boundary.

label: immediate transformation of
Defs: x immediate transformation of y iff x immediately succeeds y temporally at a time boundary t, and all of the matter present in x at t is present in y at t, and all the matter in y at t is present in x at t

label: proximal to
Defs: x proximal to y iff x is closer to the point of attachment with the body than y.

label: distalmost part of
Defs: X distalmost part of Y <=> X is in distal side of Y and X is adjacent to the distal boundary of Y

label: mesoparasite of
Defs: A sub-relation of parasite-of in which the parasite is partially an endoparasite and partially an ectoparasite

label: preaxial to
Defs: x preaxial to y iff x is further along the preaxial-postaxial axis than y, towards the front.

label: function of
Defs: a relation between a function and an independent continuant (the bearer), in which the function specifically depends on the bearer for its existence

label: overlaps sequence of
Defs: x overlaps the sequence of x if and only if x has a subsequence z and z is a subsequence of y.

label: has material basis in germline mutation in
in left side of
Defs: X in left side of Y <=> if Y is subdivided into two left and right portions, X is part of the left portion.

label: opposite to
Defs: Direcly opposite to. i.e. on the opposite side through the axis.

label: expresses
Defs: Inverse of \'expressed in\'

label: transformation of
Defs: x transformation of y if x is the immediate transformation of y, or is linked to y through a chain of transformation relationships

label: is concretized as
Defs: A relationship between a generically dependent continuant and a specifically dependent continuant, in which the generically dependent continuant depends on some independent continuant in virtue of the fact that the specifically dependent continuant also depends on that same independent continuant. A generically dependent continuant may be concretized as multiple specifically dependent continuants.

label: existence ends at start of
Defs: holds between x and y if and only if the time point at which x ends is equivalent to the time point at which y starts. Formally: iff ω(x) = α(y).

label: has epiphyte
Defs: inverse of epiphyte of

label: precedes
Defs: x precedes y if and only if the time point at which x ends is before or equivalent to the time point at which y starts. Formally: x precedes y iff ω(x) <= α(y), where α is a function that maps a process to a start point, and ω is a function that maps a process to an end point.

label: causally upstream of or within
Defs: p \'causally upstream or within\' q iff (1) the end of p is before the end of q and (2) the execution of p exerts some causal influence over the outputs of q; i.e. if p was abolished or the outputs of p were to be modified, this would necessarily affect q.

label: only in taxon
Defs: x only in taxon y if and only if x is in taxon y, and there is no other organism z such that y!=z a and x is in taxon z.

label: has role
Defs: a relation between an independent continuant (the bearer) and a role, in which the role specifically depends on the bearer for its existence

label: is subsequence of
Defs: inverse of has subsequence

label: is causal germline mutation partially giving rise to
Defs: Relates a gene to condition, such that a mutation in this gene partially contributes to the presentation of this condition[modified from orphanet].

label: in out-paralogy relationship with
Defs: Paralogy that results from a duplication preceding a given speciation event.

label: has primary input
Defs: p has primary input c if (a) p has input c and (b) the goal of process is to modify, consume, or transform c.

label: correlated with
Defs: A relationship that holds between two entities, where the entities exhibit a statistical dependence relationship. The entities may be statistical variables, or they may be other kinds of entities such as diseases, chemical entities or processes.

label: acts upstream of or within, positive effect
generically depends on
Defs: A generically dependent continuant *b* generically depends on an independent continuant *c* at time *t* means: there inheres in *c* a specifically deendent continuant which concretizes *b* at *t*.

label: immediately anterior to
Defs: x immediately anterior to y iff x anterior to y and x is contiguous with y.

label: tracheates
Defs: The relationship that holds between a trachea or tracheole and an antomical structure that is contained in (and so provides an oxygen supply to).

label: realized in response to
Defs: r \'realized in response to\' s iff, r is a realizable (e.g. a plant trait such as responsivity to drought), s is an environmental stimulus (a process), and s directly causes the realization of r.

label: has sensory dendrite in
Defs: Relation between a sensory neuron and some structure in which it receives sensory input via a sensory dendrite.

label: in serial homology relationship with
Defs: Iterative homology that involves structures arranged along the main body axis.

label: has ectoparasite
Defs: inverse of ectoparasite of

label: regulates levels of
Defs: p regulates levels of c if p regulates some amount (PATO:0000070) of c

label: transports
Defs: Holds between p and c when p is a transport process or transporter activity and the outcome of this p is to move c from one location to another.

label: enables subfunction
Defs: Holds between an entity and an process P where the entity enables some larger compound process, and that larger process has-part P.

label: obsolete has direct output
Defs: p has direct input c iff c is a participanti n p, c is present at the end of p, and c is not present at the beginning of c.

label: correlated with condition
Defs: A relationship between an entity and a condition (phenotype or disease) with which it exhibits a statistical dependence relationship.

label: capable of
Defs: A relation between a material entity (such as a cell) and a process, in which the material entity has the ability to carry out the process.

label: has synaptic terminal in
Defs: A general relation between a neuron and some structure in which it either chemically synapses to some target or in which it receives (chemical) synaptic input.

label: involved in or involved in regulation of
Defs: c involved in or regulates p if and only if either (i) c is involved in p or (ii) c is involved in regulation of p

label: causal relationship with disease as subject
synapsed_by_via_type_II_bouton
Defs: Relation between a muscle and a motor neuron that synapses to it via a type II bouton.

label: developmentally contributes to
Defs: inverse of has developmental contribution from

label: has function
Defs: a relation between an independent continuant (the bearer) and a function, in which the function specifically depends on the bearer for its existence

label: colocalizes with
Defs: a colocalizes_with b if and only if  a is transiently or peripherally associated with b[GO].

label: occurent part of
Defs: A part of relation that applies only between occurents.

label: part_of
Defs: a core relation that holds between a part and its whole

label: has substance added
Defs: "has substance added" is a relation existing between a (physical) entity and a substance in which the entity has had the substance added to it at some point in time.

label: is sequentially aligned with
Defs: x is sequentially aligned with if a significant portion bases of x and y correspond in terms of their base type and their relative ordering

label: exports
Defs: Holds between p and c when p is a transportation or localization process and the outcome of this process is to move c to a destination that is part of some s, where the end location of c is part of the region that surrounds s.

label: in pro-orthology relationship with
Defs: 1:many orthology that involves a gene in species A and one of its ortholog in species B, when duplications more recent than the species split have occurred in species B but not in species A.

label: synapsed_via_type_III_bouton_to
Defs: A relation between a motor neuron and a muscle that it synapses to via a type III bouton.

label: has target start location
Defs: This relationship holds between p and l when p is a transport or localization process in which the outcome is to move some cargo c from some initial location l to some destination.

label: hyperparasitized by
Defs: inverse of hyperparasite of

label: in xenology relationship with
Defs: Historical homology that is characterized by an interspecies (horizontal) transfer since the common ancestor.

label: involved in negative regulation of
Defs: c involved in regulation of p if c is involved in some p\' and p\' negatively regulates some p

label: capable of inhibiting or preventing pathological process
Defs: Holds between a material entity c and a pathological process p if and only if c is capable of some activity a, where a inhibits p.

label: positively regulates
Defs: Process(P1) postively regulates process(P2) iff: P1 initiates P2, or P1 increases the the frequency of initiation of P2 or the magnitude or rate of output of P2.

label: causal agent in process
Defs: A relationship between a material entity and a process where the material entity has some causal role that influences the process

label: developmentally preceded by
Defs: Candidate definition: x developmentally related to y if and only if there exists some developmental process (GO:0032502) p such that x and y both participates in p, and x is the output of p and y is the input of p

label: existence starts with
Defs: x starts ends with y if and only if the time point at which x starts is equivalent to the time point at which y starts. Formally: x existence starts with y iff α(x) = α(y).

label: synapsed_via_type_II_bouton_to
Defs: A relation between a motor neuron and a muscle that it synapses to via a type II bouton.

label: immediately left of
Defs: x immediately left of y iff x left_of y and x is contiguous with y.

label: regulates transport of
Defs: A relationship that holds between a  process that regulates a transport process and the entity transported by that process.

label: has start sequence
Defs: x has start sequence y if the start of x is identical to the start of y, and x has y as a subsequence

label: partially overlaps
Defs: x partially overlaps y iff there exists some z such that z is part of x and z is part of y, and it is also the case that neither x is part of y or y is part of x

label: output of
Defs: inverse of has output

label: conduit for
Defs: x is a conduit for y iff y overlaps through the lumen_of of x, and y has parts on either side of the lumen of x.

label: is quality measured as
Defs: inverse of the relation of is quality measurement of

label: negatively regulates
Defs: Process(P1) negatively regulates process(P2) iff: P1 terminates P2, or P1 descreases the the frequency of initiation of P2 or the magnitude or rate of output of P2.

label: in isoorthology relationship with
Defs: Orthology that involves functional equivalent genes with retention of the ancestral function.

label: developmentally replaces
Defs: x developmentally replaces y if and only if there is some developmental process that causes x to move or to cease to exist, and for the site that was occupied by x to become occupied by y, where y either comes into existence in this site or moves to this site from somewhere else

label: immediately dorsal to
Defs: x immediately dorsal to y iff x dorsal to y and x is contiguous with y.

label: relation between physical entity and a process or stage
regulates in other organism
Defs: x \'regulates in other organism\' y if and only if: (x is the realization of a function to exert an effect on the frequency, rate or extent of y) AND (the agents of x are produced by organism o1 and the agents of y are produced by organism o2).

label: has gene product
Defs: x has gene product y if and only if x is a gene (SO:0000704) that participates in some gene expression process (GO:0010467) where the output of that process is either y or something that is ribosomally translated from y

label: decreases by repression quantity of
Defs:
The entity A has an activity that down-regulates by repression the quantity of B. The down-regulation is due to A having an effect on an intermediate entity (typically a DNA or mRNA element) which can produce B.

For example, protein A (transcription factor) indirectly decreases by repression the quantity of protein B (gene product) if and only if A negatively regulates the process of transcription or translation of a nucleic acid element that produces B.

label: has exposure route
Defs: A broad relationship between an exposure event or process and a process by which the exposure stressor comes into contact with the exposure receptor

label: existence starts at end of
Defs: holds between x and y if and only if the time point at which x starts is equivalent to the time point at which y ends. Formally: iff α(x) = ω(y).

label: continuous with
Defs: X continuous_with Y if and only if X and Y share a fiat boundary.

label: sends synaptic output throughout
Defs: A relationship between a neuron and a region, where the neuron has a functionally relevant number output synapses distributed throughout that region (rather than confined to a subregion).

label: input of
Defs: inverse of has input

label: has partial material basis in germline mutation in
